title: honey's marinade
directions: Mix all ingredients well and marinate in refrigerator.
Great for chicken wings, pork or steak tips.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients.
Mix carefully in bowl.
Mix dressing of mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar.
Pour over and let mellow for 4 to 5 hours.
Serve.

title: chicken gumbo
directions: Place chicken in large pot with water and celery tops.
Boil until chicken is tender.
Remove chicken and set aside until cool. Debone and chop chicken.
Add vegetables, celery, onion, okra, corn, lima beans, mixed vegetables and tomatoes to broth; boil approximately 30 to 40 minutes stirring occasionally.
Add chicken and rice and boil 30 minutes more.
May add water if needed.

title: barbecue green beans
directions: Brown bacon and onions.
Combine catsup, brown sugar and Worcestershire sauce.
Simmer 2 minutes.
Layer green beans in a casserole.
Pour sauce over beans.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes, or microwave on High for 8 minutes.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Butter both sides of frozen bread and cut into cubes.
Spread cubes over bottom of a 9x13-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle sausage over bread; then sprinkle cheese over sausage.
Combine half and half, eggs, salt and dry mustard.
Pour over layered bread, sausage and cheese and refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350 degrees for 30 minutes.

title: soft ginger cookies
directions: Combine molasses with sugar, shortening and water.
Add the vanilla, vinegar and ginger.
Add the egg.
Mix together cinnamon, nutmeg, salt, baking soda and flour.
Add to the batter.
Mix thoroughly.
Bake at 350° for about 15 minutes.

title: zucchini cheeseburgers
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large bowl.
Form into patties and fry in oil.
Serve on toasted buns with cheese, lettuce and tomato.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: lemon loaf
directions: Cream butter, 1 cup sugar and eggs.
Beat until light and fluffy.
Add milk alternately with flour that has been blended with baking powder.
Mix well.
Add lemon rind and nuts.
Bake in 8 1/2 x 4 x 2-inch loaf pan at 350° for 1 hour.
Remove from oven. Combine lemon juice with 1/4 cup sugar; pour over hot bread.
Let stand until cool before removing from pan.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Mix well with mixer.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Makes 2 layer cake or tube pan.

title: joe willis's transparent pie
directions: In top part of double boiler, melt butter and sugar.
Add salt; beat eggs and combine with butter and sugar mixture.
Add corn syrup and vanilla.
Cook and stir constantly until all sugar has dissolved completely and mixture is smooth.
Pour mixture into pie or tart shells.
Bake approximately 30 minutes at 350°.
After 15 minutes oven can be turned down to 300° and pies can cook longer.
This is wonderful, like pecan pie without the pecans, a Southern recipe.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Drop by small tablespoons onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° until lightly browned.

title: hot cocoa mix
directions: Combine equal amounts of ingredients.
Place 2 or 3 teaspoons of mixture in a cup of hot water.

title: nutmeg sauce(for donut pudding)
directions: Mix butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Blend egg yolks, flour and vanilla into the first mixture.
Gradually add the butter-egg mixture to the boiling water.
Cook slowly until thickened.
Add nutmeg.
Stir well.
Remove from heat.
Pour over donut pudding which is served in cereal-type bowls for each serving.
Two to three heaping tablespoonfuls of donut pudding makes a nice serving.

title: marble squares
directions: Combine margarine, water and chocolate in saucepan; bring to boil.
Remove from heat.
Stir in combined flour, 2 cups sugar, baking soda and salt.
Add 2 eggs and sour cream; mix well.
Pour into greased and floured 15 x 10 x 1-inch jelly roll pan.
Combine cream cheese and 1/3 cup sugar, mixing until well blended.
Blend in 1 egg; spoon over chocolate batter.
Cut through batter several times for marble effect. Sprinkle with chocolate pieces.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Yields about 2 dozen.

title: green bean supreme
directions: Cook green beans until tender (10 to 15 minutes).
Melt margarine in a small saucepan.
Saute onions until lightly brown. Stir in salt and flour.
Gradually add evaporated milk.
Cook over medium-high heat until thickened.
Add cheese and cook until cheese melts.
Combine cooked green beans and cheese sauce.
Pour into 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Combine bread crumbs and melted margarine; sprinkle over green bean mixture.
Bake in a moderate 350° oven for 15 to 20 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: bacon cheese spread
directions: Cook bacon, drain and crumble. In a bowl mix bacon, onion, cheese, and salad dressing and chill.

title: brandy cheese dip
directions: Combine ingredients until smooth and fluffy in an electric mixer.
Serve with unsalted crackers, rye toast or wedges of unpeeled apples or pears.
Makes about 1 1/2 cups.

title: sweet and sour 3 bean salad
directions: Drain, rinse and combine first 3 ingredients.
Add remaining ingredients.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: sweet and sour sauce
directions: Combine sugar and vinegar in a pan.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until sugar dissolves.
Remove from heat.
Stir in mustard, ginger and pineapple.
Combine cornstarch and juice, stirring until blended.
Gradually stir about 1/4 of hot mixture into cornstarch mixture.
Add remaining hot mixture, stirring constantly.
Cook over medium heat until smooth and thickened. Yield:
1 1/2 cups.

title: poppin' fresh barbecups
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
In skillet brown ground beef.
Add onion; cook until tender.
Drain excess fat.
Add barbecue sauce and brown sugar.
Separate dough into 10 biscuits.
Place each biscuit in ungreased muffin cup, pressing dough to cover bottom and sides. Spoon meat mixture into each cup.
Sprinkle each with cheese. Bake 10 to 12 minutes, until golden brown.
Serve immediately. Makes 10 barbecups.

title: italian meat loaf
directions: Mix well and place in dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
tags: Del Monte Italian style stewed tomatoes

title: taco dip
directions: On a platter, layer the bean dip, then sauce.
Sprinkle the chopped tomatoes, as desired.
Top with shredded lettuce and then shred cheese over the lettuce.
Use tostados or Fritos to scarf down this tasty dish.

title: sandwich spread
directions: Put all ingredients in large pan and cook over medium heat until thick.
Fill jars and seal.
Add a few hot peppers to make hot spread.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: In a saucepan, heat and stir together the milk and cheese until blended; remove from heat.
In a mixing bowl, gradually stir hot mixture into eggs.
Add stuffing, broccoli and 1/4 teaspoon salt; mix well.
Turn mixture into a greased 1 1/2-quart casserole pan.
Bake, uncovered, at 325° for 45 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: triple layer cookie bars
directions: Preheat oven to 325° for glass pan or 350° for aluminum.
Melt butter in a 9 x 13-inch pan while oven is heating.
Sprinkle crumbs evenly over butter.
Top evenly with coconut and drizzle sweetened condensed milk over coconut.
Bake for 25 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: instant hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix well together and store in tight container.
Use 2 tablespoons of mix per cup hot water for hot chocolate.

title: chicken and asparagus casserole
directions: Line bottom of 9 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish with asparagus. Place chicken over asparagus.
Mix together soup, mayonnaise, lemon juice and curry powder.
Pour over chicken.
Sprinkle cheese over top.
Cover with foil and bake at 375° for 30 minutes. Serves 4.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Brown meat in skillet with salad oil.
Take meat out; saute onion in oil.
Add all ingredients and mix well.
Add meat and simmer until tender, approximately one hour.
Good with chicken, pork chops and deer.

title: bacon roll-ups
directions: Slice bacon strips in half.
Roll up with water chestnut in middle.
Secure with toothpick.
Place on broiler pan in 375° oven and bake until brown.
Drain and place in 3 1/2 quart casserole dish.
Mix catsup and brown sugar.
Poor over roll-ups and bake 15 minutes in 375° oven.

title: mother's helper dessert
directions: Stir pudding into fruit cocktail (juice and all) with a spoon. Add Cool Whip until thick.
Stir in sliced bananas to your taste. Refrigerate for a while to cool.
Serve for dessert.

title: quick cordon bleu
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease large cookie sheet.
Mix chicken, ham, cheese and mushrooms in large bowl.
Spoon into center of each crescent.
Fold closed, pinching ends.
Bake 18 to 24 minutes.

title: brown sugar cookies
directions: Add sugar to soft butter; cream well.
Add eggs; beat until well mixed.
Sift the soda with the flour.
Add gradually to the mixture; blend well.
Add chopped nuts.
Drop onto buttered cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: creamy fruit salad
directions: Stir fruits together and add dry pudding mix.
Mix until smooth and chill.

title: bologna candy
directions: Combine sugar
and milk.
Cook to soft ball stage.
Add dates and cook
until
mixture leaves the side of the pan when it is stirred.
Remove
from
heat.
Stir in coconut and nuts; cool slightly.
Turn
out
on
a wet towel.
Shape into a roll and refrigearte.
When cold, slice into 1/4-inch slices.

title: corn bread pie
directions: Brown ground beef; drain.
Add onion, bell pepper, chili powder, corn, salt and pepper.
Add tomato soup and 1 1/2 cans water.
Stir together (should be soupy) and simmer about 15 minutes.

title: mrs. field's cookies
directions: Cream together the sugar, butter and brown sugar. Add eggs and vanilla.
In a separate bowl, combine flour, oatmeal (which is blenderized in small amounts until fine with blender), baking powder and baking soda.
Mix all ingredients together and add chocolate chips, grated Hershey bar and chopped nuts.
Place golf ball size cookies 2-inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 375° for 6 minutes.

title: italian spaghetti and meat ball sauce
directions: In a 5-quart Dutch oven or a 4 to 6-quart pressure cooker, fry out garlic in oil.
Add onions and fry until limp or light brown. Add tomatoes, seasonings, salt and pepper to taste and tomato paste.

title: lasagna
directions: Take some cheese.
Pour pizza sauce in a pan.
Add together. Pour it over shells.
Let it freeze for a day.
Put aluminum foil over it.
Take foil off and cook it.

title: moist fruitcake
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition. Sift 1 1/2 cups flour with baking powder; add alternately with flavorings to creamed mixture.

Sprinkle remaining flour over nuts and fruits; add to batter. Place brown paper in bottom of a tube cake pan; grease bottom and sides. Place broiler pan containing water under cake pan in oven. Bake for 2 hours and 30 minutes at 250°.

title: corn chowder
directions: Simmer water, onion, celery, potato and parsley until half cooked (about 10 minutes).
Add corn.
Simmer gently until nearly done (not more than a few minutes).
Add milk and bring the soup just to the boiling point without actually boiling.
Add seasonings and correct to taste.
Serve very hot!
Serves 4 to 6.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix graham cracker crumbs and butter together and press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Beat confectioners sugar, eggs, butter and vanilla on high for 20 minutes.
Do not underbeat.
Spread over crust.
Add pineapple and bananas.
Top with whipped cream, walnuts and cherries.
Chill one hour or more.
May be served with chocolate sauce if desired.

title: eggs fantastic
directions: Saute crumbled sausage, mushrooms and onion with salt and pepper.
Drain very well on paper towels.
Combine eggs and sour cream in blender and blend for 1 minute.
Pour eggs in a greased 7 1/2 x 11-inch baking dish.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes, until set in the middle.
Spoon hot sauce over eggs and add sausage mix, then layer the 3 cheeses, beginning with the Velveeta.
Casserole may be refrigerated or frozen at this point and baked later.
Bake, uncovered, at 300° for 45 minutes.
Remove from oven and let set 5 to 10 minutes before cutting and serving.

title: pineapple custard angel food dessert
directions: Cook in top of double boiler sugar, salt, flour and egg yolks. Cook until thickened.
Remove from heat.
Add Jell-O.
Set aside to cool.
Add crushed pineapple (do not drain).
Fold mixture into stiffly beaten egg whites.
Pinch angel food cake into small pieces.
Cover bottom of a 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Pour custard mixture over cake.
Top with Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with coconut. Refrigerate overnight.

title: rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add melted margarine and sugar. Next, add flour.
Let rise and store in refrigerator.

title: garlic butter
directions: In a medium bowl, combine butter with garlic, lemon juice, salt, parsley, wine and salad oil. Mix well. Makes 1 1/2 quarts.

title: old fashion egg custard
directions: Beat eggs all together, then add milk, sugar, flour, butter and nutmeg. Beat well.
Pour into an unbaked 9-inch pie shell and bake in a 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Mix in order given.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour. Bake in greased pans.

title: lemonade cake
directions: Bake in a greased and floured Bundt pan at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes. Cool 5 minutes.
Push cake tester into cake, pricking holes (or ice pick) for the Lemon Glaze (all over the cake).

title: peach praline pie
directions: Mixing is the most important step according to Jenna.
She says, "Mix until your arm is very tired!"
Pour into pie shells. Bake at 425° for 15 minutes, then reduce oven to 350° and continue baking for 50 minutes.
Cool on wire rack.
Serve with whipped topping.

title: sweet and sour meatloaf
directions: Mix ground beef, bread crumbs, salt, pepper, onion and half of the tomato sauce.
Form into a loaf, wrap in foil and put into pan.
Bake in 350°F. oven for 50 minutes.

title: summer salad
directions: Fry bacon until crisp; drain.
Cut broccoli and cauliflower into bite size pieces.
Add onion.
Mix together the mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar.
Pour dressing over vegetables and bacon. Refrigerate overnight.
Just before serving, add cheese and mix well.

title: black bean tortilla casserole
directions: Saute the first 4 ingredients a little. Add the piquante sauce, tomatoes, cumin and black beans. Mix ingredients and put a layer in bottom of 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Put a layer of sprinkled cheese on top of mixture. Put tortillas on top of cheese. Repeat layers, ending with bean mixture on top. Bake 35 minutes at 350° covered with foil. Put another layer of cheese on top and bake 10 more minutes. Serve on shredded lettuce. Top with sour cream, chopped black olives and green onions. You and your guests will love this! Serves 8 people.

title: chili
directions: Sprinkle in onion powder.
Try some Old Bay, too.

title: sausage cake
directions: Mix well.
Bake at 350° in a 9 x 13-inch pan for 1 hour or done.

title: ole time hush puppies
directions: Heat the 1 1/2 to 2 cups cooking oil in a deep-sided skillet or heavy-gauge pot.
(Heavy cast-iron pots and pans are best for this type of frying.)
Combine all dry ingredients together in a large bowl.
Add the eggs, buttermilk and onions.
Stir well until you have a coarse batter.
Add the 2 tablespoons of bacon drippings (or oil) and blend well with the other ingredients.

title: chewy chocolate cookies
directions: Cream the butter and sugar in a large mixing bowl.
Add eggs and vanilla; blend well.
Combine flour, cocoa, baking soda and salt in another bowl.
Blend into creamed mixture.
Stir in nuts or chips.
Drop by teaspoon onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 9 minutes.
Cookies will puff during baking and flatten upon cooling.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: black bean soup
directions: In 4-quart saucepot over medium heat, cook onion, garlic, cumin and pepper flakes in oil until onion is tender, about 3 minutes. Remove from heat.
In electric blender, puree 2 cans of beans and their liquid in batches with chicken broth; add to pot.
Stir in remaining beans, salsa and lime juice.
Heat mixture to boil; reduce heat to low.
Simmer for 30 minutes.
Ladle 1 cup of soup into bowl; top with dollop of yogurt.
Serve hot with crackers. Makes ten 1-cup servings.

title: grandma's oatmeal and raisin cookies
directions: Cream the butter and brown sugar together.
Add egg, vanilla and water to creamed mixture.
Add oats, flour, soda and salt. Add nuts and raisins.
Grease cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° for 14 to 16 minutes.

title: old fashioned chess pie
directions: Mix sugars, corn meal and flour.
Add beaten eggs, milk, butter or margarine, vinegar and vanilla.
Mix well.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake in 325° oven for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: beef stew(homemade)
directions: Brown meat and onion in 1 tablespoon shortening.
Add carrots, peas and potatoes; add water, Worcestershire sauce, salt and pepper.
Cook on medium heat, stirring occasionally (approximately 2 to 2 1/2 hours).
Add Kitchen Bouquet; mix cornstarch in small glass of water until dissolved.
Pour into beef stew and cook until thickened.

title: spudnuts
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water and 1 teaspoon sugar.
Set aside. Cook and mash potatoes and measure 2 1/2 cups in large mixing bowl.
Add scalded milk, sugar, salt, butter, vanilla and eggs. Stir well.
When yeast has begun to work, add to mix and stir again and set aside and let stand for 10 minutes.
Mix 14 cups flour into mixture, 1 cup at a time, stirring well after each addition.
Turn onto well floured board and knead in up to 2 cups more flour.
Dough will be quite sticky.
Do not make stiff.
Let raise in a warm place.
Roll out about 3/4-inch thick and then cut with doughnut cutter and place about 1 inch apart on well floured surface.
When doubled, fry in hot fat until light brown.
Drain and sugar or glaze.

title: turkey milanese
directions: Sprinkle turkey with salt and pepper.
Coat with egg white. Roll in bread crumbs and cheese.
Fry in skillet containing 1/4 cup hot oil until brown.
Serves 4.

title: chutney
directions: In medium saucepan, combine apricots and water; set aside 10 minutes.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Bring to boil over high heat; reduce heat and simmer, stir frequently, 10 minutes or until thickened.
Serve warm or chilled.

title: french onion soup
directions: Cook onions in margarine in Dutch oven
or heavy saucepan over medium heat, stirring occasionally, until onions are tender and just beginning to brown.
Sprinkle with flour.
Gradually stir in 1
can of broth, water and Worcestershire sauce.
Stir in remaining broth and water.
Heat to boiling, reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, for 5 minutes.
Place 1 slice of toast in each of 6 ovenproof soup bowls or casseroles.
Pour soup over bread. Sprinkle with cheese.
Set oven control to broil.
Broil soup with tops 3 to 4 inches from heat until cheese is melted and light brown, approximately 5 minutes.

title: cornmeal dumplings-guatemala(chuchitos)
directions: Cut meat into 1 inch cubes and fry in oil over medium heat for 3-4 minutes.
Set aside.
Process the tomatoes, chile pepper. and 2 Tbsp. water into a smooth sauce, set aside.
Mix the masa harina, margarine, 1 1/2 cups cold water and the salt together onto a thick mush.
Put 1/2 cup mush in each wet corn husk, make indentation with finger and add 1 Tbsp. of sauce mix in the indentation.
Add in one chunk of meat into center.
Cover the the stuffing with the mush and wrap the dumpling into a sausage shape with the corn husks.
Steam the dumplins over hot water for 1 1/2 hours.
Unwrap and serve.

title: grape salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add pineapple, pie filling and nuts.
Chill until set.

title: chunky fudge brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Butter and flour a 9 x 9-inch pan. Melt butter and unsweetened chocolate in small saucepan over low heat, stirring constantly. Pour chocolate mixture into large bowl. Whisk in sugar and eggs.
Mix in flour, then nuts and chocolate chunks.
Pour batter into pan.
Bake until tester comes out with moist crumbs attached, about 30 minutes.
Cool brownies in pan on rack.
Cut into squares.

title: edith harris' lemon meringue pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Using mixer at high speed, beat egg yolks until fluffy.
Add condensed milk and lemon juice.
Beat until creamy; pour into pie crust.

title: tater tot hot dish
directions: Brown hamburger and onion.
Put hamburger in bottom of baking dish.
Add green beans on top.
Next, layer Tater Tots in a row on top.
Pour soups over Tater Tots.
Bake in oven at 350° for 45 minutes.
Do not cover.

title: pecan brittle candy
directions: Mix sugar, syrup, salt and water.
Cook over medium heat until sugar dissolves.
Stir in pecans.
Cook until 300° on candy thermometer.
Turn heat off.
Add baking soda and butter.
Pour out on cookie sheet.
Cool.
Break into pieces.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Mix and beat sugar, eggs, oil and buttermilk.
Add to dry ingredients.
Add pineapple, coconut, nuts and carrots.
Mix well.
Bake at 375° in a 9 x 13-inch pan, about 45 to 50 minutes.

title: unmexican haystack
directions: With an electric mixer, blend the first 5 ingredients till smooth.
Chop ham and green onions very fine with a food chopper or food processor, then mix into the cream cheese mixture till blended well.

Place tortilla on plate, with a rubber spatula spread a thin layer of cream cheese/ham mixture on the tortilla. Keep layering tortillas and mix; end with the cream cheese on top, sprinkle with pecans.
Refrigerate a couple hours before serving. Best if prepared the night before-flavors blend together.
I cut into squares with party toothpicks inserted into each square.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Put sliced cheese on top and croutons.
Broil for 5 minutes.

title: monkey bread
directions: Cut each biscuit into 4 pieces.
Mix sugar and cinnamon together.
Roll biscuit pieces into sugar and cinnamon mixture. Arrange biscuit pieces in Bundt pan or a loaf pan.
Sprinkle nuts on top.
Melt butter and stir in brown sugar.
Pour over biscuits and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool for 10 minutes. Remove from pan and place on a serving dish.

title: lime congealed salad
directions: Pour 1 cup boiling water over mixture of first 5 ingredients until dissolved.
Then mix in cottage cheese, pineapple, nuts and whipped cream, no sugar.

title: shrimp potato salad
directions: Boil shrimp and peel.
Cook potatoes and cut.
Boil eggs; peel and chop.
Cool potatoes and eggs.
Mix eggs, mayo, mustard, relish, celery seed, salt, pepper and everglades.

title: magic cookie bars
directions: Layer ingredients as listed in a 9 by 13 baking dish.
Pack down firmly.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until lightly brown and bubbly.

title: cheese ball
directions: Combine one package of cream cheese and sour cream, mixing until well blended.
Spread mixture on bottom and side of one-quart bowl lined with plastic wrap.
Sprinkle with pecans. Combine remaining cream cheese, Cheddar cheese, onions and sherry, mixing at medium speed until well blended.
Press into bowl over pecans.
Chill overnight.
Unmold onto serving plate.
Remove plastic wrap and smooth.
Garnish with pecan halves.
Serve with rye party slices and butter crackers.

title: mandarin bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, beating in one at a time. Add pineapple, oranges and bread cubes.
Mix and put into a 1 1/2-quart greased casserole.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: christmas cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Roll and cut with various shaped cookie cutters.
Bake at 350 degrees for 5 to 10 minutes.

title: cornbread dressing
directions: Saute onions and celery until yellow and limp.
Crumple cornbread into the onion mixture.
Tear bread into fine pieces and add to mixture.
Add broth until mixture is moist, but loosely packed (about 1 1/2 to 2 cups).
Add chopped hard-cooked eggs and slightly beaten eggs.
Season with salt and pepper.* Pour into buttered baking dish.
Cover with oil.
Bake 45 minutes at 325°.

title: banana berry pie
directions: NutraSweet jello and pudding can be used.

title: corn pone
directions: Put meal, sugar and salt in bowl.
Add boiling water.
Stir until smooth.
Let set overnight.
Add flour, egg, baking powder, soda and buttermilk.
Bake in greased iron skillet 15 minutes at 450°.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake 45 minutes longer.

title: happy home
directions: Take 2 heaping cups of patience, 1 heartful of love, 2 handfuls of generosity, dash of laughter and one handful of understanding.
Sprinkle generously with kindness.
Add plenty of faith and mix well.
Spread over a period of a lifetime and serve everybody you meet.

title: chicken marsala(poultry)
directions: Sprinkle chicken pieces with salt and pepper to taste.
Melt butter in skillet.
When very hot, add chicken.
Brown on both sides for about 5 minutes.
Add onion and brown for 2 minutes on a lower flame.
Add water and cover.
Simmer 20 minutes or until tender.
Add Marsala and mushrooms.
Simmer for 10 minutes.
Serve with rice.

title: pumpkin roll
directions: Beat eggs at high speed for 5 minutes.
Beat in sugar.
Stir in pumpkin and lemon juice.
Sift together remaining ingredients. Fold this into mixture.
Grease and flour a 13 x 15-inch cookie sheet, include sides.
Spread mixture onto cookie sheet, sprinkle with 1 cup chopped nuts.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
When done, take dish towel and sprinkle with powdered sugar.
Flip pumpkin roll directly from oven onto the towel and roll up.
Let cool.

title: apple pie cake
directions: *Can use 1/4 cup applesauce to substitute.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Press or roll cookie dough onto greased pizza pan or baking sheet.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.
Cool.
Combine cream cheese, whipped topping and confectioners sugar in a bowl.
Beat well.
Spread over cooled crust.
Top with fruit or your choice.

title: hunting style veal
directions: Brown garlic in cup of Wesson oil.
Lift out.
Cut veal in 1-inch squares.
Brown in oil after garlic is out.
Salt to taste. Begin adding tomato puree a little at a time until it makes a brown gravy.
Add rest of oil.
Wash all seed from green peppers and cut in quarters.
Keep turning them under meat until they are tender.
Takes about 40 minutes.
Serve with rice.

title: potato chip puff-ups
directions: Melt margarine; combine with onion soup mix.
Wrap each cheese block in biscuit dough and roll into a ball.
Dip balls in melted mixture and roll in crushed potato chips.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes on a greased cookie sheet.
Serve hot.
Yields 30 puff-ups.

title: glazed pear shortcake
directions: Grease and flour 8-inch round cake pan.
Drain pears; reserve syrup.
Blend flour, sugar, salt and baking powder in a small bowl.
Cut in butter.
Pour milk over mixture and toss with a fork.
Spoon into cake pan.
Top with pears; brush with syrup and sprinkle with cinnamon.
Bake at 400° until golden brown, approximately 45 minutes.

title: roast beef burritos
directions: Heat oil in skillet and saute garlic and onion until tender. Add beef, tomatoes, chili peppers, cumin and taco sauce.
Simmer 1 hour; thicken with cornstarch by adding cornstarch or 1/4 cup flour to 1 cup cold water.
Heat the tortillas.
Spoon the meat onto the tortillas and roll up.
Heat the enchilada sauce and add the cheese. Stir constantly until cheese melts. Watch so cheese doesn't stick to pan. Spoon red sauce onto burritos and enjoy! Serves 6.

title: no cook chocolate peanut butter yums
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients and pat into an ungreased jelly roll pan.
Smooth top of mixture.
Mix chocolate chips and butter in top of double boiler or microwave.
Spread melted chocolate and peanut butter mixture into bite size squares.
Chill for 30 minutes.

title: california spinach bake
directions: Thaw chopped spinach slightly.
Combine spinach, sour cream, onion soup mix and eggs in medium size bowl; use hand beater and whip thoroughly.
Pour into baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Everyone will want your recipe for this tantalizing dish.

title: melt-away rounds
directions: Cream butter until fluffy.
Add cheese, flour, salt and paprika or poppy seed.
Form a dough.
Chill dough for 2 hours.
Shape into small balls.
Place on greased cookie sheet.
Sprinkle with extra poppy seed or paprika.
Bake balls at 400° for 10 minutes.
Balls should never get browned.
Cool on cookie sheet.
Remove carefully. Store in airtight containers until ready to serve.
Reheat at 400° for a few minutes to serve.
Makes easy and tasty appetizers.

title: low-fat nutty kisses
directions: Beat egg whites until soft peak forms.
Add cream of tartar. Beat again, slowly add sugar and brown sugar, beating after each addition.
Add in vanilla, still beating.
Then, with wooden spoon or plastic spatula, fold in cereal.
Drop by tablespoon on well-sprayed cookie sheet, leaving 1/2-inch space between each one. Bake in 250° oven for 30 minutes.
Turn oven off; leave in oven 30 minutes longer.
Do not open oven at anytime until completely finished.
Yields about 2 1/2 dozen.

title: irish potatoes
directions: Turn out hot potato pulp into a small bowl.
Add sugar, mashing it in. (Potato should be hot enough to melt sugar.)
Add vanilla and coconut and mix well.
Work mixture by kneading until it can be shaped more or less like a miniature potato.

title: company-best meatballs
directions: Combine egg and milk; beat slightly.
Add breadcrumbs and stir until moistened.
Add ground beef, Worcestershire sauce, salt and black pepper.
Mix well and shape into small meatballs.
Brown in skillet sprayed with Pam.
Pour off drippings.
Combine soup and water.
Pour over meatballs.
Cover and simmer for 30 minutes. Serve over rice or noodles.
Yields approximately 24 meatballs.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix ground chuck, green pepper, onion, egg, milk and crackers together by hand.
Bake in oven at 400° for 45 minutes; bring out and spread mushroom soup on top.
Put back in oven for 15 minutes.

title: shrimp artichoke casserole
directions: Grease a 15-inch shallow casserole dish.
Arrange artichokes, halved, on the bottom.
Cover with shrimp.
Saute mushrooms in butter and place on shrimp.

title: scallops nantucket
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Place scallops in four 12-ounce ovenproof casseroles.
Drizzle each portion with 1 tablespoon of clarified butter, 2 tablespoons vermouth and 1 tablespoon lemon juice.
Top with seasoned bread crumbs (see recipe). Place casseroles on jelly roll pan.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes, or until scallops are almost firm.
Top with cheese.
Bake 2 minutes longer, or until cheese is melted.
Garnish with parsley.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream together shortening, both sugars, eggs and vanilla. Stir in peanut butter. Sift together flour, soda and salt. Blend into cream mixture. Drop on ungreased cookie sheet. Press criss-cross pattern with fork dipped in flour. Bake at 350° for about 10 minutes, until light brown.

title: prize winning bread
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients and set aside.
Mix 6 tablespoons sugar, salt, potato flakes and shortening together.
Then add the hot water.
When shortening is melted, add the cold water and yeast mixture.
Add 4 cups flour and beat good.
Then add 2 or more cups flour and stir until very thick.
Then I gradually add the rest of the flour.
This works real good in large mixer with bread hook. Turn out on floured board and knead.
Let rest in oiled bowl until doubled, then put in bread pans.
Let rise another 1/2 hour.
Makes 4 loaves.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: low-fat lasagna
directions: Fry ground turkey and drain.
Add rest of ingredients: spaghetti sauce, onion and pepper.
Boil lasagna noodles (about 6 or 8; I break in half).
In cake pan, lay noodles in bottom, touching each other.
Put cottage cheese, then ground turkey mixture, then 3/4 large package of Mozzarella cheese.
Put another layer of noodles and sprinkle rest of Mozzarella cheese on top. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes to cool before serving.

title: hot clam dip
directions: Soften cheese (in microwave).
In pot, over stove, add all ingredients, stirring until smooth.
Heat gently 5 minutes before serving.
Serve hot with Fritos or Melba rounds.
For a very large crowd, double all ingredients plus 3 or 4 extra ounces of cream cheese.
Serves lots.

title: chocolate delight four layer salad
directions: Mix and press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes.

title: chicken and broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli; drain.
Arrange in bottom of 3-quart baking dish.
Cook and debone chicken.
Break into chunks on top of broccoli.
Mix undiluted soup, mayonnaise, lemon juice and curry powder.
Pour over chicken.
Sprinkle with grated cheese.
Top with bread crumbs tossed in melted margarine.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
(Serves 8 to 10 people.)

title: cheese cake
directions: Combine Milnot, margarine, powdered sugar and graham crackers and line 9 x 13-inch pan.
Save 1 cup to sprinkle on top.

title: corn casserole
directions: Melt the margarine in a 9 x 12-inch baking dish.
Mix all other ingredients.
Stir to mix margarine with other ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes (uncovered).
(May add 1 to 2 chopped jalapeno peppers, if desired.)

title: peanut butter sticks
directions: Cut all crusts from bread.
Slice cut bread into finger slices and set aside.
Bake crust pieces in 300° oven until brown, slightly.
Put crust pieces in blender and make fine crumbs.
Add 1/2 cup sugar to crumb mixture.
In double boiler over hot water, mix peanut butter, oil, 1/2 cup sugar and vanilla.
Stir until warm, but not hot.
Dip bread slices in peanut butter mixture, then roll in crumb mixture.
Store in closed box or tin.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Bring soup bone, ground beef and 3 quarts water to a boil. Reduce heat.
Simmer covered 1 1/2 hours.
Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer covered for 30 minutes.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Mix pudding and pineapple well, then add other ingredients. Stir together; pour into dish or bowl.
Chill.
Keep refrigerated.

title: cheese potatoes
directions: Don't thaw potatoes.
Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: french salad dressing
directions: Mix all together and serve on salad.

title: taco dip
directions: Combine refried beans
and
taco
seasoning;
spread on large platter, then add
green
chilies and onions, layer sour cream next, then lettuce,
tomatoes, black olives and Monterey Jack cheese.
Serve this as dip with nacho chips.

title: millionaire's pie
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large bowl.
Whip.
Pour into graham cracker crusts.
Chill before serving.
Makes 2 pies.
Then enjoy!
Keep refrigerated.

title: abracadabra-or easy on your sanity meal
directions: You may brown your meat a day or two before and season with salt and pepper, if you like.
Place the meat into a crock-pot or slow cooker.
If you would like to do your potatoes at the same time, add them to the meat.
Top with your choice of flavoring. Cook 8 to 9 hours and your whole meal is ready.
You don't have to worry about cooking and the clean-up is a breeze!

title: heavenly hash candy
directions: Brown 5 tablespoons sugar; add milk.
When melted, add 3 cups sugar; add oleo.
Cook until forms a soft ball.
Remove from heat. Add Marshmallow Creme.
Whip.
Add pecans.
Spread on buttered dish.
Let cool and cut.

title: crawfish dip
directions: Make roux with flour and oil.
Add seasonings and saute; add crawfish and cook about 10 minutes.
Add soup, shallots, and parsley.
Cook until desired consistency.

title: barbecued beef brisket
directions: Trim all fat from brisket.
Sprinkle on both sides and rub in the onion, celery and garlic salt.
Sprinkle with 2 teaspoons of sugar, a few drops of liquid smoke and Lea & Perrins.
Wrap in heavy-duty foil overnight in refrigerator.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix ingredients together until blended.
Use as a dip for all your fresh fruits.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Combine beef, onion, green pepper in large dutch oven, cook until meat is browned, stirring to crumble.
Drain well.
Return meat mixture to pan.
Add garlic salt, pepper, oregano, basil, pizza sauce.
Stir well.
Cover, reduce heat, simmer 15 minutes. Cook macaroni according to pkg. directions omitting salt.
Drain. Add to meat mixture.
Stir well.
Spoon into lightly greased 12 x 8 x 2 baking dish.
Top evenly with pepperoni.
Cover and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Top with cheese and bake uncovered 5 minutes. (More cheese can be used if desired.) 6 - 8 servings.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Layer carrots, peppers and onions in casserole.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Bring these ingredients to a boil.
Pour over carrots mixture.
Cover and marinate several hours or overnight.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix and place on cookie sheet in rounded 1-inch balls.
Bake at 350° for about 8 minutes until brown.

title: escoveitched fish
directions: *Recommended fish: King, snapper, Jack, cutlass, sprat or goat fish.

title: cheryl's veggie burgers
directions: Mix well and fry in hot oil on medium heat for 15 minutes for each burger.
Makes 12 to 15 burgers.

title: popcorn balls
directions: Boil to medium hard ball.
Pour over 3 quarts popped popcorn; stir with spoon until cool enough to press into balls.

title: 7-up salad
directions: Mix Jell-O and let cool.
Add 7-Up, pineapple, marshmallows and bananas; let set.

title: never fail biscuits
directions: Mix together.
Roll into lightly floured board.
Roll out. Cut biscuits.
Bake at 475° for 8 to 12 minutes until golden brown.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Deposit noodles into a boiler with warm water.
After noodles have been cooked and noodles are soft, deposit cheese in the pot along with butter and milk.
Stir after all everything has been mixed.
After stirred, you may now serve and enjoy!

title: banana pumpkin bread
directions: Slice bananas into blender.
Puree (2 cups).
Combine and mix bananas, pumpkin, eggs and sugar.
Beat in oil.
Add remaining ingredients.
Stir until just blended.
Pour into 3 greased 8 1/2 x 4 1/2-inch loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: cheesy vegetable macaroni
directions: In a 10-inch skillet over medium heat, in hot oil, cook zucchini with garlic until tender-crisp, stirring occasionally. Stir in spaghetti sauce and Parmesan cheese.
Reduce heat to low. Cover; simmer 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Toss with hot macaroni.
Sprinkle with Mozzarella cheese.
Serve with additional Parmesan cheese, if desired.
Makes 6 cups or 6 servings.

title: broccoli tomato dish
directions: Melt
shortening,
saute
mushrooms
and
garlic.
Add tomato paste,
water
and
wine.	Mix dry ingredients and add slowly to saucepan.
Stir in cheese and cook over low heat for 10 minutes. Layer
everything
and put in greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Bake, uncovered, for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: poppy seed dressing
directions: Add the first 6 ingredients together and mix in blender or food processor, then gradually add the salad oil.

title: broccoli-cauliflower salad
directions: In a large bowl, toss together vegetables.

title: apple coffee cake
directions: Beat eggs and sugar.
Add margarine and vanilla. Mix dry ingredients.
Add to egg mixture alternating with orange juice. Fold in apples.
Grease and flour Bundt pan. Bake at 325° for about 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: garlic roast chicken
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Salt and pepper chicken, putting in a baking pan.
Bake 20 minutes.
Melt butter.
Cut cloves in slices. Brush chicken with butter; sprinkle with garlic.
Bake until chicken is golden and juices run clear when meat is pierced with a knife, 15 to 20 minutes.
Let the chicken rest for 10 to 15 minutes before carving.

title: dry jello salad
directions: Mix Cool Whip and cottage cheese, then add drained pineapple. Stir in jello.
Chill.
Will keep at least 4 days.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Wash mushrooms; pull out stems and place on a baking sheet. Mix the rest of the ingredients together and fill mushrooms.
Bake 5 minutes at 350°.
Broil until tops are light brown.

title: no crust egg pie
directions: Mix butter, sugar and flour.
Add beaten eggs and vanilla, then milk.
Mix well.
Cook for 35 minutes in buttered and floured pie plate.
Put in cold oven; set to 300°.

title: apricot-orange salad
directions: Drain juice from pineapple.
Set pineapple aside.
Heat pineapple juice and water to make 1 cup, then dissolve jello with this mixture.
Set in refrigerator to thicken, but not set.
Add orange juice concentrate; stir well.
Add drained crushed pineapple, the chopped apple and chopped dates.
You may add 1 cup chopped nuts; they are optional.
Chill in refrigerator until firm.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: no bake chocolate pie
directions: *Keep clear cover to invert and cover pie!

title: honolulu chicken
directions: Mix all ingredients except chicken together.
Simmer over medium heat for 5 minutes.
Cool.
Pour over chicken and marinate 1 to 2 hours.
Grill approximately 10 minutes.
Top with pineapple slices and serve with rice.

title: salisbury steak
directions: Mix meat, crumbs, 1/4 cup dry soup mix, milk and the eggs. Shape into patties and brown in shortening.
Put rest of soup mix and flour with the water in skillet.
Stir in mushrooms.

title: fresh apple bread
directions: Cream sugar and shortening, adding eggs and apple.
Mix in sifted dry ingredients to which pecans have been added.
Stir in buttermilk and vanilla.
Pour into greased loaf pan.
Sprinkle top with a mixture of sugar.
Bake 1 hour in preheated 350° oven. Yields 1 loaf.

title: banana punch
directions: Combine sugar and water in saucepan.
Boil over low heat for 3 minutes, stirring frequently.
Let stand until cool.
Combine with orange juice, lemon juice, mashed bananas and pineapple juice in 1 gallon jar.
Freeze.
Remove from freezer 2 hours before serving. Pour into punch bowl.
Add ginger ale just before serving.
Yield: 40 servings.

title: poppy seed chicken
directions: Combine chicken, soups and sour cream.
Mix butter into cracker crumbs and sprinkle over chicken mixture.
Sprinkle poppy seed over crackers.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes until bubbly.

title: susie's grape blueberry salad
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients and let congeal.
Mix next 3 ingredients together and place on top of salad; sprinkle nuts on top.

title: summer squash soup
directions: Saute scallions (chopped) in butter until they are golden. Add squash; cut into pieces.
Add chicken stock and cook the mixture for about 15 minutes or until squash is tender.
Put the soup through a sieve or puree in a food processor.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Add nutmeg and heavy cream.
Serve hot or cold garnished with parsley.
Serves 6.

title: easy chicken quesadillas(4 to 6 servings)
directions: Saute chicken with butter and chili powder until heated through and brown. Coat a large nonstick skillet with nonstick cooking spray. Heat to medium heat.
Place 1 tortilla in skillet. Spread 3/4 cup chicken mix over half of tortilla.
Add enough cheese and onion to cover chicken. Fold over and cook 1 minute until brown. Turn and cook other side.
Repeat to prepare remaining quesadillas. Cut into wedges. Serve with sour cream and guacamole.

title: hot fudge sundae cake
directions: Crush the Oreo cookies with fork.
Mix with 1/2 cup melted butter.
Press in a 9 x 13-inch pan (Tupperware). Freeze until firm.
Let ice cream soften.
Spread over cookie mixture and freeze until firm.
Mix 1 stick of butter, Eagle Brand milk and chocolate syrup. Boil for 5 minutes.
Let cool.
Pour over mixture and freeze until hard.
Spread Cool Whip over mixture. Sprinkle with nuts and freeze.
Let thaw about 10 minutes before serving, but is just as good frozen.

title: enchiladas
directions: Brown meat, salt, pepper, chili powder and onions.
Pour off liquid.
Spoon into flour tortillas and roll up.
Layer in large pan side by side.
Pour large can of chili over top of enchiladas. Bake 15 minutes at 350°.
Take out and cover with cheese.
Return to oven and bake until cheese melts.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream the cheese and butter together until soft.
Gradually add sugar and beat until batter is no longer grainy.
Add eggs, one at a time, and continue to beat until very light, about 10 to 15 minutes.
Fold in flour and then the flavorings.
Put into a greased and floured tube pan.
Place in cold oven and cook at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
Cool before removing from the pan, about 10 to 15 minutes.

title: sombrero dip
directions: Cook ground meat and 1/4 cup chopped onion over medium heat until brown.
Add catsup, chili powder and salt.
When mixture is heated through, reduce heat to low.
Garnish top in thirds with grated cheese, sliced olives and 1/4 cup chopped onion.
Serve hot with corn chips.
Makes 1 1/2 cups.

title: creamy tacos
directions: Brown meat and add chili mix and all other ingredients.
Serve over chips.

title: bay crab cakes
directions: Saute
onion
and
green pepper in butter until tender. Remove from
heat;
stir in crab meat and next 9 ingredients. Mix well and shape into 8 patties.
Coat with additional bread crumbs. Pour
oil
to
depth
of 1/4-inch into heavy skillet. Fry
cakes in	hot
oil
4 to 5 minutes on each side. Yields 8 cakes.

title: cheesy mexican corn bread
directions: Preheat oven to 375 degrees.
Grease and flour a 9 X 13 inch pan.
In a medium bowl, mix cornmeal, eggs, buttermilk, jalapenos, salt, corn and oil; blend together well.
Pour half the batter into pan.
Sprinkle with cheese; add remaining batter.
Bake 45 minutes.
Cool 5 minutes before cutting and serving.

title: betzy's delicious dessert
directions: Mix and put in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cool and chill.

title: fruit squares
directions: Cream margarine and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add, eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add vanilla. Sift flour and baking powder together.
Add gradually to creamed mixture.
Pour into a greased and floured cookie sheet.
Spread dough; with back of teaspoon, mark off 30 to 40 depressions. Spoon 1 teaspoon of cherry pie filling in each depression.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Mix all other ingredients.
Add yeast; mix well.
Cover and chill.
Roll and cut like biscuits; let rise.
Bake at 400° until done.

title: dad's chili
directions: In large pan, brown ground chuck adding onion mid-way through. Drain when meat is thoroughly cooked.
Add chili beans, pork and beans, tomatoes, sugar and tomato paste.
Add amount of chili powder to own taste.
Set on low heat; stir occasionally.
Allow to simmer for about 30 minutes.

title: favorite cookie(makes 3 dozen)
directions: Cream sugar and butter; beat in flour, vanilla and salt.
Then stir in pecans.
Drop by teaspoon onto ungreased baking sheet and make a thumbprint in each.

title: e-z peanut butter fudge
directions: Mix thoroughly; boil 3 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add 1 (6 1/2 ounce) jar marshmallow
cream
and 1 (12 ounce) jar peanut butter.
Mix well and pour at once into greased 8 1/2 x 13-inch pan.

title: slushy punch
directions: Stir together sugar and 2 3/4 cups water until sugar dissolves. In a blender container combine bananas, half of the pineapple juice, and the orange juice concentrate.
Cover; blend until smooth.
Add to the sugar mixture.
Stir in remaining pineapple juice and lemon juice.
Transfer to a 13x9x2 inch-baking pan. Freeze for several hours or until firm.
To serve, let mixture stand at room temperature for 20-30 minutes.
To form slush, scrape a large spoon across the frozen mixture.
Spoon into a punch bowl. Slowly pour the carbonated beverage down the side of the bowl. Stir gently to mix.
Makes 23 (about 4 ounce) servings.

title: chicken breasts in sour cream(serves 8)
directions: Arrange chicken in shallow baking dish so that they do not overlap.
Cover with fresh mushrooms.
Combine soup, sherry and sour cream in small bowl.
Stir well and pour over chicken and mushrooms.
Make sure completely covered.
Dust with paprika and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix all ingredients in bowl with electric mixer.
Grease and flour 4 (1 pound) coffee cans.
Pour mixture evenly in all 4 cans. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Allow to cool and remove from cans.

title: stuffed cabbage rolls
directions: Cook cabbage
leaves
in
salted water a few minutes to soften.
Drain.
Combine
tablespoons
soup
with remaining ingredients.
Divide
meat mixture into 8 balls.
Place 1 ball on each cabbage
leaf.
Fold
in sides of leaves.
Roll up and secure with toothpicks, if necessary.
Place rolls, seam down, in heavy skillet.
Pour remaining soup over rolls.
Cover and cook over low
heat for 40 minutes, spooning sauce over rolls occasionally.

title: oven fried potatoes
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch pan, arrange potatoes with seal side down. Mix remaining ingredients and brush over potatoes. Bake in preheated oven at 325° for 45 minutes or until golden brown and tender.

title: pasta salad
directions: Mix ingredients and let set overnight.
Right before serving, chop and add 2 cucumbers, 2 tomatoes and 1 small onion; toss and serve.

title: seven step squares
directions: Melt oleo in an 8 x 8 pan (or 7 x 9).
Add graham cracker crumbs to margarine; mix and pat down.
Spread on in layers the walnuts, butterscotch bits, chocolate bits and coconut.
Pour the sweetened condensed milk over the mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes (until slightly browned on top).
Keep chilled.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Cook sausage until done and add cream cheese. Layer the bottom of a 9 x 13 pan with 1 can of crescent rolls. Spread sausage mixture over rolls and sprinkle with shredded cheese. Then cover with the remaining can of crescent rolls. Bake at 350° until crescents are to desired brownness.

title: vegetable meat dinner
directions: Cook roast until over half tender in added juice.
Then in a 12 to 14-inch roasting pan, place roast juice and squares of meat cut from roast all about the pan's bottom.
Then place cabbage wedges, small potatoes, carrots and peas or beans and salt and pepper. Broil under tinfoil until done.
Then serve with bread.
Makes about 12 servings.
Cut down if smaller meal is desired.

title: million dollar salad
directions: Cream and blend together cream cheese and powdered sugar. Whip Dream Whip and add to the cream cheese mixture.
Add well drained pineapple, well drained oranges, halved grapes or cherries, marshmallows and nuts.
Mix well and put into flat pan or dish and chill.
Serves 15 to 20.

title: brown rice confetti salad
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in a saucepan. Cook according to package directions. Remove from heat and cool. Combine rice, squash strips and next 6 ingredients. Set aside.
Combine lemon juice and next 3 ingredients in a jar.
Cover tightly and shake vigorously.
Pour over rice mixture. Toss gently. Cover and chill 1 to 2 hours. Garnish, if desired.
Yields 6 cups.
Per 1 cup serving:
174 calories, 29% from fat.
Preparation time:
1 hour.

title: chocolate sheet cake
directions: Sift flour.
Measure and resift with sugar and salt.
Mix butter, water and cocoa in saucepan and bring to a boil.
Pour over flour and sugar.
Mix soda, buttermilk and eggs.
Add vanilla; beat well.
Batter will be thin.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Combine sugar and shortening, add eggs, water, and pumpkin. Sift dry ingredients and combine with first mixture.
Add nuts, raisins and dates.
Bake for 1 hour at 350° oven.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: barbecued shrimp
directions: Mix oil, lemon juice, salad dressing, salt, pepper and Worcestershire sauce.
Place shrimp in bowl and cover with marinade for 2 to 4 hours or overnight.
Put on skewers and charcoal grill 6 inches from coals.
Cook for 10 minutes, turning once and brushing with marinade.

title: killer brownies
directions: Mix dry ingredients until blended.
Add eggs (beaten), margarine and vanilla with a fork until moist.
Do not over mix. Sprinkle with Chocolate Chips.
Bake 25 min.
Do not over bake. Brownies will be very moist.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Mix in strawberries, pineapple and bananas; chill until set.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: egg salad party snack
directions: Stir all ingredients together.
Adjust seasoning.
Will make 1 1/2 cups of mix.
Serve on or with crackers.

title: veal cordon bleu
directions: Pound veal slices with a mallet until very thin (between 2 sheets of wax paper).
Place cheese on each of 6 slices of veal. Cover each with a slice of ham.
Top with remaining slices of veal.
Seal by pounding edges together.
Dredge the packets in flour.
Dip them in lightly beaten eggs.
Coat them with bread crumbs.
Saute packets in heated butter for 8 minutes, turning them once, until the meat is brown and cheese is melted.
Makes 6 servings.

title: seven-up cake
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Add oil and mix.
Add eggs one at a time, beating mixture after each addition.
Add 7-Up and mix well. Pour into three 8-inch cake pans which have been well-greased and floured.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes until cake tests done. Spread Seven-Up Cake Filling between each layer.

title: freezer peanut butter pie
directions: Spread half of the ice cream into crust.
Combine peanut butter and corn syrup.
Spread over ice cream.
Spread evenly with remaining ice cream.
Drizzle with chocolate sauce; top with nuts. Cover and freeze 3 or 4 hours.
Remove from freezer 15 minutes before serving.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.
Can be made weeks before serving.

title: red beans and rice salad
directions: In a large bowl, combine rice, red beans, tomato, green bell pepper, red onion and garlic; mix well.

title: margarita cocktails
directions: Combine all ingredients in blender.
Fill with ice to suit and blend well.
Dip the rim of glasses first in lemon juice, then in salt.
Fill glasses with cocktail and serve.

title: never-fail chocolate fudge
directions: Mix butter, cream and sugar in heavy saucepan.
Bring to a full rolling boil, stirring constantly.
Continue boiling over medium heat until 234°, or makes a soft ball when dropped in cold water. Remove from heat, stir in chocolate, marshmallows and nuts until well blended.
I stir while the pan is in cold water until it starts getting a little thick.
Then I take it out and drop by spoonfuls on waxed paper or foil.
This is usually ready to eat while still hot.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook the broccoli 5 minutes as directed on package.
Drain well.
Mix the soup, eggs, mayonnaise and cheese.
Fold into broccoli.
Put in greased casserole. Sprinkle with the crackers. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Ummm good!

title: canned okra
directions: Cook until the okra changes color.
Put in quart jars.
Cover the okra with all the ingredients.

title: broccoli soup
directions: Saute onions in margarine.
Add water and remaining ingredients.
After this has cooked and is good and hot, add roux to thicken.
If needed, thin with half and half as you use daily.

title: baked carrots
directions: Put partially cooked carrots in a casserole.
Add orange juice and honey.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: rotel cheese-sausage dip
directions: In skillet, scramble and cook sausage. Drain well. Mix sausage with cheese and Ro-Tel. Put in crock-pot on low heat until cheese is melted and dip is hot. The cheese will burn easily after it gets done.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix and chill for 6 hours.
Serve with carrots, celery, cauliflower, broccoli, cucumbers, cherry tomatoes, green peppers and zucchini.

title: mexican wedding cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar together.
Blend in vanilla, flour and nuts.
Chill and then shape into balls on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
When cold, sprinkle powdered sugar on them.

title: microwave swiss steak
directions: Power Level:
Medium (50%).
Cooking Time:
1 hour and 10 minutes to 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: macaroni and cheese casserole
directions: Cook macaroni until done.
Mix together all ingredients and macaroni.
Pour into casserole dish (small).
Cook 35 to 40 minutes in 350° oven.

title: new year's day bean soup
directions: Wash beans well and place in a large kettle.
Cover with water, add 2 tablespoons salt and soak overnight.
Drain well and add 2 quarts water and ham hocks.
Bring to a boil and simmer slowly 2 1/2 to 3 hours.
Then add remaining ingredients.
Simmer 1/2 hour longer.
Freezes well.

title: easy lemon refrigerator pie
directions: Mix together.
Put in a graham cracker pie crust.
Put Cool Whip for topping.

title: chocolate chip cookies(double batch)
directions: Melt butter.
Beat butter, sugar, brown sugar and vanilla in a large bowl.
Add eggs; beat well.
Add flour, soda and salt; mix well.
Add chocolate chips and nuts.
Bake at 375° for 9 minutes.

title: mandarin salad
directions: Cook almonds (low heat) with sugar, stirring constantly, until sugar melts and almonds are coated (use wooden spoon).
Cool on wax paper; pull apart.
Store at room temperature.
Place lettuce, romaine, celery and onions in plastic bag.
Pour dressing in bag. Add oranges.
Close tightly and shake until well coated.
Add almonds and shake.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Arrange chicken and vegetables in a baking dish.
Dissolve bouillon in hot water, and blend in soy sauce.
Pour over chicken and vegetables.
Let stand a few minutes before baking.
Bake for 30 minutes or until chicken is tender.

title: brunswick stew
directions: Blender chop green onion, corn and tomatoes.
Combine all ingredients and simmer 2 hours.
Stir to keep from sticking.

title: garlic-honey marinade
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Pour over boneless pork or chicken; refrigerate 8 hours before grilling.

title: homemade spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown and drain ground beef.
In a medium saucepan mix together all ingredients and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat. Simmer for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: salisbury steak
directions: Dip patties in crumbs.
Pour gravy over (mushroom soup and gravy mix).
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: poached pears in white wine
directions: Peel pears, core and cut into eighths.
Place in pan with wine, sugar and lemon strips.
Simmer all for 5 to 10 minutes until pears are tender but not really soft.

title: "catch that collierville zebra"
directions: Tip:
Better to use chocolate you buy at the crafts stores to make candy.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Combine all but strawberries.
Strawberries go in last.
Pour into 2 greased and floured pans.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: golden punch drink
directions: Mix all together and serve over ice.
Serves 30 large glasses.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together (do not drain corn).
Bake in 9 x 13-inch baking dish at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: onion dip
directions: Mix it up.
Could add a little horseradish if you want to make it zappy.
Makes 2 big dishes.

title: mock crab spread
directions: Mix all together.
Chill overnight.
Serve on pumpernickel bread slices or Ritz crackers.

title: watergate salad
directions: Combine dry pudding mix with other ingredients and mix well. Chill.

title: chile rellenos in a pan
directions: Mix everything together well. Grease a 9 x 13-inch Pyrex dish. Pour mixture into dish. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until set.

title: fannie mae fudge
directions: Melt margarine; add sugar and mix.
Add milk.
After it gets hot, add marshmallows.
Bring to a boil.
Take off heat.
Add chocolates and nuts.
Stir and pour into greased cookie sheet.

title: barbecued garlic shrimp(serve with crusty bread to soak up the marinade.)
directions: You will need bamboo skewers, soaked in water for 30 minutes.

title: sausage and egg bake
directions: Place bread cubes in 9 x 9-inch baking dish.
Add cooked sausage and half of cheese.
Mix eggs, milk and seasonings.
Pour over bread and meat.
Top with remaining cheese and sprinkle paprika on top.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 45 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: zucchini pate
directions: Put zucchini, vinegar, sugar and 1/2 teaspoon salt in bowl lined with a double thickness of cheesecloth.
Toss gently.
Cover and set aside for 1 hour.
After 1 hour, gather ends of cheesecloth and squeeze to drain as much as possible.

title: green jello salad
directions: Boil water and pour over jello.
Cool.
Add milk, pineapple, cottage cheese, salt and Miracle Whip.
Mix.
Pour into a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Refrigerate.
Cut into squares and serve as salad. Great for large gatherings.
Serves 14 to 16 people.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Slice beef thin and brown in butter. Reserve 1/3 cup beef stock. Stir in remaining stock, ketchup, garlic and salt into skillet with meat. Bring to a boil. Reduce heat. Cover skillet and simmer until beef is tender. Stir in mushrooms and onion. Simmer until onion is tender. Mix reserved beef stock and flour. Gradually add to skillet, stirring constantly. After mixture has thickened, stir in sour cream and heat through. Serve over egg noodles.

title: pea salad
directions: Add each ingredient in layers and cover with Ranch dressing and slice black olives on top.
This is better if chilled overnight.

title: poor man's stroganoff
directions: Melt butter; brown meat.
Drain off your grease.
Add onion, mushrooms and seasonings.
Set aside.
Cook your noodles, then reheat beef mixture.
Add sour cream.
Serve over noodles.

title: altar bread wafers
directions: Roll out and cut.
Bake at 375° for 5 to 7 minutes.

title: apple cake
directions: Combine apples and sugar in a bowl.
Set aside.
Combine dry ingredients and spices in a large bowl.
Make a well in center. Combine oil, vanilla and egg white; add to flour mixture.
Stir until moistened.
Stir in apple mixture.

title: jalapeno noodle salad
directions: Cook shells and drain.
Rinse in cold water.
Toss in rest of ingredients and stir well.
Chill, preferably for 5 days.
The longer it stays in the refrigerator, the better it gets!

title: clarissy's beef and macaroni
directions: Brown ground beef in onion powder.
Drain off excess liquid. Mix macaroni with ground beef.
Add another tablespoon of onion powder, pepper and salt to taste.
Add cheese cubes, margarine and cream.
Pour into glass baking dish.
Top with cracker crumbs. Bake about 30 minutes at 300°.

title: spanish meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients and shape into loaf.
Cover top of loaf with catsup and bake for 45 minutes to an hour at 350°. Wonderful!

title: anniversary cookies
directions: Melt margarine in saucepan.
Add sugar and stir.
Break egg yolks and add vanilla.
Mix well; set aside.
Add dry ingredients to margarine mixture.
Mix well.
Will be thick.
Add egg mixture. Beat all together.
Pour mixture into a 9 x 9-inch cake pan that has been lined with plastic wrap.
Spread and cover mix with wrap. Refrigerate until firm.
Slice thin and bake on an ungreased cookie tin for 10 minutes.
Remove immediately.
Store in tight fitting topped cookie jar.

title: french toast casserole
directions: Butter bottom and sides of a 9 x 13 x 2-inch baking dish.
Cut bread into 1-inch thick slices; place in a single layer in baking dish.
Beat eggs, milk, salt, sugar and vanilla together; pour over bread.
Use most of egg mixture, but not all.
Cover with foil; leave in refrigerator overnight (4 to 36 hours).
Before baking, place small slice of butter on each slice of bread; sprinkle cinnamon sugar over top.
Pour left over egg mixture around sides.
Bake at 350°, uncovered, for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: honey-oatmeal muffins
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Blend egg, milk, oil and honey. Stir into dry ingredients until moistened.
Add raisins.
Coat 12 muffin cups with cooking spray.
Fill with batter.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: buttermilk hot cakes
directions: Combine eggs, buttermilk and soda in bowl; mix well.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Add flour mixture and shortening to buttermilk mixture; mix well.
Drop by spoonfuls onto hot griddle. Brown on both sides.
Yields 20 servings.

title: zucchini relish
directions: Mix together zucchini, onions and peppers in large container. Sprinkle with 5 tablespoons salt.
Mix well and let stand overnight.
In morning, place mixture in colander and rinse with warm water; drain well.
Combine sugar, nutmeg, dry mustard, turmeric, celery seed, black pepper, cornstarch and cider vinegar in large pot.
Bring to a boil.
Add zucchini-onion-pepper mixture and cook slowly for 20 minutes.
Stir occasionally.
Place in clean, hot pint jars and seal with lids.
Relish may be processed in hot water bath for 10 minutes.
Yield:
6 to 7 pints.

title: baked spaghetti
directions: Cook spaghetti noodles, while browning ground beef with seasoning and tomato paste.
Drain.
Mix with spaghetti.
Layer with grated Cheddar cheese (ending with cheese on top). Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Microwave in ovensafe casserole dish covered with plastic wrap on Medium-low for 20 minutes.

title: risotto with seafood
directions: Saute onions in hot oil in heavy-bottomed pot large enough to hold all ingredients.
Meanwhile, drain liquid from oysters or clams and add the stock.
Heat mixture and keep warm.
When onions are soft, add wine and cook over high heat until liquid has evaporated.

Add rice and cook, stirring, until rice is coated. Add about a cup of simmering stock to the rice along with the thyme and saffron and cook over high heat, stirring often, until the liquid has been absorbed into the rice, stirring almost continuously.
You may not need all the liquid.
If using clams, and they are large, cut in half or smaller.
If scallops are large, cut in half.
If shrimp is uncooked, add along with the oysters, clams and scallops to risotto about three minutes before it is ready.
Add salt and pepper.
Stir and continue to cook.
If shrimp is cooked and large, cut in halves or thirds.
Add one minute before risotto is ready, just long enough to heat through. Yields 4 servings.

title: brownies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease a square pan, 8 x 8 x 2-inch.
Melt chocolate and Crisco together over low heat.
Beat in sugar and eggs.
Blend flour, baking powder and salt; stir into chocolate mixture.
Mix in nuts.
Spread in pan.
Bake for 30 to 35 minutes, until top has a dull crust.
A slight imprint will remain when touched lightly with finger.
Cool slightly.
Cut in 2-inch squares.
Makes 16 brownies.

title: pecan pound cake
directions: Cream together butter and milk; add eggs one at a time, adding milk after each egg.
Sift together flour and salt.
Add to creamed mixture.
Add 1/2 cup toasted pecans to mixture.
Pour into a greased 9-inch tube pan or loaf pan.
Sprinkle in the remaining pecans.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 25 minutes.
Check pan doneness after 1 1/4 hours.
Cool for 5 minutes on each.
Remove from pan and cool.

title: blender cheese cake
directions: Blend the first 6 ingredients for 5 minutes and then 2 minutes on puree.
Butter an 8 x 8-inch aluminum pan.
If fruit is to be added, drain and pour into pan.
Pour cheese mixture on top.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Sprinkle with cinnamon after baking.

title: yummy warm fruit salad
directions: Combine fruit in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle lightly with salt and brandy.
Dot with butter.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Served warm is best.

title: buttery onion pretzels
directions: In a skillet, melt margarine.
Stir in soup mix.
Heat and stir until well blended.
Add pretzels; toss to coat.
Spread pretzel mixture in a baking pan.
Bake at 250° for 1 1/2 hours, stirring every 15 minutes.
Cool.
Store in an airtight container. Yield: 6 cups.

title: cheese cake
directions: Beat cottage cheese in blender until smooth.
Beat first 5 ingredients together; add vanilla, flour, melted butter and cornstarch until blended
Stir in sour cream.

title: ranger joe cookies
directions: Mix in order given.
Roll into small balls and flatten with fork.
Bake on greased cookie sheets at 375° for 9 to 11 minutes.

title: never-fail pie crust
directions: Mix flour and salt.
Cut in Crisco until mixture is about the size of a pea.
Beat egg, vinegar and water.
Add to flour mixture.
Divide into 2 parts and roll on floured board.

title: party rolls from jean
directions: Mix yeast, sugar and water until dissolved.
Combine with remaining ingredients, except flour.
Gradually add flour.
Knead lightly.
Place in a covered bowl and let rise 2 hours.
Punch down and let rise again until double in size.
Roll out and cut to desired size.
Let rise in buttered pans 1/2 hour.
Bake at 375° for 10 or 15 minutes.
Yields approximately 50 party size rolls. Freezes well.

title: corn casserole
directions: Can be prepared ahead of time.

title: no-fat blackberry spread
directions: Combine all ingredients in a medium saucepan.
Boil 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat; stir 3 minutes. Immediately pour spread into freezer containers, leaving 1/2 inch headspace; cover at once with lids.
Cool to room temperature. Freeze.
Yield:
2 cups (18 calories and 0% fat per tablespoon).

title: curly noodle soup
directions: Pour chicken broth into a large saucepan.
Place on burner over high heat and cover.
When the broth boils, stir in the mini lasagna noodles.
Let the broth boil again.
Turn the burner to medium-low.
Cover the pan and cook 12 minutes or until the noodles are almost tender.
Stir in the chicken meat, stewed tomatoes and vegetables.
Turn the burner to medium-high.
Cover and cook about 5 minutes or until the soup boils again.
Turn off the burner.
Remove saucepan from heat and serve.
Yield:
4 servings (6 cups).

title: shrimp appetizer bread
directions: Cut bread in half lengthwise.
With fork, remove 1 inch-wide section of bread from center of each half, leaving a 1/2 inch shell.
In medium bowl, mix cream cheese, mayonnaise and lime juice until smooth.
Spread cut surfaces of bread with 1/3 cup cream cheese mixture; sprinkle parsley evenly on top.

title: orange blossoms
directions: Melt over hot water the chocolate morsels.
Stir in sugar, corn syrup and orange juice.
Mix well.
Combine crushed vanilla wafers and nuts.
Add chocolate mixture; stir thoroughly.
Form into 1-inch balls.
Drop into granulated sugar and roll until well coated.
Seal tightly in heavy-duty foil.
Let stand several days to ripen.
(These keep well and improve in flavor upon storing.) Yields 4 1/2 dozen.

title: easy stew
directions: Place meat and vegetables in crockpot. Mix rest of ingredients and pour over meat and vegetables. Cook on high for 4 hours.

title: salad divine
directions: Mix all ingredients (except jello).
Pour gelatin over other ingredients dry and mix real good.
Chill in refrigerator for 2 to 3 hours.

title: crispy baked fish
directions: Wash and dry fillets.
Cut into serving pieces.
Pour lemon juice into a shallow bowl.
Add fish and let stand in juice 10 or 15 minutes.
Drain fish.
Season with salt and pepper.
Dip in oil.
Roll in corn flake crumbs.
Arrange in one layer on a lightly oiled baking dish.
Bake at 475° for 10 minutes without turning.

title: hot turkey sandwiches
directions: Mix together.
Pour over turkey.
Cover.
Bake in 325° oven until done, about 3 to 3 1/2 hours, basting every 1/2 hour.
Take turkey out of gravy mixture, debone and put meat back in gravy. Heat and serve in buns.
(I half the recipe and use a turkey breast.)

title: divinity
directions: In a 2-quart saucepan, combine sugar, corn syrup, salt and water.
Cook to hard ball stage at 260°, stirring only until sugar dissolves.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Saute onion in oil until tender. Stir in chili powder. Cook 1 minute. Add tomato sauce, stewed tomatoes and 1/2 teaspoon salt. Cook over high heat until boiling. Reduce heat and simmer until sauce thickens slightly. In large bowl, mix chicken, green chilies, sour cream and salt. Place 1/2 cup chicken mixture along edge of tortilla and roll. Pour 1/2 tomato sauce into 9 x 13 dish. Sprinkle with cheeses. Place rolled enchilada seam side down. Pour remaining sauce on top. Sprinkle with cheese. Bake until bubbly.

title: summer salad
directions: Dissolve sugar in vinegar; heat if necessary.
Mix remaining ingredients in covered dish.
Pour solution of vinegar, sugar and oil over vegetables.
Store in refrigerator, preferably overnight. Serve cold.

title: pecan tassies
directions: Mix together package cream cheese and stick of butter.
Add 1 cup flour.
Mix.
Chill for one hour.
Form into 24 (1-inch) balls.
Press balls into bottom and sides of muffin pans.
Beat together 1 egg, brown sugar, butter, vanilla and salt.
Pour into muffin cups.
Top with pecans (whole or cut in pieces).

title: *baked chicken with sauce
directions: Combine melted butter and paprika and brush on both sides of each chicken half. Place in lightly greased baking pan.
Bake in preheated 375° oven for 1/2 hour or more or until chicken is brown on top. Do not turn.

title: biscuit pudding
directions: Break biscuits in pieces and soak in cream and water.
Add other ingredients.
Bake at 350° until set and thick.

title: sausage brunch
directions: Brown sausage, drain.
Add to remaining ingredients and mix. Pour mixture into a greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Let stand overnight in the refrigerator.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: banana pudding
directions: Melt butter, then add flour.
Stir in 1 cup of milk at a time.
Stir until it bubbles.
Add sugar, then stir well.
Remove from heat, then add vanilla.
Pour over vanilla wafers and bananas; chill.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients (except grated cheese).
Pour into 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle grated cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: ann landers' meat loaf
directions: Mix together thoroughly.
Put into loaf pan, top with 2 strips of bacon (optional).
Pour 1 (8 ounce) can tomato sauce over it and bake 1 hour at 350°.
Serves 6.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Cook carrots until almost done.
Mix vinegar, oil, sugar and soup together.
Add onion and bell pepper to carrots while the carrots are still warm.
Add vinegar mixture. Leave set for 3 or 4 hours before eating.
Can be eaten days later if kept in fridge.

title: tangy fruit salsa
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Cover and refrigerate about 1 hour. Makes 1 2/3 cups.
Great served with Ricotta Cream.

title: ginger chip cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add egg, molasses, flour, baking soda, cinnamon, ginger, cloves and salt.
Blend until smooth dough forms, using medium to low speed on mixer.
Stir in the semi-sweet chocolate pieces; shape into 1-inch balls.
Dip tops of balls in sugar.
Place dipped side up on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes, until browned and firm.
Makes 5 dozen cookies.

title: chicken souffle
directions: Place 2 slices of diced bread cubes in bottom of a casserole dish.
Mix together chicken, mayo, onion and pepper.
Spread over cubes.
Add remaining cubes.
Beat eggs and milk; pour over cubes. Cover and let stand overnight in refrigerator.
Spread soup and cheese over top.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream together butter, oil and sugar.
Add eggs one at a time. Mix well.
Add milk and vanilla.
Blend well.
Sift together flour, baking powder, salt and cocoa.
Add flour mixture to butter mixture slowly beating well between each addition.
In well-greased and floured Bundt cake pan, bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: hamburgers with a twist
directions: Saute onion until it is transparent.
Cook hamburg in skillet, separating well with a fork until it is well done and brown.
Add soup, ketchup and pepper and mix well and heat.
Slice French bread in half lengthwise.
Spread hamburg mixture over bottom half.
Replace the top and slice bread in triangles.
Serve with pickles and chips.

title: strawberry pizza
directions: Mix ingredients.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan or a 14-inch pizza pan.
Cook at 350° until lightly browned.
Let crust cool.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Cook and drain spaghetti; pour into large serving bowl.
Mix all other ingredients, stir and cover.
Let chill for at least 4 hours.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix ingredients until you have a good, thick consistency.
Drop by tablespoon into deep hot oil until golden brown.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Cook ground beef and onion until done; drain grease out. Divide chopped cabbage into 3 parts; put part as first layer in a 2 or 2 1/2-quart baking dish, then half meat, then 1/4 cup rice, then 1/3 cabbage, then half meat, then 1/4 cup rice, then last layer of cabbage.
Mix tomato soup with water and brown sugar; pour over the casserole.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Bake covered for 1 to 1 1/2 hours at 350° (until cabbage is done).

title: lasagna
directions: Brown ground beef, mixing with Ragu sauce.
Layer in pan: sauce, noodles, sauce, half cottage cheese, half Mozzarella and Parmesan to taste.
Then start with sauce again, more noodles, sauce, remaining cheese, the last of the sauce and then Parmesan. Cook at 350° for about 45 minutes.

title: nectarine-blackberry pie
directions: Rinse berries and drain dry on absorbent towels.
In a 1 1/2-quart pan, combine sugar and cornstarch.
Add 1 cup of the berries and the water.
Cook, stirring often, over medium-high heat until the mixture comes to a full boil, 5 to 7 minutes.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Drain Veg-All; place in casserole dish.
Mix soup, sour cream and
onions
and pour over Veg-All.
Melt margarine and add crackers
and
almonds; put on top.
Bake in oven at 350° for 20 minutes or until slightly brown.

title: lemon curd meringues
directions: Meringues can be made several days ahead and stored in airtight container in freezer.
Recipe makes 48 shells.

title: nan's gelatin salad
directions: Drain and measure the juice from the pineapple.
Add water if necessary to make 2 cups. Set aside. Dissolve the lemon and orange gelatin in the boiling water.
Add the vinegar, salt and reserved pineapple juice. Refrigerate for 30 minutes or until slightly thickened. Stir in the pineapple, carrots and walnuts.
Chill until set.
Serves 6.

title: football treats(serves 15 to 20)
directions: Grate cheese.
Combine with other ingredients in medium-size bowl.
Spread evenly on cocktail rye.
Place on cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: soft molasses cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs and molasses.
Dissolve soda in sour milk.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Add to creamed mixture with sour milk.
Roll out dough, cut out and sprinkle with sugar or roll in balls, flatten and sprinkle with sugar.
Bake at 350° for 8 minutes or until done.

title: easy good fudge
directions: In a
heavy saucepan mix and boil sugar and milk for three minutes. Add vanilla and boil three more minutes. Mix all ingredients together and pour in a large baking dish. Let cool and cut in pieces.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken.
Mix soup and milk; combine with diced chicken. Mix broth with stuffing mix and sprinkle over top of chicken.
Bake for 20 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: reuben sandwich
directions: Toast bread, butter lightly.
Arrange sliced corned beef on 4 slices of toast.
Divide sauerkraut among sandwiches.
Top with Thousand Island dressing.
Top each with a slice of Swiss cheese. Top with other slices of toast, buttered side down.
Place each sandwich on a paper plate.
Cook one at a time, for 1 1/2 to 2 minutes, or just until cheese melts.
Either use grill or microwave to cook.

title: mom's punch
directions: Mix together with tray of ice and add sherbet.
Serve.

title: 100 good cookies
