directions: Cream together the butter, oil and sugars.
Add eggs.
Add soda, salt, cream of tartar, vanilla and flour.
Stir in Rice Krispies, oatmeal, nuts and coconut with spoon.
Form into balls and flatten on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 13 to 14 minutes.

title: chicken meal - in- one
directions: In an ungreased 13 x 9 x2 inch baking dish, combine hash browns, beans, and carrots. Top with chicken. Combine remaining ingredients, pour over chicken and vegetables. Cover and bake at 375° for 50 minutes. Uncover, bake 25 to 30 minutes longer or until chicken is done.

title: lemon dessert
directions: Mix cracker crumbs and oleo.
Spread in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Beat egg whites, gradually adding sugar until stiff.
Spread over cracker crumb layer.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
Cool. Spread 1 can of lemon pudding on top of meringue.
Top with Cool Whip.
Cut into squares.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: crusty rye bread with orange honey sauce
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Lightly oil baking sheet.
In a small bowl, mix milk, vinegar, honey and molasses.
In a large bowl, combine rye flour, whole wheat flour, wheat germ, oats, caraway seed, baking powder and baking soda.
Add the milk mixture and combine well.
Knead dough on a lightly floured work surface until slightly sticky, 2 to 3 minutes (if the dough remains very sticky, knead in a little flour).
Shape dough into a round.
Place on the prepared baking sheet.
Bake until crusty and well browned, about 1 hour.
Serve warm with Orange Honey Sauce.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Stir in pineapple, cranberry sauce and wine.
Chill until mixture thickens slightly. Fold in nuts and turn into a 2-quart serving bowl or 9 x 12 x 2-inch dish.
Chill until firm.

title: pineapple salad
directions: Cook
flour,
pineapple
juice,
butter, eggs and sugar until slightly
thickened.
Let cool slightly.
Add pineapple and cheese.
I
use 1 1/2 quart Corning Ware bowl.
Refrigerate.
Will keep several days and is just as good then as when you first made it.

title: green beans - italian style
directions: Snap beans into 1-inch pieces and cook.
Heat oven to 350°. Toss beans with oil, vinegar, onion, salt, garlic and pepper. Stir together bread crumbs, Parmesan cheese and butter.
Mix into beans.
Pour into ungreased 1-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Beat oleo and sugar until fluffy.
Beat in egg and vanilla. Add combined flour, baking soda, salt and spices.
Mix well. Stir in oats and pecans.
Drop by tablespoonfuls on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 9 minutes for chewy, 10 to 11 minutes for crisp. Makes 4 1/2 dozen.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix all by hand and roll into small balls.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until done.

title: cantonese soft fried chow mein(kwangtung chow mein)
directions: The Chinese knew onions and many vegetables long before they reached the Occident.
The onion first reached the Greeks and Romans by way of Babylon and the Romans brought it to Germania in the first century A.D.
It took until the late Middle Ages, however, to be accepted widely since its strong smell was too pungent for the times.
And at court, eating onion was considered coarse and crude.
How different today after the Swabians and their Alsatian neighbors had invented a delectable recipe for onion pie, not unlike quiche.

title: toll house brownies *
directions: Sift flour.
Add butter to melted chocolate to blend.
Combine sugar and eggs.
Add flour, vanilla and chocolate morsels.
Bake in greased shallow pan in moderate oven (350°) for 30 to 35 minutes.
Cut in squares before cold.

title: strawberry or raspberry pie
directions: Mix.
Bake at 350° until light brown.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Whip cream cheese and butter together.
Add sugar and blend well.
Add eggs which have been beaten alternately with flour, beating well after each addition.
Add flavoring.
Pour batter into greased and floured Bundt pan or spray pan with plenty of Pam.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: bean and cheese dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together except cheese.
Place into baking dish, sprinkle shredded cheese on top.

title: chiles rellenos (egg) casserole
directions: Spread each
slice
of bread with butter.
Cut up in an 11 x 7
x
2-inch
baking
dish.
Top
with
Cheddar and Jack cheese. Sprinkle
with chilies.
Beat eggs until frothy.
Add remaining ingredients,
mixing
well.
Pour
egg mixture over casserole. Cover and chill overnight or for at least 4 hours. Uncover and bake at 325° for 50 to 55 minutes or until lightly browned.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.
Serves 6.

title: braunschweiger pate
directions: Mix braunschweiger, 1/3 package cream cheese (3 ounce) and Worcestershire sauce.
Refrigerate until chilled.
Shape as desired.
Frost with remaining cream cheese and mixed in dried onion soup.
Refrigerate until chilled and roll in chopped nuts.

title: three bean salad
directions: Prepare several days before serving.
Place the three kinds of beans in a bowl and then add the onion.
Mix oil, vinegar with sugar and salt.
Pour over the beans and toss well.
Refrigerate covered until serving time.

title: marshmallow creme
directions: Beat egg white until stiff.
Cook Karo to firm ball stage. Pour slowly over egg white.
Soak gelatin in water.
Add vanilla, salt and gelatin.
Beat until shiny and thick.
Makes 1 pint.

title: swiss cheese baked chicken
directions: Place chicken in greased baking dish, bone side down.
Do not season chicken.
Place slices of Swiss cheese to completely cover chicken.
Spread soup over cheese.
Sprinkle generously with crushed seasoned croutons.
Bake until fork-tender, about 1 hour, at 350°.
Serves 4.

title: layered salad
directions: Tear lettuce and place a layer in deep glass bowl.
Sprinkle on 1/2 of celery, green pepper, onion and peas.
Repeat layers. Add sugar to salad dressing and spread over top to seal edges. Sprinkle on cheese.
Cover with foil or plastic wrap and refrigerate for 12 hours.
Toss just before serving.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain well first 3 ingredients.
Mix the milk and lemon juice together.
Mix well with wire beater until foamy.
Fold in sour cream.
Add Cool Whip.
Mix well.
Add nuts and fruit; mix well. Chill and serve.

title: fried mush
directions: Heat broth.
Mix together cold
water
and cornmeal and salt. Add to hot broth and cook 1
hour.
Put
in Pyrex bread pan to cool and then refrigerate.
Slice 1/4-inch thick.
Roll in flour and fry in skillet.
Serve with apple butter, pancake syrup, etc.

title: baked artichoke dip
directions: Preheat oven to 400°. Mash artichoke hearts.
Add mayonnaise, cheese and Worcestershire sauce.
Top with sliced almonds.
Bake 20 minutes in ovenproof serving dish.

title: caramel dip
directions: Melt margarine in heavy pot.
Then add brown sugar and cook until this is bubbling on slow heat.
Take off heat and stir in sour cream and flavoring. Good on apples and pineapple.

title: southern fried squash
directions: Place flour in a plastic bag and add seasonings to taste. Heat oil in skillet.
Place squash in bag and shake until each pieces is coated with flour.
Place pieces individually into hot grease (should sizzle).
Cook until brown around edges.
Turn each piece over and cook until brown.
Drain on paper towels.

title: cornbread biscuits
directions: Mix together the first 5 ingredients.
Add the eggs, shortening and milk.
Bake at 350°.
Bake muffins for 15 minutes and bread for 30 minutes.

title: key lime pie
directions: Mix all in a 9-inch pie plate.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 375°.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: May substitute raisins for chips.
If so, add 1 teaspoon cinnamon and 1 teaspoon nutmeg.

title: elbow macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni according to package directions.
Drain and rinse with cold water.
Toss with remaining ingredients.
Garnish with radish roses.
Serve on lettuce.

title: mashed potato candy
directions: Mix mashed potatoes with sugar until firm and can easily be handled.
Roll out on flat wax paper 1/4-inch thick.
Spread on peanut butter.
Roll up into a long roll.
Refrigerate until well chilled.
Slice in bite size pieces.

title: ham and cheese ball
directions: Mix ingredients
together.
Shape into a ball.
Roll in 1/2 cup chopped nuts.

title: cranapple warmer hot punch
directions: Heat all ingredients just to a boil.
Serve.

title: sweet and sour meat balls
directions: In large saucepan, combine jelly, catsup and vinegar.
Bring to a boil, lower heat and simmer while you prepare meatballs.

title: diabetic peanut butter cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray cookie sheet lightly with Pam. Sift flour and baking powder.
Cream peanut butter, oil, water, sweetener and egg.
Mix dry ingredients and vanilla into mixture. Stir in peanut butter chips.
Drop by teaspoon onto cookie sheet. Bake about 10 minutes.
Makes 2 1/2 dozen cookies.

title: quick fruit dessert
directions: Toss the
fruits
together,
adding small amounts of the dry instant pudding
mix.
Be
sure to use a container that can be covered.
Refrigerate and chill.
May be eaten alone or with plain cake or cookies.

title: brown rice casserole
directions: Melt oleo and stir in remaining ingredients.
Place in a 2 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Cover and bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Microwave chicken, almost covered with water, 15 minutes on High. Cool for 5 minutes. Pull off bone and shred. Put broccoli in microwave. Combine broccoli, chicken, cheese, onion and mayonnaise. Put in oblong pan; salt and pepper to taste. Cover with stuffing mix and bake at 350° until it bubbles.

title: pineapple bran muffins
directions: Beat eggs and stir in sugar, buttermilk, bran and pineapple. Let mixture stand for 5 minutes.
Resift flour with soda, baking powder, and salt.
Stir dry ingredients into the bran mixture only until all the flour is moistened, adding cooled shortening as you stir.
Bake at 400 degrees for 25 minutes.

title: coconut pie
directions: Beat sugar, eggs and salt until mixture is lemon colored.
Add butter and flour; blend well and add milk.
Stir in 1 cup coconut and pour in unbaked pie shell.
Sprinkle 1/2 cup coconut on top and bake in slow oven for 1 hour.

title: unbaked peanut butter krispies cookies
directions: Mix sugar and syrup.
Bring to a boil.
Remove from burner. Add peanut butter; stir.
Add Rice Krispies.
Stir.
Drop by teaspoon onto waxed paper.

title: tater tot hot dish
directions: Put uncooked hamburger in bottom of pan.
Put Tater Tots over hamburger evenly.
Spread mushroom soup over Tots.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: raw tomato relish (mom's)("mom" is frances grimes, #276.)
directions: Chop and drain tomatoes.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix and bottle.
There is no cooking!

title: picnic cupcakes
directions: Melt chocolate and margarine.
Mix eggs, flour, sugar, vanilla, nuts and chocolate mixture.
Just stir; do not beat. Pour into cupcake tins.
Bake at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: homemade bagels
directions: Mix water and yeast in large bowl.
Stir in sugar, salt and 4 cups flour.
Turn onto board and knead for 10 minutes, adding flour as needed.
Place in greased bowl.
Cover; let rise 15 minutes. Punch dough down and roll into 1-inch thick ropes and fasten ends to form a circle.
Place on a greased cookie sheet and let rise 20 minutes.

title: cheddar olives
directions: Halve olives lengthwise.
Remove pimentos and chop fine. Blend cheese with pimentos.
Stuff olive halves with this mixture. Press halves together.
Cut bacon slices in half.
Wrap each olive in 1/2 slice bacon.
Secure with toothpick.
Broil 4 to 5 minutes on each side or until bacon is crisp.

title: nettie dokey's icebox cookies
directions: Cream first 3 ingredients well.
Add raisins and vanilla. Sift flour, baking soda and salt.
Make into rolls or pack in pan. Leave overnight in refrigerator.
Slice very thin and bake at 350° for 12 minutes.

title: chicken stir-fry
directions: Heat oil in skillet over high heat.
Cut chicken into strips. Add to skillet with garlic.
Stir-fry for 3 minutes.
Add vegetables.
Stir-fry another 3 minutes.
Reduce.

title: tammy's salad
directions: Cut all veggies into bowl.
Add salad dressing.
Refrigerate at least an hour.
You can add any veggies you want (squash, zucchini, etc.).

title: chili
directions: Mix all together.
Put food in crock-pot.
Cook on low for 10 to 12 hours, on high for 6 to 7 hours or on auto 6 to 8 hours.

title: 100 dozen sugar cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar until light, using medium speed. Add eggs and milk.
Add flour sifted with baking powder, salt and vanilla.
Keep mixture in refrigerator, rolling a small amount at a time.
Cut with a 2 1/2 inch cutter.
Sprinkle with sugar.
Bake on a greased baking sheet at 360° for 10 minutes.

title: strawberry nut bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour five 4 1/2 x 2 3/4 x 2 1/2-inch loaf pans.
Cream butter, sugar, vanilla and lemon extract until fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Sift together flour, salt, cream of tartar and soda.
Combine jam and sour cream.
Add jam mixture alternately with dry ingredients to creamed mixture, beating until well combined.
Stir in nuts.
Divide among 5 small loaf pans.
Bake 50 minutes or until done.

title: dallas dip
directions: Mix together first four ingredients.
Mix together last three ingredients and toss together.
Refrigerate in covered container until ready to serve.
Flavors blend very well if prepared a day or two ahead of serving.
Serve Doritos chips for dipping.
Makes approximately 2 1/2 cups of dip.

title: rice picnic salad
directions: Cook until rice is done and all liquid is absorbed.
Chill rice and add:

title: lima bean casserole
directions: Drain liquid from beans.
Save.
Mix beans with the grated onion, salt and pepper.
Melt butter.
Add crumbs and stir until butter is absorbed.
Blend the mushroom soup with the liquid from the beans.
Arrange alternate layers of beans, soup and buttered crumbs in greased, uncovered casserole.
Top with crumbs.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: sweet potato breakfast biscuits
directions: With pastry blender
cut
Crisco, sugar, cinnamon, salt and baking powder into peeled and mashed sweet potatoes.
Then work in 2 1/2 cups flour,
leaving
cup
flour to pat out biscuits. Bake in 425°
(preheated) oven for 25 minutes. (For variation add raisins and/or
coconut
to
dough.)
Brush tops with melted butter.

title: boo bites
directions: Melt butter and marshmallows.
Remove from heat and add remaining ingredients.
Stir cereal in last.
Shape into 1 1/2-inch balls.
Store in tight container.

title: quick sausage balls
directions: Mix all ingredients in bowl until blended.
Mixture will be thick and sticky.
Shape into small balls or drop by teaspoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes. Best when served warm.

title: cornbread dressing
directions: Saute onion and celery in
1/2 stick margarine.
Combine with next 3 ingredients and add seasonings.
Bake in baking dish for 20 to 30 minutes at 375°.

title: little pizzas
directions: Brown sausage, leaving grease in pan.
Add chopped up Velveeta, ketchup and Heinz 57. Mix well.
Add oregano.
Stir. Cook on low heat until cheese is melted.
Spread cheese and sausage mixture on party rye.
Bake at 375° for 5 minutes or longer, until cheese is bubbly on top.

title: old fashion pound cake
directions: Cream sugar and Crisco together.
Add eggs, salt and vanilla. Add flour, slowly mixing until creamy.
Beat an additional 5 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pina colada
directions: In a blender mix all the ingredients except the ice for 30 seconds.
Serve in a tall glass with ice.
Decorate with pineapple chunks and cherries and enjoy.

title: pasta primavera
directions: Prepare spaghetti according to package directions; drain.
In skillet over medium heat, in hot oil, cook vegetables with garlic until tender, about 10 minutes.
Stir in spaghetti sauce; heat through, stirring occasionally.
Spoon sauce over hot spaghetti. Makes 5 servings.

title: taco dip
directions: Spread cream cheese on bottom of serving tray.
Layer the taco sauce and sprinkle with the cheese.
Slice the top green of the onions over the cheese layer.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: german potato salad
directions: Peel and slice potatoes.
Grate butter and cheese.
Mix ingredients.
Marinate 1 day.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Stir once while baking.

title: chalupas - sort of
directions: Cook beans per package directions.
Cook meat and seasonings; when done, shred meat and mix well.

title: squash puppies
directions: Trim ends off squash.
Slice and cover with water; cook until tender.
Drain squash, mash and drain again.
Combine squash and remaining ingredients.
Drop mixture by scant tablespoon into hot oil, fry 5 minutes.
Drain and serve hot.

title: poor man's steak
directions: Mix together thoroughly and press into 1/2 to 3/4-inch thickness on tray or cookie sheet.
Chill overnight.
Cut in 4-inch squares.
Coat with flour; brown on both sides in a skillet.
Place in a baking dish.

title: homemade eagle brand milk
directions: In 2 cup glass measure, mix margarine and water.
Microwave 2 minutes on High.
Add rest of ingredients.
Stir.
Pour in blender and whirl until smooth.
Equals 1 can Eagle Brand milk.

title: ruby's punch
directions: Mix all ingredients except frozen pineapple juice.
Near serving time, take juice out of freezer and let set to thaw slightly. Add to rest of mixture. Should be slightly slushy. Makes 3 gallons punch.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients in mixer.
Chill.
Roll
ball in pecans or sprinkle with parsley.

title: cheddar biscuits(like those at red lobster)
directions: In a medium bowl, combine all ingredients. Stir until blended. Drop by spoonfuls on greased cookie sheets. Bake 15 to 20 minutes or until golden brown. Best if served hot.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Brown ground beef, onions, and pepper; drain. Mix soups together in a bowl. In casserole dish, layer ground beef mixture, then pour soups over that. Spread cheese, one layer over all. Put tater tots on top of that in single layer. Cook until tater tots are browned.

title: frankfurter pilaf
directions: Melt margarine in large heavy saucepan or Dutch oven; add onion and saute until golden.
Add rice and saute until translucent; add bouillon and frankfurters and bring to boil. Cover and simmer over very low heat 20 to 25 minutes, or until rice is tender and liquid is absorbed.
Season with salt and pepper to taste.

title: dinner rolls
directions: Cream sugar and Crisco and beat.
Add egg, yeast (dissolved in 1/2 cup warm water and the 1/2 teaspoon of sugar).
Add milk, then flour and salt.
Put in refrigerator.
Will keep one week.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix hash browns, onions (sauteed in 1 stick melted margarine), sour cream, cream of celery soup and Cheddar cheese together. Bake in a large baking dish.
Makes 2 (1 1/2-quart) dishes.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: sour cream muffins
directions: Melt butter and cool.
Mix with flour and sour cream.
Drop into ungreased muffin tins.
Bake in 325° oven for twenty minutes.

title: luscious layer cookie mix
directions: (Layer ingredients starting at bottom of jar and working to top.)

title: peanut butter delight
directions: In top of double boiler combine butter, peanut butter and peanut butter chips.
Place over boiling water.
Stir until melted. Fold in marshmallows.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cut into squares.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: Cook celery, onion and broccoli in a 2 1/2-quart saucepan. Blend cottage cheese in blender until smooth.
Slowly add milk and beat until smooth. Add chicken soup to milk mixture.
Add to vegetables and heat until hot.
Do not let boil.
Makes 6 servings.

title: fruited breakfast muffins
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients; stir in carrots and next 4 ingredients.
Add oil and remaining ingredients.
Place in baking cups.
Fill 2/3 full.
Bake in a 350° oven for 25 minutes or until golden brown.

title: chicken breasts colletta
directions: Separate chicken breast fillets if connected, cutting away membranes or fat.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Rinse mushrooms; drain and pat dry.
Season flour with salt and pepper and dredge chicken breasts in mixture.
Heat oil in a heavy skillet over medium-high heat and cook until nicely browned on one side (about 3 minutes).
Add garlic cloves.

title: beef-cheddar macaroni casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large skillet, brown beef; drain fat and set aside.
In same skillet, saute onion in margarine until translucent.
In large bowl, combine beef, onion, spaghetti sauce, macaroni, 1 cup of the cheese, mushrooms and seasonings.
Spoon into an 11 x 7 x 2-inch baking dish.
Bake, covered, for 20 minutes, or until bubbly.
Remove cover; evenly sprinkle with 1/2 cup cheese.
Bake 5 minutes longer, or until cheese melts.
Serves 6.

title: no-bake cookies
directions: Mix sugar, oleo, milk and peanut butter together in saucepan. Boil for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and add cocoa or Nestle Quik, vanilla and oats.
Mix well, then drop onto wax paper by rounded spoonfuls.
Let cool, then enjoy.

title: foil meal
directions: *Can be replaced with steak, fish, sausage, etc.

title: texas barbecue sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients in 1 quart saucepan.
Cover and simmer 5 minutes.	Makes 2 cups.

title: hamburger rolls
directions: Put all the ingredients, except flour, into a mixing bowl. Add 2 cups of flour and beat for 2 minutes with electric beater. Then gradually add balance of flour until the dough no longer sticks to side of the bowl.
Place dough on a lightly floured surface and knead 7 to 8 minutes.
Place in a greased bowl, turning once to grease top.
Cover and let rise in a warm place until double.
Punch down and remove from bowl.
Cut dough into 18 pieces.
Knead each piece into a ball and place on a greased cookie sheet about 3 inches apart.
Cover and let rise until double.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: company cauliflower
directions: Steam cauliflower for 10 minutes.
Steam broccoli for 5 minutes
and add to cauliflower.
Heat butter in frying pan and brown green pepper, celery and mushrooms until softened.
In a small bowl, mix milk and flour well.
Add to mixture in pan and stir until thick.
Remove from heat.
In 9 x 13-inch glass dish, add half of cauliflower/broccoli; pour half of mixture on top and cover with grated Cheddar cheese.
Repeat.
Bake at 350° for about 20 minutes.
Can be prepared 1 to 2 days ahead.

title: silky egg custard
directions: Cream margarine, sugar and salt.
Add eggs, one at a time, mixing after each one.
Add milk, vanilla and sweet milk.
Pour into pie shells.
Bake 20 minutes until edges are firm at 350°.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease and flour 10-inch tube pan or 12-cup Bundt pan.
Beat butter and cream cheese together in large bowl until well blended.
Add sugar and beat until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each egg. Blend in vanilla.
Sift flour and salt together and blend into creamed mixture.
Spoon batter into prepared pan.

title: fried pie crust
directions: Mix sugar, egg whites, shortening and salt together.
Add flour and buttermilk; mix well and knead until smooth.
Pinch off into balls and roll out into 6-inch squares.
Fill and fold into half moon.
Flute with fork and fry.

title: punch
directions: Mix. Makes 1 1/3 gallons.
Servings: 40, 4 ounces each.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Layer bread, meat and cheese in dish.
Sprinkle with onion salt.
Beat eggs and milk together and pour over bread.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Next morning, add a can of cream of mushroom soup (or other cream soup) by pouring over top.
Bake 1 hour at 350° uncovered.
Serves 8.

title: cream cheese frosting
directions: Cream cheese with wooden spoon.
Gradually blend in sugar. Stir in vanilla.
Spread on cake, etc.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In large mixer bowl, combine melted butter, sugar, brown sugar and vanilla.
Beat until creamy.
Beat in eggs.
Add flour, soda and salt.
Beat until smooth.
Add chocolate morsels.
Drop by spoonful onto cookie sheet sprayed with Pam.
Bake at 375° for 9 to 11 minutes.

title: chicken divan
directions: Arrange asparagus in a shallow baking dish.
Top with chicken and water chestnuts.
Mix soup and milk.
Pour over chicken. Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 450° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Drain the green beans.
Mix the beans, soup and water.
Mix well.
Put in casserole dish and sprinkle onion rings on top. Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Melt butter and mix with crumbs; pat half in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Reserve some crumbs for top.

title: lemon-apricot pound cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together, adding eggs one at a time.
Pour into greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Cool 5 minutes before turning out of pan.

title: pecan pie
directions: Cream the butter and sugar.
Add eggs one at a time.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Use unbaked pie shells.
Cook very slow (about 300°) until done.

title: pate chinois
directions: Brown onion and meat. Drain.
Boil and mash the potatoes (milk, butter and seasoning).
Place drained meat on bottom. Top with creamed corn.
Place mashed potatoes on top of corn and season to taste. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: sauerkraut 3-bean salad
directions: Dressing:
Heat sugar, oil and vinegar until sugar is dissolved.
Cool.

title: carrot bars
directions: Combine all ingredients until well blended.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: yum yum cookies
directions: Boil together the dates, raisins and water for 3 minutes.
Cool and drain, saving the liquid.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Cook onions, garlic and ground beef until meat is brown. Drain off fat.
Stir in salt, pepper and mushrooms. Cook 5 minutes.
Stir in soup; simmer 10 minutes.
Stir in sour cream; heat thoroughly.
Serve over cooked egg noodles.

title: por-do pie
directions: Melt margarine in a baking dish.
Place 6 hamburger bun halves brown side down in melted butter.
Beat well together eggs, milk, sugar, cornstarch and vanilla.
Pour over buns.
Let set until liquid soaks into buns.
Sprinkle with good amount of coconut. Bake at 350° until light brown, about 40 minutes.

title: mam-maw ruth's seven minute frosting
directions: Cook egg whites, sugar, water, and syrup in a double boiler. Beat with mixer until it stands in a peak, about 7 minutes.
Add vanilla flavoring.

title: marinated vidalias
directions: Slice onions and separate into rings.
Combine water, sugar and vinegar.
Stir until sugar dissolves.
Pour over onion rings, cover and chill at least 3 hours.
Drain.
Stir in mayonnaise and celery seed.
Serve on lettuce leaves.
Yield:
4 servings.

title: raisin bars
directions: Mix together sugar, eggs and oil.
Add remaining ingredients. Bake in 350° oven in two loaves for about 20 minutes or until light brown.
Cut into slices.
Place on side and sprinkle lightly with cinnamon and sugar.
Place in oven for about 5 minutes more.

title: potato casserole
directions: Defrost potatoes.
Put in bowl.
Add melted stick of butter, onion, soup, sour cream and cheese.
Mix and pour into greased casserole dish.
Top with cornflakes and melted butter.
Cook at 350° for 30 minutes, covered.

title: hamburger stroganoff
directions: Brown ground beef and chopped onion.
Mix together all ingredients.
Put in greased casserole and bake covered in preheated 325° oven for 1 hour.

title: cranberry congealed salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water and stir in sugar.
In blender or food processor, chop cranberries and orange (cut into sections) and grind up fine, including rind.
Add pineapple, well drained (add juice to Jell-O mixture).
Add celery and nuts.
Mix well and pour into your favorite mold or glass dish to congeal in refrigerator, or place into 24 foil liners in muffin pans for individual servings.

title: low calorie lemon pie
directions: Bring 2/3 cup water to boil.
Add jello; set aside.
In blender, put cream cheese and cottage cheese; whip until smooth. Blend in Cool Whip.
Add jello and 1 teaspoon lemon flavoring. Put in crust and chill at least 4 hours.

title: grandma's butter jam cookies
directions: Soften the margarine; cream in sugar, egg yolks and vanilla. Blend.
Add flour.
Roll into little balls, place on ungreased cookie sheet (1-inch apart).
Press down in center with thumb. Fill centers with raspberry, peach or apricot preserves.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: marion's spinach casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Thaw spinach. Make cream sauce. In a small saucepan over low heat, melt butter. Blend in flour, salt and cayenne. Cook and stir for 3 to 4 minutes. Stir milk in slowly. Raise heat to medium. Cook and stir the sauce constantly with a wire whisk until thickened and smooth. Drain thawed spinach well. In a buttered 2-quart casserole dish, layer 1/2 crumbs, 1/2 spinach, 1/2 chopped eggs, 1/2 cheese and 1/2 sauce. Layer alternately with remaining ingredients.
Cut bacon into small pieces and place on top. Bake in preheated oven 40 to 45 minutes.

title: arroz con pollo casserole
directions: Cook flour and garlic in oil over low heat, stirring constantly, until flour is browned.
Stir in chili powder. Gradually add milk, broth, picante sauce, cumin and oregano.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, 5 minutes.
Add Velveeta cheese; stir until melted.
Keep warm.

title: seafood crepes
directions: Saute shrimp and green onion in butter.
Add 1/4 cup dry vermouth and cook down for sauce; set aside.
Pour 1/4 cup dry vermouth in pan and boil down to 1 tablespoon.
Add 2 tablespoons of cream to cornstarch, whisking.
Add 2 cups of cream, minus 2 tablespoons to sauce.
Add 1/2 cup Swiss cheese to melt.
Add 1/3 cup of sauce to shrimp mix.

title: meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients except tomato sauce. Shape into loaf and put tomato sauce on top. Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: saucy pork chops
directions: Mix ketchup, mustard, chili powder, sugar and water together. Put chops in greased baking dish, in one layer.
Pour sauce over chops.
Arrange 1 slice of onion and lemon on top of each chop. Bake in the oven at 325°, covered, for 2 hours.
Remove cover and baste; continue baking, uncovered, for 1/2 hour more.

title: cream cheese ball
directions: Place cream cheese in medium bowl and mix until cream cheese is soft.
Mix in bell pepper, green onions, pineapple and seasoning salt.
Line another mixing bowl with plastic wrap.
Form the mixture into a ball and place it on the plastic wrap.
Cover the bowl and refrigerate until the ball has set, 2 hours or more. When ready to serve, roll the cheese ball in the nuts.
Makes 1 large ball.

title: pot roast
directions: Coat the roast with flour.
Brown roast on all sides in cooking oil.
Sprinkle lightly with garlic powder, salt and pepper.
Add onion and water.
Cover and roast for about 2 hours at 325° or simmer on low fire for about 2 hours.
Add vegetables and cook about an hour longer or until meat and vegetables are tender.

title: swedish apple pie
directions: Cut apples into pie plate.
Then sprinkle with cinnamon and 1 tablespoon sugar.
Mix butter, 1 cup flour, egg and salt until smooth.
Drop by spoonful over apples.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: brownies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
In large saucepan, melt cocoa and
shortening
over
low
heat.
Remove from heat.
Blend in sugar,
eggs and vanilla.
Mix in remaining ingredients.
Spread in
prepared pan.
Bake 30 minutes or until brownies pull away from
the
side
of
the pan.
Do not overbake. Cool slightly; cut into bars.
Makes 32.

title: quick yeast rolls
directions: Mix together dry ingredients.
Add milk and salad dressing. Bake in muffin tin at 350° until done, approximately 20 to 25 minutes.

title: *key lime pie
directions: This is an authentic Key Lime Pie with native Key limes.
Note the creamy yellow inside.
Key Lime Pie is world famous for a just right tart taste.

title: chicken-bow tie pasta medley
directions: Heat the olive oil.
Add minced garlic.
Cook strips of chicken.
Push it aside and add broccoli florets.
(If little pieces, you don't have to precook.)
Saute that together.
Then put in your sun-dried tomatoes, basil, red pepper flakes, salt and pepper, seasoning to taste.
Then add white wine to deglaze skillet and add chicken broth and butter.
Cover and let it simmer together five minutes.
Then toss chicken mixture and pasta together, and put a little grated Parmesan cheese on.
Serve immediately.

title: dairy free lasagna
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cook lasagna noodles as package directs. Do not overcook.
Drain noodles.

title: coffee squares
directions: Mix butter, sugar, egg and vanilla.
Add dry ingredients alternately with coffee.
Put in 7 x 11 inch pan.
Sprinkle butterscotch bits and nuts on top.
Bake at 350 degrees for 35 minutes.

title: red satin punch
directions: Refrigerate juices and 7-Up.
At serving time, pour juices in punch bowl; slowly pour 7-Up.
Add ice cubes.
Makes 35 punch cups.

title: poinsettia punch
directions: Pour diluted lemonade into bowl. Pour in ginger ale.
Add a tray of ice cubes.
Stir in sherbet until well blended.
Makes 20 punch cup servings.

title: velveeta tortilla dog
directions: Place Velveeta strips and wiener on tortilla.
Roll up; secure with toothpick.
Microwave on paper towel on High for 45 seconds or until cheese is melted and wiener is hot.
Serve with Pace picante sauce or salsa.
Makes 1 serving.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream shortening and sugar and add egg and bran.
Sift flour, baking powder, salt and soda together.
Mix nuts with flour and add bananas alternately to which the water has been added.
Stir in vanilla.
Pour into greased loaf pan.
Let stand 30 minutes and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool before cutting.

title: real swiss fondue
directions: Rub a heavy saucepan (preferably enameled) with a clove of garlic.
Grate the cheese into the saucepan.
Add the flour and wine, and a squeeze of lemon juice.
Bring to a boil quickly, while stirring.
When melted, season with kirsch if desired, and nutmeg and pepper to taste.
The alcohol in the wine will evaporate in the cooking process.

title: souper oven stew
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
In a 3-quart casserole, combine meat, potatoes, carrots, onion, salt, pepper and soup.
Add enough water to reserved bean liquid to equal 1 cup. Add to mixture.
Mix well. Bake, covered, at 325° for 3 to 3 1/2 hours or until meat is tender. Stir in beans during the last 30 minutes.

title: 7 can chicken dish
directions: Mix all ingredients, except cheese.
Bake until bubbly, 30 or 40 minutes at 350°.
The last 15 minutes, top with cheese.

title: nacho dip
directions: Cut up cream cheese and put in the bottom of greased 8 x 8-inch pan.
Put onion and chili peppers on top of cream cheese. Pour can of chili over onion and peppers.
Top with grated cheese. Bake 15 minutes at 450°.
Serve with nacho chips.

title: old fashion stack cake
directions: *Note:
If you want molasses, add 1 cup molasses and use 1 cup less brown sugar.

title: deviled crabs
directions: Mix together well.
Place in greased baking dish. Sprinkle with cracker crumbs and dot with butter.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: spaghetti with garlic and oil
directions: In a small saucepan or skillet, cook garlic in olive oil on low heat until soft.
Stir in parsley, salt and black pepper. Heat and stir for 3 minutes.
Toss garlic mixture with spaghetti and bacon until coated.
Serve immediately.
Serves 2 to 3.
Serve with salad and bread.
Top with Parmesan cheese.

title: lentil soup
directions: Rinse lentils, drain and place in a pot.
Add 8 cups water and all ingredients.
Cover and simmer 1 1/2 hours.

title: peanut butter chocolate fudge
directions: In large saucepan, melt peanut butter chips, 1 cup condensed milk and 2 tablespoons butter.
Stir occasionally.
Remove from heat and spread mixture into wax paper lined 8-inch square pan. In small saucepan, melt chocolate morsels, remaining milk and butter.
Spread chocolate mixture on top of peanut butter mixture. Chill 2 hours or until firm.
Turn fudge onto cutting board. Pull off paper and cut into squares.
Store in tightly covered container.

title: easy pineapple jam
directions: Combine ingredients in a saucepan.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Pour into jars.
Cover and chill several hours or until set.
Keep stored in refrigerator.
Makes approximately 3 cups.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream butter, brown sugar, sugar, eggs and vanilla until light and fluffy.
Add flour to creamed mixture; stir in chocolate chips.

title: curried cabbage
directions: Cook cabbage in 1/2-inch of water for about 5 minutes or until tender-crisp.
Drain.
Melt margarine.
Add flour, curry and pepper; stir.
Add milk; continue to stir until smooth.
Pour sauce over cabbage and serve.

title: peach pie
directions: Mix flour and sugar well.
Add half & half milk.
Stir till mixed well.
Add peaches.
Pour into an unbaked 9-inch deep dish pie shell.
Use a regular 9-inch pie shell for top crust.
Bake 45 minutes at 375 degrees.

title: leftover turkey casserole
directions: Mix turkey, soups, pepper, sherry and water together in a large mixing bowl.
Pour into a large baking dish.
Bake for one hour at 375°.
Remove casserole from the oven; stir.
Top with onion rings and bake 10 more minutes.
This is good served over mashed potatoes.

title: championship bean dip
directions: Combine and place in slow cooker.
Cook on high for 2 hours, stirring occasionally.
Serve with chips and salsa.

title: green bean bake
directions: Brown bacon and onions (drain off most of grease).
Add brown sugar, catsup and Worcestershire.
Simmer 2 minutes.
Put green beans in casserole and spread mix over the top.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: chili cheese dip
directions: Brown hamburger; drain.
Melt cheese in a large pot over slow heat.
Add Ro-Tel tomatoes, hamburger, Worcestershire sauce and chili powder; stir.
Serve warm with tortilla chips.

title: sweet potatoes with brown sugar and apricot sauce
directions: In medium saucepan, bring sugar, nectar, margarine, cinnamon and nutmeg to a boil.
Boil gently 2 minutes.
Arrange potatoes in a baking dish (12 x 8 x 2-inch or larger if doubling recipe). Pour sauce over potatoes; sprinkle with nuts.
Cook in 350° oven (turning or basting potatoes several times) for 30 minutes or until potatoes are heated through and sauce is bubbly.
Sauce will thicken as it sets after baking.
This recipe is easy and great! I double this for a large crowd.

title: pizza macaroni
directions: Cook macaroni.
Mix with tomatoes, cubed Cheddar cheese and onion.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese and croutons over top.

title: yam crunch
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Then put into greased casserole dish.

title: garden macaroni salad with dill dressing
directions: Combine macaroni, carrots, tomato, celery, bell peppers, onions
and
dressing
in
a
large bowl; stir well.
Cover and chill.
Serve
on
a lettuce lined platter, if desired.
Yield: 12 servings (about 62 calories per 1/2 cup serving).

title: jalapeno corn
directions: Mix corn, chillies and cheese.
Pour into casserole dish.
Mix bread crumbs with melted margarine and sprinkle on corn mix.
Bake in 400° oven for approximately 15 minutes or until heated and bread crumbs are toasty.
To brown crumbs, place under broiler until brown.

title: squash delight
directions: *Can use spaghetti squash or any variety of pumpkin squash.

title: ham rolls
directions: Combine onion, radishes and cream cheese.
Spread on the ham slices and roll up.
Cut to wanted size.

title: chicken cacciatore with rigatoni
directions: Brown chicken and chopped onion in olive oil.
When well browned, add salt, pepper and bay leaves.
Cook for a few minutes, turning pieces occasionally.
Add wine; cook until wine is almost evaporated.
Add your sauce.
Season with salt and pepper (onion and garlic if desired) to taste.
Simmer 1/2 hour or until tender. (I like to add a can or frozen package of peas for the last 10 minutes or so.)
Meanwhile, cook macaroni; pour on platter and cover with chicken and sauce.
Top with grated cheese, if desired.

title: bread pudding
directions: Soak bread crumbs in milk for 1/2 hour.
Cream shortening with brown sugar and 3 beaten egg yolks.
Combine with bread crumb mixture.
Fold in egg whites beaten with sugar and vanilla.
Turn into an ungreased 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Place in shallow pan.
Add 1/2 inch of water to pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: dump cake
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch pan, put pineapple into the bottom and spread it out.
Pour and spread cherry pie filling over pineapple. Sprinkle cake mix over cherry filling.
Melt butter and pour over cake mix as evenly as you can.
Sprinkle one cup of coconut and chopped pecans.
Bake 1 hour at 325°.

title: kentucky ham biscuits
directions: About 35 minutes before serving, preheat oven to 450°.

In a large bowl with fork, mix flour, sugar, baking powder and salt. With pastry blender or two knives, used scissor fashion, cut in shortening until mixture resembles coarse crumbs. Add milk, parsley and ham.
With fork, stir dough until just mixed.
Onto ungreased cookie sheet, drop dough by 1/4 cupfuls, 1-inch apart, to make 12 biscuits. Bake 15 minutes or until golden brown.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Cook carrots in salt water until tender and drain.
Layer carrots, peppers and onion in bowl.
Mix oil and soup together and pour over them.
Mix sugar, vinegar, salt, pepper and Worcestershire sauce together.
Heat, not quite to boiling, and pour over all.
Keep refrigerated.
The longer it stands, the better it gets.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Brown ground chuck; add onion and slowly cook until onion is tender.
Add soups and enchilada sauce.
Mix well and set aside. In greased 9 x 13-inch pan, tear and line bottom with tortillas. Cover with meat mixture, then a layer of grated cheese.
Repeat with another layer of tortillas and soup mixture.
Bake in a 350° oven until bubbly and slightly brown.
Remove from oven and cover, while hot, with grated cheese.

title: corn casserole
directions: Saute onion and pepper in margarine.
Mix in a large bowl the eggs, creamed corn, whole corn with juice, corn bread mix, sauteed vegetables and salt.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch creased casserole. Spoon sour cream on top in small dollops.
Just before baking, cover with cheese.
Bake 30 minutes at 400°.

title: pea salad
directions: Open can of peas, drain.
Put in bowl.
Dice cheese in with peas.
Dice onion and add to bowl of peas.
Add salt, sugar and mayonnaise to taste.
Best when served cold.

title: crispy chocolate snacks
directions: Heat shortening and chocolate chips in a 3-quart saucepan over low heat, stirring constantly, until melted and smooth.
Remove from heat.
Stir in cereal and nuts until well coated.
Firmly press in ungreased square pan, 9 x 9 x 2-inch.
Refrigerate about 30 minutes or until firm.
Cut into about 1 1/2-inch squares. Store in refrigerator.
Makes 3 dozen snacks.

title: stuffed peaches
directions: Fold banana slices into cottage cheese.
Fill peach halves or if would prefer, use pear halves or cantaloupe or fill crepes. Chill and serve.

title: nanny's tomato sauce
directions: Plunge tomatoes in boiling water to loosen skins, approximately 2 minutes.
Peel tomatoes and chop.
Heat oil in iron skillet; add tomatoes.
Add sugar and vinegar to taste.
Cook down to thick paste.
Should have a sweet/sour taste.
Add more sugar and/or vinegar to taste.
Serve on top of black-eyed, purple hull or crowder peas.
Good with boiled okra.

title: cheesy mashed potato casserole
directions: Cook potatoes until done; mash.
Add remaining ingredients, except Cheddar cheese; mix well.
Pour into buttered casserole dish.
Top with Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 8.

title: hot cranberry cheer
directions: Put juices, sugar and salt in a large pot or coffee pot.
Put cinnamon sticks and cloves in top of coffee maker.
If using a large pot, you can tie the spices in a cloth.
Heat all ingredients slowly; can be simmered for 2 hours.
Great for Christmas.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together; mix thoroughly.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Drain first 3 vegetables.
Mix sugar, vinegar, oil, salt and pepper.
Bring to a boil.
Let cool and pour over vegetables.
Mix well.
Refrigerate.

title: lentil salad
directions: Cook lentils according to package directions.
Drain.
While lentils are still warm, add vinegar, oil and lemon juice.
Mix well.
Chill for 1/2 hour to 45 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients and chill for at least 1 hour.
Mix occasionally while it is chilling.

title: pecan oven fried chicken
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients; stir well.
Dip chicken in milk and dredge in mixture.
Place chicken in 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Pour butter over top.
Bake for 1 hour.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and mix onion until tender; add salt.
Drain squash.
Melt butter.
Add stuffing mix.
Stir in sour cream and soup.
Combine all ingredients.
Place in baking dish.
Top with cheese.
Bake 30 minutes at 375°.

title: crab marguerite(by pat waltjen)
directions: Layer 1/2 crab, 1/2 bread (broken into small pieces) and 1/3 grated cheese in a greased 9 x 13 x 2-inch casserole.
Saute mushrooms, onions, green pepper and celery in butter.
Remove from heat and add mayonnaise, salt, pepper and dry mustard.
Spread evenly over crab, bread and cheese.
Beat eggs; add milk and mix well.
Layer rest of crab, bread and 1/3 cheese; over all of this pour milk and egg mixture.
Refrigerate for at least 3 hours, preferably overnight.

title: taffy apple salad
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients in bowl.
Add pineapple, Cool Whip, apples and peanuts.
Cut apples in pineapple juice to prevent them from turning brown.

title: spiced cranberry tea
directions: Walk with God and He will bless you.
Go back to where you first lost sight of God and there you will see the reason why and you will find Him.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix the pudding with the milk.
Stir in the Eagle Brand milk and the Cool Whip.
Layer alternately with vanilla wafers, sliced bananas and pudding.
Chill.

title: oven rice casserole
directions: Add all ingredients together.
Bake in a covered casserole dish for approximately 35 minutes or until all the liquid is absorbed.
This serves 3; double ingredients if desired.

title: apricot balls
directions: Grind apricots, add coconut and milk.
Chill overnight.
Roll into balls.
Roll balls in confectioners sugar.
Store in covered container.

title: fruit salad pie
directions: Combine cherries, pineapple, sugar, cornstarch and coloring. Cook until thickened.
Remove from heat and cool.
Add bananas and nuts.
Make filling the day before and refrigerate overnight.

title: perfection salad
directions: Soften gelatin in 1/4 cup water.
Dissolve in 1 1/4 cups boiling water.
Add salt, sugar, lemon juice and vinegar.
Stir to dissolve sugar.
Let cool.
Add remaining ingredients.
Chill in oiled molds or shallow pan.
I use both red and green cabbages. Also use mayonnaise, sour cream and a little chili sauce mixed well.

title: squash relish
directions: The vegetables can be put in food processor.
Put the spices in cheesecloth or bag.
Cook all ingredients for 20 minutes.
Put in jars and seal.

title: camper's breakfast
directions: Brown sausage in heavy skillet; drain.
Beat eggs.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Scramble eggs in heavy skillet over medium heat; stir in crumbled sausage.

title: pasta with fresh asparagus and scallops
directions: Slice the asparagus into 1/8-inch slices.
Cut on a 45° angle. Set aside.
Heat a large kettle of water and put the pasta on to cook until just al dente.
Heat a large frying pan or wok and add the olive oil and garlic.
Toss for a moment and add the asparagus. Cook over high heat, stirring all the time, just until the asparagus is the least bit tender, about 2 minutes.
Add the green onions and toss.
Add the cream and bring to a quick simmer.
Add the scallops and turn off the heat.

title: dip
directions: Brown the hamburger meat.
Add soup, green chilies, chili powder and sauces.
Add cheese last and let melt.

title: upside-down pizza
directions: Mix Mozzarella cheese and sour cream together.
Brown hamburger and add sauce and mix.
Simmer slow 10 to 15 minutes.
Pour into a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Top with cheese spread.
Top with canned biscuits laid out flat until top is completely covered.
Bake at 450° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: nacho dip
directions: Soften cream cheese and spread on the bottom of 8-inch pan. Pour chili and spread over cream cheese.
Spread shredded cheese over chili.
Bake 30 minutes at 350° or microwave 7 to 8 minutes or until cheese has melted.
Serve with nacho chips.

title: new england squash pie
directions: Mix sugar, salt and spices.
Blend well into squash filling. Beat the eggs separately.
Add milk to eggs and stir well.
Blend into squash mixture.
Pour into 9-inch pie plate lined with crust. Preheat oven to 425°.
Bake 20 minutes at 425° and then 45 minutes at 375°.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Melt coating over low heat.
Stir in 1 or 2 cups of toasted pecans.
Drop on waxed paper to cool.

title: macaroni casserole
directions: Cook macaroni and drain.
Add other ingredients to macaroni while hot.
Pour into baking dish.
Sprinkle cheese cracker crumbs over top.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: cheese bread
directions: Cut bread in half lengthwise.
Mix all other ingredients together and spread onto each half of bread.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Slice and serve.

title: date loaf
directions: Cook sugar and milk as for fudge.
Just before soft boil, add dates.
Bring back to boil for 1 minute.
Remove from heat; add vanilla and nuts.
Beat until stiff.
Pour into long row on damp cloth; roll up until cold (can put into refrigerator).
Remove from cloth and slice in 1/4-inch slices.
Will keep well in cookie tin or wrapped in foil.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Brown onion in butter.
Combine remaining ingredients in large mixing bowl.
Salt to taste.
Add onion and mix thoroughly.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Spread cornflakes evenly over potato mixture.
Bake 45 minutes in 350° oven.
Serves 12.

title: ice-cream sandwiches
directions: Bake Peanut Butter Cookies; cool.

title: cornbread
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Blend in eggs.
Stir in chilies, corn and cheese.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Add to corn mixture, mixing until well blended.
Pour into greased and floured 8 x 12-inch baking dish. Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Slice and boil cabbage. Drain well. Melt butter and Velveeta; cook onion with this while melting. (Can do this in microwave.) Add soup (it blends better if warm when adding). Place cabbage in large casserole dish. Top with cheese mixture, then crumbled bread (or stuffing mix) on top. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: hot crabmeat canapes(makes 24 hors d'oeuvres)
directions: In a large mixing bowl, combine the crabmeat, sherry, salt, pepper and dill and set aside.
Melt the tablespoon of butter without browning it in a small heavy saucepan.
Remove from the heat and stir in the flour.
In a small bowl, beat the egg yolk with the cream and briskly stir this mixture into the butter-flour roux with a wire whisk.
Return the pan to the heat and cook slowly, whisking constantly, for a minute or two until the mixture thickens; do not let it boil.
Pour the sauce over the crabmeat mixture in the bowl and stir together with a spoon until the ingredients are well combined.
Taste for seasoning.

title: jello popcorn balls
directions: Melt together butter and marshmallows, then add jello.
Mix with popped corn and shape into balls.
Yield:

title: angel flake biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in water; set aside.
Combine flour, baking powder, baking soda, sugar and salt.
Cut in shortening to flour mixture.
Combine yeast mixture, butter and buttermilk.
Mix in flour mixture.
Knead lightly on floured board and cut.
Place in buttered baking dish and brush with butter.
Let rise 30 minutes. Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: santa's punch
directions: Fill 2 ice cube trays with lemon-lime beverage, reserving rest of lemon-lime beverage.
Place a cherry in each ice cube section. Freeze.

title: chicken-n-rice
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients.
Pour into a large baking dish. Arrange chicken on top of this. Dot with butter. Bake in a 325° oven for 2 hours, uncovered, or until tender. Add more water if needed.
Do not salt as onion mix has plenty.

title: hot curried fruit
directions: Mix the fruit together and place in casserole.
Mix softened butter with brown sugar and curry.
Spread over fruits.
Bake 1 hour at 325°.
Cool in refrigerator overnight or all day.

title: heavenly hash candy
directions: Put chocolate chips, oleo and marshmallows in container and set aside.
Mix evaporated milk and sugar in a heavy saucepan; bring to a boil and boil for 5 minutes on high, stirring often. Turn down to medium and cook for about 2 more minutes.
Mixture will get slightly darker.
Take off heat; add chips, oleo and marshmallows.
Stir until melted.
Add nuts and stir in.
Drop by spoonful on waxed paper.

title: mama's 1-2-3-4 cake
directions: Mix well all ingredients.
Bake at 325° for 25 minutes or until done.
Wonderful sheet cake.

title: swedish nuts
directions: Melt margarine in large cookie pan.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Gradually add sugar.
Put nuts into meringue and coat well.
Spoon nuts in buttered pan and turn to coat well.
Bake in 325° preheated oven for 10 minutes.
Take out and stir well.
Bake 10 minutes more and stir.

title: beef enchiladas
directions: Set aside 1/4 cup enchilada sauce.
Brown ground beef in large, deep skillet.
Boil 2 eggs.
Slice into pieces black olives and eggs.
Mix tomato sauce and remaining enchilada sauce with ground beef.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Also add onion at this time. Add black olives and eggs.
Stir and simmer 10 more minutes. In large skillet, add 1 tablespoon oil and 1 tablespoon enchilada sauce.
Turn on simmer and place tortilla in skillet until well coated.

title: quick fruit salad
directions: Combine all ingredients in a bowl.
Refrigerate until serving.

title: ground beef stroganoff
directions: Saute onion and garlic in the oleo.
Stir in ground beef. Cook until meat changes color.
Stir in 2 tablespoons flour, salt and pepper.
Cook this on low for about 20 minutes.
Add mushrooms (chopped) and soup; let simmer, stirring occasionally (do not let stick).
Just before serving, add sour cream; let come just to a boil.
Serve over egg noodles.
(I use the narrow noodles, cooked according to directions.)

title: salmon loaf with olive sauce
directions: Mix ingredients well; bake in bread pan at 325° for 35 minutes.

title: brownies
directions: Cream margarine, sugar and vanilla.
Beat in eggs.
Blend in cocoa.
Stir in flour and nuts; bake in 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan at 325° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: turkey meat loaf
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In a small bowl, stir chicken bouillon into 1/2 cup salsa.
Set aside.

title: chicken glace
directions: In a small saucepan, sprinkle gelatine over cold water.
Let stand one minute, then stir over low heat about three minutes. Set aside.

title: spiced pecans
directions: Beat well egg white and 1 tablespoon water.
Add nuts and coat well.
Put sugar, cinnamon and salt into plastic bag.
Add nuts and coat well.
Lightly oil jelly roll pan and spread nuts in pan. Bake at 250° for 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes.
Separate pecans and store in airtight container.

title: potluck potatoes
directions: Place unpeeled potatoes in saucepan; cover with water.
Cook until tender, but firm.
Drain; cut potatoes into 1 inch cubes. Place in an ungreased 2 1/2-quart casserole.
Add pimento, onion, garlic salt and onion salt; toss gently.
Sprinkle with cheese. Place the bread cubes on top and pour butter over all.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes or until bread is toasted. Yield:
10 to 12 servings.

title: cranberry salad mold
directions: Crush sauce with fork.
Soak gelatin in water for 2 minutes in small
bowl; set bowl in larger bowl containing very hot water, stir until dissolved.

title: homemade brownies
directions: Mix cocoa and baking soda in a bowl. Add 1/3 cup oil and 1/2 cup boiled water. Stir until thick. Add sugar, eggs and rest of ingredients. Bake in greased 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Prepare cake according to directions on box-let cool.

title: liver i'll even eat
directions: Sprinkle liver slices with salt and pepper, then coat lightly with flour; shake off excess.
Dip each floured liver slice into beaten egg, then into cracker crumbs until evenly coated.
Melt 2 tablespoons of the butter in a wide frying pan over medium-high heat.
Cook liver slices quickly until nicely browned on both sides and juicy pink inside (about 3 to 4 minutes total).

title: amish shoo-fly pie
directions: Mix ingredients together thoroughly in a bowl until crumbs are formed.

title: mexican meat loaf
directions: Combine ground meat, 2/3 c. picante sauce, crackers and eggs. Form into a loaf and place in greased loaf pan; top with picante sauce.
Bake at 350 degrees for 1-1/2 hours.

title: summer chicken salad
directions: Combine the mayonnaise and whipped topping. Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well. Serve on lettuce bed.

title: carrot casserole
directions: Boil sliced carrots for 20 minutes.
Strain and set aside. Saute the diced celery in the margarine for 5 minutes.
In a large bowl, combine all ingredients.
Bake in a 9 x 12-inch baking dish at 350° for about 20 to 25 minutes.

title: amazing coconut pie
directions: Mix all ingredients except coconut; beat on low speed for 3 minutes.
Pour into a 9-inch greased pie pan.
Let set in pan 5 minutes, then add coconut.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix altogether.
Bake at 350° to 375° for 45 to 60 minutes. Use large loaf pan.

title: memaw's chocolate fudge icing
directions: Boil all ingredients together 3 minutes.
Cool.
Beat and frost cake.

title: ham quiche wedges
directions: Mix eggs (beaten), sour cream, cheese, onion and onion salt. Sprinkle ham in pie shell.
Pour egg mixture over ham and bake about 25 minutes.
Bake at 425°.
Let stand 5 minutes before cutting.

title: cashew deviled eggs
directions: Cut eggs in half lengthwise and remove yolks.
Mash egg yolks; add mayonnaise, sour cream, salt and mustard.
Blend well.
Fill egg whites with mixture.
Sprinkle cashews on top.

title: pecan fingers
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix shortening and confectioners sugar thoroughly.
Stir in flour.
With hands, press and flatten mixture in ungreased oblong pan, 9 x 13-inches.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes.

title: banana-nut cake(diabetic)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine dry ingredients in large bowl. Add all remaining ingredients, except walnuts and Cream Cheese Glaze; mix well.
Stir in walnuts.
Spread into well-greased Bundt or tube pan.
Bake for 50 to 55 minutes, or until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool in pan on wire rack 15 minutes.
Turn cake out onto wire rack.
Cool completely.
If desired, prepare Cream Cheese Glaze.
Spoon over top of cake, letting excess glaze drip down sides.
Serve at room temperature or chilled.
Makes 12 servings.

title: pretzel salad with strawberries
directions: Mix ingredients and press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 8 minutes at 400° and then cool 1/2 hour.

title: lasagna
directions: Boil noodles until tender.
Brown hamburger.
Add tomato soup, onion, garlic clove, oregano, water and vinegar.
Simmer 15 minutes in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Place cooked noodles (3 to 4) across pan.
On top of noodles, put cottage cheese to cover.
Top with meat sauce and Mozzarella.
Repeat layers until 3 to 4 layers high.
Last layer, sprinkle Parmesan cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes to 1 hour until heated through.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and eggs. Mix together flour, spices and baking powder. Add alternately with milk. Add nuts, pumpkin and baking soda. Mix well and pour into a 9 x 13 x 2 pan. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: maryland crab cakes
directions: Remove shells from crab meat.
Add all of the above ingredients in order listed.
Shape into 10 to 12 cakes and fry in hot oil until golden brown or broil.

title: strawberry and pretzel salad
directions: Mix pretzels, 1 tablespoon sugar and melted margarine in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 400° for 8 minutes.
Beat cream cheese and sugar together.
Beat in Cool Whip.
Spread over cooled, baked crust.
Spread completely to the edges so jelly layer doesn't make soggy.

title: raw apple pie
directions: Mix first four ingredients in bowl; add beaten eggs, butter and vanilla and fold in chopped apples.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes; reduce heat to 350° and bake for 25 minutes.
This fills two pastry filled pie pans.

title: bean casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Place half of mixture in casserole dish.
Sprinkle with slivered almonds.
Add remaining half of mixture, topping with more almonds.
Bake in 350° oven until bubbly.
A few minutes before serving, add grated cheese and 1 can French fried onions; heat through.

title: southern corn dressing
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Mix bread, eggs and other ingredients well.
Should be consistency of cake batter or thick soup or it will cook up too dry.
Put in a greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Bake about 40 minutes.

title: squash and sausage casserole
directions: Cook sausage and drain.
Cook squash and drain.
Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into baking dish.
Bake at 375° until bubbly.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cream Crisco, peanut butter, sugar, brown sugar,
milk
and
vanilla in large bowl at medium speed until well blended.
Beat in egg.
Combine flour, baking soda, baking powder
and
salt.	Mix
into
creamed
mixture.
Drop rounded tablespoonfuls
of	dough 2-inches apart onto greased baking sheet.
Flatten in crisscross pattern with fork dipped in flour. Bake
at
350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Cool 2 minutes on baking sheet.
Remove to cooling rack.

title: spicy shrimp casserole
directions: Peel shrimp; devein if desired.
Place cooked rice in a bowl. Add shrimp, cheese and soup to rice.
Melt butter in a large skillet over medium-high heat and add green onions.
Cook, stirring constantly, until tender.
Stir green onions, Worcestershire sauce and next 4 ingredients into rice mixture. Spoon into lightly greased 11 x 7 x 1 1/2-inch (or 2-quart) baking dish.
Bake casserole at 375° for 45 minutes.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: parmesan-pepper dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together gently.

title: ritz ice cream cake
directions: Roll crackers; put into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Melt margarine and pour over crumbs.
Add pecans and mix well.
Reserve 1/2 cup for topping and spread evenly in pan.
Melt ice cream (almost soupy). Mix in dry pudding and pour over crumb mixture.
Spread Cool Whip over all and sprinkle on your 1/2 cup reserved topping.
Freeze overnight.

title: russell stover candy
directions: Mix together; chill 2 hours or overnight.
Roll in balls and chill again.
Dip in chocolate.

title: puppy chow
directions: Melt oleo, chocolate chips and peanut butter.
Pour over Crispix.
Mix well. Put into large brown grocery bag.
Add 1 cup powdered sugar.
Shake well.
Add another cup; shake well.
Add 1/2 cup and shake well.
Pieces should be individually coated.
If needed, add another 1/2 cup powdered sugar.

title: pecan crispies
directions: Cream butter and sugar. Beat in egg and vanilla. Sift flour. Blend into creamed mixture. Stir in nuts. Drop from teaspoon on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake 10 minutes at 375°. Makes 2 1/2 dozen.

title: homemade mayonnaise
directions: Into blender put egg, vinegar, mustard, salt and 1/4 cup of oil.
Cover blender.
Blend 15 seconds on chop.
Remove cover and pour in remaining oil in a fast stream.
Blend 3 seconds on liquefy.
Store in small sealed container in refrigerator.

title: daddy bob's fish stew
directions: Fry bacon in Dutch oven and leave bacon in Dutch oven with fat. Add can of tomatoes, ketchup, Worcestershire sauce, potatoes, salt and pepper to taste and red pepper.
Cook until potatoes are done. Add bass fillets and cook until fish flakes.
Serves 6.

title: mounds cake
directions: This recipe is best made the day before you want to serve it. Make cake according to package. Bake in greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Allow to cool. Make holes all over cake with a long-tined fork. Add milk to cream of coconut until it measures 2 cups. Mix slowly. Pour over top of cake. Spread whipped topping over top and sprinkle on lots of coconut. Place in refrigerator. Stays moist 3 to 4 days.

title: kiwi fruit salad
directions: Put pineapple, bananas and oranges in a bowl.
Squeeze lemon juice over them.
Add strawberries and kiwi fruit and mix well. Boil honey with 3/4 cup water; cool.
Pour over salad and mix well.
Refrigerate 1 hour to blend flavors.

title: caramel corn
directions: Notice:
Use a brown grocery bag; cut 6 to 8 inches off the top to fit in the microwave.

title: taco casserole
directions: Brown meat in small amount of shortening.
Add taco mix; stir until mixed.
Add water and soups.
Cook, stirring, until mixture simmers.
Remove from heat.
Place alternate layers of tacos and meat mixture in casserole.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Yields 8 servings.

title: biscuits
directions: Mix all ingredients together and knead real good.
Preheat oven to 425°.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes.

title: duck with turnips
directions: Fry duck lightly on both sides.
Make gravy by browning the flour in butter.
Add chopped onion and let mellow.
Add parsley, green onion and celery with 3 cups of water.
Let all simmer for 10 minutes.
Add duck to gravy and cook until it begins to tenderize.
Add parboiled turnips and cook until duck is tender.

title: easy banana bread
directions: Grease and flour a loaf pan.
(I use the miniature loaf pans.)
Mash banana and mix in egg, oil and sugar.	Mix well and then add flour and nuts.
Pour into pan and bake at 350° for metal or 300° for glass pan for 45 to 50 minutes or until toothpick inserted comes out clean.

title: salad supreme
directions: Drain pineapple, saving juice.
Mix jello according to directions and pour into 9 x 13-inch Pyrex dish.
When almost congealed, add pineapple and nuts.
Congeal completely.
Mix cream cheese and Cool Whip and spread on jello.
Cool.
To pineapple juice, add lemon juice, sugar, flour and eggs.
Cook over low heat until thick.
Chill.
When cool, pour over jello-cream cheese.

title: old recipe for homemade bread
directions: Add yeast to lukewarm water and 1 teaspoon of sugar.
In saucepan, heat the 2 cups of milk until scalded; add shortening, 2 tablespoons of sugar and salt.
Cool to lukewarm.
Add yeast mixture, then flour.
Let rise until doubled, then work down and let rise again.
Make into buns or loaves and let rise again. Bake at 350° until done.

title: candy orange slice cake
directions: Soften 1 cup butter or margarine.
Add 2 - 3 oz. packages cream cheese, beat until smooth and creamy.
Sift and measure 2 cups flour.

title: black forest cherry dessert
directions: In saucepan, heat all ingredients, except ice cream.
Spoon ice cream into six dishes.
Pour warm cherry mixture over the ice cream.
Serve immediately.
Delicious!

title: touchdowners
directions: Put Spam and Velveeta cheese through meat grinder.
Mix with enough Miracle Whip to make it spread easily.
Add pickle relish and mix well.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Reserve half of the butter.
Mix the first 9 ingredients and place in well buttered casserole dish.
Mix bread crumbs with the reserved melted butter; sprinkle on top of casserole.
Cover and bake approximately 1 hour and 10 minutes at 350°, then uncover and bake approximately 10 to 15 minutes longer.

title: delicious banana cake
directions: Cream butter; gradually add sugar, beating well.
Add egg yolks, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Dissolve soda in buttermilk; add to creamed mixture alternately with flour, beginning and ending with flour.
Stir in mashed bananas and pecans.
Beat egg whites until stiff peaks form.
Fold into batter.
Pour batter into 2 greased and floured 8-inch round pans. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chicken breast fillets
directions: Heat oil in skillet; brown garlic cloves in hot oil.
Remove garlic and add chicken.
Thoroughly brown chicken in oil.
Remove chicken from oil and drain.
Place in 11 x 7-inch pan.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over chicken.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: fruit cake
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients.
Add beaten eggs and vanilla.
Mix well.
Pour batter into 2 brown paper lined and buttered loaf pans. Bake at 250° for 2 1/2 hours.

title: 5 cup salad
directions: Mix dry jello and pineapple; set aside for 10 minutes.
Then add cottage cheese, marshmallows and Cool Whip.
Stir together. Let set overnight in refrigerator before serving.

title: date and nut bread
directions: Mix together dates, baking soda and boiling water; let cool. Cream together sugar, butter and egg.
Add vanilla, flour and nuts.
Mix all together.
Makes 1 loaf.
Line pan with wax paper on bottom.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: duane's slop
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Stir in soup and noodles. Simmer for 5 minutes.
Serve over toast.
Yield:
8 servings.

title: walnut crescents
directions: Mix flour and cinnamon.
Reserve.
Beat margarine, corn syrup and vanilla in a large bowl on medium speed until well blended. Stir in flour mixture and walnuts.
Cover and refrigerate until chilled and easy to handle, at least 3 hours.
Heat oven to 350°. Shape dough by rounded teaspoonfuls into rolls, 2-inches long. Place 2-inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet, shaping to form crescents.
Bake until light brown on bottoms, 15 to 18 minutes. Cool on wire rack.
Roll in powdered sugar.
Makes about 6 dozen cookies.

title: chicken nuggets
directions: Skin chicken and cut meat off bones.
Dip in batter and deep fry in vegetable oil.

title: easy yeast rolls
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together in a large bowl.
Add enough flour to make a soft dough.
Beat with a fork.
Cover with a little oil and let rise.
Will keep in the refrigerator for several days.

title: orange slice cookies
directions: Mix orange slices (pieces) with 1/4 c. flour.
Mix next ingredients in order given.
Add orange slices.
Roll into balls and put on greased cookie sheet.
Bake for 10 to 12 minutes at 350°.

title: delightful banana pudding
directions: Put
broken
up
angel
food cake pieces in large bowl. Put cut
up
bananas
and strawberries on top of cake pieces. When cool, pour banana pudding over all.
Stir gently.
Place in refrigerator
to chill well.
May be served with Cool Whip on top or as is.

title: aunt lou's rolls
directions: Mix the Crisco, sugar and boiling water; let cool.
Dissolve yeast in warm water; let stand 5 minutes.
(I use 1 envelope of quick rise.)
Add flour and beat well.
Refrigerate overnight. Roll out and let rise.
Bake at 400° for approximately 15 minutes. Makes at least 48 small rolls.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Combine shortening, sugars, eggs, water and vanilla. Sift together flour, salt and soda and combine with creamed mixture. Stir in oatmeal. Drop by teaspoonful onto cookie sheet. Bake at 350° 12 to 15 minutes.

title: peach yum yum
directions: Mix ingredients and put a thin layer of crumbs in a 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: reception punch
directions: Boil sugar and water about 5 minutes.
Cool.
Add juices, tea and water mixture.
Pour over ice and add ginger ale or mix all at once if you're planning to use most of drink.
Keeps well.
Makes large quantity.

title: cheese cake
directions: Heat 1 cup until hot.
Graham cracker crust can be made with 1/2 stick margarine and 1 3/4 cups graham cracker crumbs.

title: banana pineapple salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in hot water.
Add marshmallows and chill. When mixture has set to the consistency of egg whites, stir in pineapple.
Pour in a 13 x 9 pan and let jell.
Mix sugar, flour, pineapple juice and eggs in saucepan, cook over low heat until thickened.
Add cream cheese and stir until smooth.
Fold in whipped topping mix prepared according to directions.
Cool.
When gelatin layer is set, slice bananas over top.
Layer cream cheese mixture over that and top with nuts.

title: crab imperial
directions: Cook first 3 ingredients until thick, stirring constantly. Add Worcestershire sauce and set aside to cool.
Mix mayonnaise, lemon juice, salt and pepper together and add to cooled mixture. Add cubed bread.
Melt 3 tablespoons butter and fold into crabmeat.
Mix all ingredients together and bake in 350° oven for 20 to 30 minutes in a buttered baking dish.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Line a buttered casserole dish with chicken.
Heat soups.
Combine with sour cream.
Pour over chicken.
Sprinkle with cracker crumbs.
Drizzle with melted oleo. Bake at 350° until mixture bubbles, about 15 to 20 minutes.

title: mexican lasagne
directions: Brown meat; add onion and garlic.
Sprinkle with chili powder. Add tomato sauce, sugar, olives and chilies.
Simmer 15 minutes.

title: barbecue meatballs
directions: Combine all ingredients and shape into balls. Place in 9 x 13 pan. Pour sauce over top. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: orange congealed salad(low cal)
directions: Drain pineapple and reserve juice.
Heat 1 1/2 cups water and pineapple juice.
Add jello and stir.
Add 2 packages Equal.
Add 1 1/2 cups cold water.
Put in refrigerator; let slightly thicken. Add crushed pineapple and cottage cheese and mix well.
(Beat cottage cheese with mixer.) Let set in refrigerator.
Makes 8 servings.

title: creamy spinach lasagna
directions: Prepare noodles.
In skillet over medium heat cook onion, mushrooms and garlic until tender.
Remove from heat.
Stir in spinach, oregano, basil and pepper; set aside.
In food processor blend cottage cheese, egg whites, flour and 1 cup Mozzarella. Preheat oven to 375°.
In 13 x 9-inch pan arrange 3 noodles.
Top with half spinach, half cheese mixture and half of tomato sauce. Arrange 3 more noodles; repeat layers.
Top with remaining 3 noodles.
Sprinkle with remaining Mozzarella and Parmesan.
Bake 45 minutes or until bubbly.
Remove from oven; let stand 10 minutes.
Makes 12 servings.

title: chicken in foil
directions: Sprinkle 3 tablespoons onion soup mix onto each chicken breast. Wrap individually in foil.
Bake at 350° for one hour.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Drain pineapple and reserve 2 tablespoons juice.
Mix pineapple and cheese. Put in a buttered casserole dish.
Mix flour and sugar; sprinkle over pineapple.
Pour reserved juice over this.
Crush Ritz crackers and mix with melted oleo.
Pour over pineapple mix.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: maw-maw's fudge
directions: Add the first 5 ingredients; stir well over low heat until melted.
Bring to a boil over medium heat; cook over low heat with no stirring to reach soft ball stage (10 to 15 minutes).
Remove from heat; let stand 30 to 40 minutes (110°).
Stir in remaining ingredients; beat vigorously with wooden spoon until it loses its gloss.
Pour into an 8 or 9-inch pan.
(When marshmallows are melted, beating is probably over.)

title: no-fail popovers
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
In mixing bowl, beat eggs slightly. Add remaining ingredients; beat just until smooth.
Do not overbeat.
Fill generously greased muffin cups half full.
Bake at 450° for 15 minutes, then reduce heat to 325° and bake 25 to 30 minutes, or until golden brown.
Prick crust with tip of knife during last 5 minutes of baking to allow steam to escape.
Serve hot.
Makes 6 to 8 popovers.
Use popover cups for larger, higher rising muffins.

title: orange-pecan muffins
directions: Beat
cream
cheese
with electric mixer until light and fluffy.
Add
biscuit mix and sugar; mix well.
Add the remaining ingredients,
stirring
just
until moistened.
Spoon into greased muffin
pans, filling 2/3 full.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Yields 1 1/2 dozen.

title: stuffed green peppers
directions: Place tomato juice, rice and onion over low heat until juice is absorbed.
Mix with other ingredients and fill peppers.
Place in pan with lid.
Cover and bake in oven at 300° for 30 minutes. No need to precook peppers if you like them firm.
Peppers are usually large so I cut them across like you would an orange and fill the 2 sides.
Very good.

title: blim(potato pancakes)
directions: In blender, combine egg, onion and Bisquick.
Set on "chop"; blend until smooth.
Gradually add potato chunks.
Blend on low speed.
Heat oil in large skillet.
Spoon potato batter into skillet.
Turn each potato cake once.
Fry until golden brown. Serve for breakfast, lunch or dinner.

title: chicken parmigiana
directions: Dip chicken in milk; dredge in bread crumbs; set aside.
Heat olive oil in large skillet over medium heat until hot; add chicken and cook 4 minutes on each side or until golden brown.
Remove from skillet and place chicken in baking dish.
Pour sauce over chicken, top with cheese and bake at 350° until cheese begins to turn golden brown (15 minutes).

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Thoroughly cream butter, peanut butter, egg and vanilla.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Blend into creamed mixture.
Shape in 1-inch balls.
Roll in granulated sugar.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Cool slightly; remove from pan.

title: bok choy salad
directions: Remove flavor packets from soup mix; reserve for another use. Crumble noodles.
Combine noodles, sunflower seeds, and almonds. Spread on a 15 by 10 inch jellyroll pan.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes or until golden brown; set aside.
Bring sugar and next 3 ingredients to a boil in a saucepan over medium heat.
Remove from heat; cool.
Place bok choy and green onions in a large bowl. Drizzle with sugar mixture.
Add ramen noodles mixture, tossing well.
Serve immediately.
Yield: 6 to 8 servings.	Prep time 15 minutes, bake time 10 minutes.

title: zucchini pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a greased pie pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients well.
Shape into balls.
Place on waxed paper.
Melt the Hershey bar, chocolate chips and paraffin. Dip balls in chocolate.
Cool on waxed paper.

title: tex-mex
directions: Brown hamburger.
Mix with all ingredients, except cheese.
Put into 9 x 13 casserole.
Cover with cheese.
Bake at 375° until cheese is melted.

title: peanut butter oatmeal cookies
directions: Cook sugar, milk and margarine for 1 1/2 minutes.
After it starts to boil, remove from heat and add vanilla and peanut butter.
Pour over nuts and oatmeal.
Mix until blended.
Drop by teaspoon on wax paper and cool.

title: tuna melts
directions: In a mixing bowl, stir tuna, salad dressing and celery until well blended. Top each cracker with 1 teaspoon of tuna mixture. Sprinkle with 1/2 teaspoon cheese. Place on microwaveproof plate and microwave on High for 15 seconds or until cheese is melted.

title: little shoes (papoutsakia)(greek)
directions: Cut eggplant in half lengthwise.
Scoop out insides and chop. Fry shells in a little butter until a bit soft, then put in baking dish.
Saute onions in all but 2 tablespoons butter. Add meat and brown. Add eggplant pulp, salt, pepper, parsley and sauce.
Mix well and simmer 15 minutes.
Cool.
