Fill eggplant shells. Sprinkle with cheese. Bake at 350° until soft, approximately 30 minutes. Preparation time: 45 to 60 minutes.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix together creamed and Niblets corn, 1/2 box muffin mix, egg, sour cream and melted butter.
Stir well and place in 9 x 14-inch Pyrex dish.
Mix Cheddar cheese and crushed Ritz crackers together and sprinkle on top of casserole.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: yellow cake bread
directions: Beat all
together
at
high speed for 5 minutes.
In a cup, mix 1/2 cup sugar and 2 teaspoons cinnamon and set aside. Spray Bundt pan with Pam.
Pour 1/2
cake mixture in bottom of pan, then add cinnamon mixture.
Add
rest
of batter and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Drizzle
powdered sugar frosting over after cool.

title: pineapple delight
directions: Bake cake in 9 x 15-inch pan and cool.
Mix cream cheese and juice from pineapple until smooth.
Add instant pudding and milk. Beat until thick.
Spread mixture over cake.
Then spread pineapple over pudding mixture.
Add Cool Whip.
Refrigerate for several hours.
Can be frozen.

title: cornbread salad
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Refrigerate overnight before serving.

title: spinach dip
directions: Drain spinach; press between paper towels until barely moist.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream the shortening, sugar and bananas.
Add eggs.
Sift flour, salt and soda. Add.
Add vanilla and nuts, if desired. Bake.

title: peppy pecan balls
directions: Combine cheeses, mixing well.
Stir in chilies; mix thoroughly.
Form into bite size balls; roll in pecans.
Chill until firm.

title: 5 cup salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Increase amounts as needed for increase in number of people served.

title: beef-a-roni(a skillet meal; large skillet)
directions: Prepare macaroni according to directions.
While macaroni is cooking, brown ground beef in oil in a large skillet.
Add onions, celery, green pepper, oregano, basil, parsley, garlic, salt and pepper.
When beef mixture is done, add tomato paste, tomatoes and 1 cup water. Simmer about 10 minutes.
Add macaroni and cook about 5 minutes more.
Sprinkle Parmesan, then other cheese on top of beef and macaroni. Cover, turn off heat and let stand 2 or 3 minutes until cheese is melted.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: hamburger crescent
directions: Saute hamburger, onion and bell pepper until hamburger is brown.
Stir in soup.
Place crescent rolls in bottom of baking dish so points of dough are hanging over edge of dish.
Place hamburger mixture on top of rolls in baking dish.
Fold points of rolls over top.
Bake at 325° until rolls are light brown. Sprinkle with cheese and allow cheese to melt prior to serving.

title: sweet and sour(chicken, pork or shrimp)
directions: Cook
and
dice
chicken.
Drain
pineapple and reserve juice. Combine
pineapple juice, brown sugar, catsup, vinegar and garlic powder.
Bring to a boil.
Combine cornstarch with a little
cold water,
then
add to sauce mixture to thicken. Add green
pepper strips and pineapple at the last minute and cook just
enough to heat.
Pour over diced chicken or pork or shrimp.

title: cherry apricot crisp
directions: Drain fruit and arrange in buttered 8-inch square pan.
Mix together rest of ingredients.
Crumble on fruit mixture.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Serve with cream.

title: calico beans
directions: Mix together all ingredients thoroughly.
Bake in a large casserole for 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: biscuits
directions: Melt butter with all dry ingredients in pan.
(I use Marie Callendar pie pan.)
Cut biscuits into quarters.
Dip in melted butter to coat and bake according to directions on biscuit can.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Beat oil, eggs and sugar.
Add dry ingredients; mix well.
Add vanilla, apples and nuts; mix well.
Grease and flour tube or Bundt pan.
Bake at 250° for 1 1/2 hours.
Cool and invert.

title: holly taters
directions: Cut potatoes into wedges.
Shake in flour mixture.
Place in oven dish.
Melt 1 stick of margarine and pour over potatoes. Bake at 400° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: sausage quiche
directions: Line pie crust with sliced cheese.
Place scrambled sausage over this.
Spread with grated cheese on top of sausage.
Beat eggs and milk and pour over top.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: mexican casserole
directions: In skillet or large pot, brown meat in oil. When brown, add onion and garlic. Saute 3 minutes. Turn off heat and add soups and sauce. Cook on medium heat until almost boiling. Add cheese (cut into pieces) until creamy. Stir often to prevent sticking.
Line baking dish with broken soft tortillas.
Spoon layer of meat sauce and layer of tortilla, ending with meat sauce. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes. Serve with toasted tortillas.

title: taco dip
directions: Mix sour cream and taco seasoning together.
Place on bottom of casserole.
Layer cheese, lettuce, tomatoes, black olives and green onions on top of taco mixture.
Serve with tortilla chips. Add jalapeno peppers if desired.

title: old-fashion egg salad
directions: In a bowl, combine mayonnaise, lemon juice, onion, salt and pepper.
Stir in eggs and celery.
Cover and chill.
Spoon 1/2 cup on a slice of bread and enjoy.

title: super great crab spread
directions: Mix together and cream well.
Spread evenly over large plate. Cover with 3/4 bottle chili sauce.
On top of that, cover with 3/4 (12 ounce) cooked crab meat, well drained (squeeze it).
Cover with sprinkle of dried parsley.
Refrigerate overnight.
Serve with favorite crackers.

title: hoagie on a stick
directions: *Can use small piece of any kind of tomatoes.

title: amish no peek chicken
directions: Place all ingredients but chicken and soup mix in glass casserole dish.
Mix well.
Put chicken on top, then sprinkle soup mix on top.
Cover and bake 2 1/2 hours at 350°.
Do not uncover until done.

title: ulana's mushroom soup
directions: In a skillet, melt 2 tablespoons of the butter.
Saute onion until limp and golden.
Add mushrooms and continue cooking until they are dark.
Remove mushroom mixture from skillet and set aside.
Melt remaining butter in skillet, and add carrots and celery.
Cook until celery is translucent but still firm. Sprinkle one tablespoon flour over carrots and celery.
Stir to blend well.

title: homemade ice cream
directions: Combine sugar, flour and salt.
Add Eagle Brand milk. Separate egg yolks and add to mixture.
Beat egg whites and fold into mixture.
Add enough regular milk to make one gallon of milk.

title: zucchini tomato casserole
directions: Grease casserole dish.
Place a layer of parboiled zucchini, fresh tomato and onion.
Sprinkle salt, pepper, sugar and sharp cheese.
Continue layering and sprinkling until you have 3 layers. Bake, covered, for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: layered lettuce salad
directions: Layer one item on top of each other in order listed. Refrigerate overnight. Stir well before serving until mayonnaise and sugar are well combined and form a dressing like creamy slaw dressing.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Drain kraut and rinse if desired.
Mix other ingredients in kraut and let marinate for an hour or longer.

title: chocolate eclair
directions: Mix pudding with 3 cups of milk.
Add Cool Whip.
In a 9 1/2 x 11-inch container, layer whole graham crackers.
Pour 1/2 pudding mixture on top of crackers.
Put another layer of whole graham crackers and pour the remainder of pudding mixture on top of crackers.
Put another layer of whole graham crackers and pour chocolate frosting on top.
(Soften frosting slightly in microwave.)
Refrigerate.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder, baking soda and spices. Combine with the pumpkin, sugar and eggs.
In a mixing bowl, mix until well blended.
Stir in nuts. Spread well in a greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 45 to 50 minutes.
Test with toothpick in center.
If it comes out clean, bread is done.

title: spaghetti casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and onion in a skillet over medium heat. Drain; add butter, mushroom soup, tomatoes, water and garlic powder; set aside.
Cook 1/2 pound spaghetti, drain and put in bottom of casserole dish (9 x 13-inch).
Add beef mixture and top with grated cheese.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.
This freezes well and may be made in two containers.
Serve one, freeze one.

title: french chocolate cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and lightly flour single round cake pan.
Melt 4 ounces semi-sweet chocolate pieces and 1 tablespoon instant coffee that has been mixed with 2 tablespoons of water.

title: holiday vegetable bake
directions: In 2-quart casserole, combine vegetables, soup, milk and half of the onion rings.
Bake in 375° oven for 45 minutes until vegetables are crisp-tender, stirring occasionally.
Sprinkle with remaining onion rings before serving.

title: texas pie
directions: Layer the ingredients in the following order:
pie filling, pineapple, cake mix, coconut and pecans chips.
Layer in a 9 x 13-inch pan, then melt 2 sticks oleo and pour over it.
Bake at 350° for about 20 minutes.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Bake cake as package directs in two layers.
After the cake cools, split each layer in two layers. Mix sugar and flour together.
Melt margarine and add sugar mixture.
Add the eggs and pineapple.
Cook until thick.
Spread on the cake layers and assemble cake while the topping is warm.

title: canadian cheese soup
directions: Cook onions in butter until tender.
Blend in flour.
Add remaining ingredients, except cheese.
Cook and stir until thickened and bubbly.
Reduce heat; add cheese and stir until cheese melts.
Simmer 15 minutes.

title: sweet sour chicken
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Place 4 cut-in-half boneless chicken breasts in baking dish; pour mixture over breasts and bake at 350° for one hour.
Serve over cooked rice.

title: chess pie
directions: Mix dry ingredients; add butter and mix well.
Add vanilla and vinegar, mixing well.
Pour in 9-inch pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: tomato chili sauce
directions: Cook until thick about 3 hours.

title: barbecue sandwiches
directions: Cut fat off meat.
Cut meat into small chunks.
Cook in pot with cut up onion, salt, pepper and water.
Simmer until meat is in shreds (several hours).
Pour in bottles of catsup and barbecue sauce to taste.
Simmer until it is a good sandwich consistency. Serve hot on a hamburger bun.

title: impossible mexican pie
directions: Lightly grease a 10-inch pie plate.
Cook and stir ground beef and onion in skillet until beef is brown.
Drain.
Stir in seasoning mix.
Spread beef mixture in pie plate.
Sprinkle with chilies and cheese.
Beat remaining ingredients until smooth, 15 seconds on high speed of blender or high speed of mixer for 1 minute.
Pour over ingredients in pie plate.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes before cutting.

title: hot mexican dip
directions: Spread cream cheese in
8 x 8-inch pan.
Put in refried beans.
Top with chili.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake or microwave until cheese is melted.

title: chinese noodle cookies
directions: Place chips and Crisco in top of double boiler.
Melt and stir until creamy. Add noodles and nuts.
Stir well. Drop by teaspoons onto lightly greased cookie sheet. Chill 10 to 15 minutes.

title: crumb cake
directions: Add 2 tablespoons lemon juice to milk to sour.
Combine brown sugar, 2 cups flour, salt and butter.
Take out 1 scant cup and put aside.
Add all remaining ingredients (except cup of flour and brown sugar mixture) and mix well.
Pour into 13 x 9-inch greased and floured pan.
Sprinkle with mixture in cup already set aside. Sprinkle cinnamon on top.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 35 minutes. Check for doneness by touching top, bounces back.
Excellent with egg souffle or just coffee.

title: s'mores(microwave)
directions: Break graham cracker into square shapes.
Put a square of chocolate on graham cracker.
Top with marshmallow and graham cracker square.
Cook on High in microwave for 10 seconds.

title: vegetable hampshire salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water; add lemon juice and chill until slightly thickened.
Blend cottage cheese, sour cream and salt together.
Stir into jello.
Add remaining ingredients.
Chill until firm or overnight.
Can use lime jello and canned peas.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour in pie shell and bake at 325° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: hot brown sandwich(originally served  at the brown hotel in louisville, kentucky)
directions: Melt the butter or margarine in a saucepan.
Add onion and cook slowly until light brown, about 15 to 20 minutes.
Add flour and blend until the flour makes a smooth paste with the onion minces in it.
Add milk and other seasonings and cook, stirring constantly and briskly, until the sauce is thick and smooth. Then continue to cook, stirring occasionally, about 25 minutes altogether.
Strain.
If the sauce isn't to be used immediately, stir occasionally to keep a crust from forming on the top.

title: microwave caramel corn
directions: Combine brown sugar, margarine, corn syrup and salt in 4-cup glass microwave bowl.
Bring to a boil.
Cook on High for 2 more minutes.
Remove from microwave and add baking soda; stir.
Put popped popcorn in brown grocery bag.
Pour syrup over popped corn. Close bag and shake.
Cook in microwave for 1 1/2 minutes on High.
Shake bag well and cook 1 1/2 minutes more.
Cool on cookie sheet.
This way, you won't have to break it up too much.

title: cucumber dip
directions: Peel and grate cucumber (not seeds) and drain off liquid. Combine this with the remaining ingredients.
Mix in blender. Chill and serve with favorite chips.
Yields 1 3/4 cups.

title: norwegian apple pie
directions: In a large mixing bowl, combine ingredients.
Stir until blended.
Turn mixture into a 9-inch buttered pie pan.
Mixture will be stiff.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until lightly brown.
Serve warm or cold.
Serve with Cool Whip or vanilla ice cream.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: zucchini hot cakes
directions: Mix ingredients (should be thick batter consistency).
Spoon into frypan greased with oleo or butter.
Fry until brown.

title: dorilas chop suey
directions: Cook meat with salt and pepper until done.
Cut celery and onions into small pieces.
Add to meat and cook until tender.
Add tomato soup and soy sauce.
Serve over boiled rice or mashed potatoes with Chinese noodles.

title: feather rolls
directions: Put warm milk and yeast in mixing bowl.
Let stand for five minutes and stir well.
Add sugar, salt and egg.
Beat with mixer until well blended.
Add flour, beat, cover the bowl and let rise 5 minutes.
Stir batter down and fill well-greased muffin tins 1/2 full.

title: wine cake
directions: Mix altogether.
Cook in tube pan at 350° for 45 minutes (or until done).
Do not eat for 24 hours.
It is really a good cake.

title: chinese ginger garlic asparagus
directions: Snap off and discard tough ends of asparagus.
Cut spears into 1/4 slanting slices.
Place wok over high heat; when wok is hot, add oil.
When oil begins to heat, add garlic and ginger and stir once, then add asparagus and stir-fry for 1 minute.
Add water, cover and cook 2 to 3 minutes.

title: peanut butter cookies(no sugar)
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Cream together margarine, peanut butter, orange rind and vanilla.
Add egg, orange juice and artificial sweetener; blend well.
Add dry ingredients gradually; mix well after each addition.
Add raisins; mix well.
Measure 1 level tablespoon of dough for each cookie; roll between hands to form ball.
Place 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Flatten with fork.
Bake about 15 minutes.
These cookies have better flavor and texture 24 hours after baking.
Makes 24 cookies.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Arrange broccoli in buttered casserole.
Mix soup, mayo, lemon juice and cheese.
Spoon over broccoli.
Top with pimento, crackers and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: aunt kim's taco dip
directions: Mix sour cream, cream cheese and taco seasoning together (blend until smooth).
Pour into at least a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Put shredded lettuce on top of the dip, then chopped tomatoes.
Then top it with shredded cheese.

title: spaghetti pie
directions: Cook spaghetti, drain.	Pour cheeses over all while still warm and mix all together.	This recipe makes two 9 x 13 pans. Bake in oven at 300° for 45 minutes or till cheese melts.
Can use your favorite spaghetti sauce for topping.	You can make this ahead and freeze till you want to serve it.

title: red rice stove top or oven baked
directions: Fry bacon to extract oil.
Slice and cook sausage in bacon grease.
After sausage is cooked, add vegetable and saut.	Then, add liquid ingredients and seasonings.
Bring to a boil.
Taste sauce and add seasonings as necessary.
Make sure that your sauce is tasty and well cooked before moving on.	Then add rice.	The ratio of sauce to rice should be 2:1.
If desire oven bake, cook rice to a boil in sauce mixture.
Place mixture in roasting pan with a lid.
Bake at 350 degrees for 45 minutes or until rice is fluffy.
If desire stove top, bring sauce mixture to a boil.
Cut the heat to low after a boil is reached and allow to steam with a lid on it until rice is fluffy.
Serve with fried chicken and Southern potato salad.

title: ice cream on a stick
directions: Put ice cream in a cup.
Put stick in the ice cream and freeze.
Take out of cup; roll in chocolate syrup and nuts. Freeze again.
Eat.

title: graham pecan treats
directions: Melt butter and brown sugar.
Bring to a boil and boil 3 minutes.
Break graham crackers along seam.
Lay on a cookie sheet.
Pour butter mixture over crackers and spread evenly. Sprinkle with pecans.
Bake at 375° for 7 minutes.
Separate crackers while still warm.

title: chipped beef dip
directions: Combine
all,
except
pecans
and
butter.
Mix
well. Place pecans
on top when you pour mixture into a small casserole dish, then pour butter over the top of the pecans.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: broccoli and cheese casserole
directions: Saute onions in butter until tender.
Combine all ingredients and put in a 9 x 12-inch pan.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: any fruit pie
directions: Combine everything.
Let set 10 to 15 minutes.
Stir occasionally.
Pour into unbaked covered pie shell.
Sprinkle sugar and milk on top of top crust, if desired.
Bake at 425° for 10 minutes, then at 325° for 40 to 50 minutes.
So simple, but so yummy and quick!

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: Cook broccoli with onion added according to package directions.
Add celery seed, cheese and soup.
Dissolve cornstarch in small amount of milk.
Then add with rest of milk to soup.
Heat slowly and thoroughly.
Do not boil.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Blend soups and broth.
Layer chips, chicken, soup mixture and cheese in casserole dish.
Repeat layers until all is used, topping with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: curry cajun spiced chicken
directions: Combine the first 8 ingredients in baking dish; mix well.
Add chicken, turning to coat.
Bake, uncovered, in a 350° oven for 30 minutes, or until tender and no longer pink.

title: gumdrop cookies(mom's)
directions: Cream shortening, margarine, sugars and vanilla.
Beat in eggs until fluffy.
Mix flour, soda and salt and add a small portion of this mixture to diced candy.
Blend in remaining ingredients. Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: peanut butter candy
directions: Combine sugar, margarine and milk in heavy 2 1/2-quart saucepan. Bring to a full rolling boil, stirring constantly. Continue boiling 5 minutes over medium heat, stirring constantly to prevent scorching. Remove from heat; stir in peanut butter and Marshmallow Creme until melted.
Add vanilla; beat until well blended. Pour into greased 13 x 9-inch pan. Cool at room temperature. Cut into squares.
Makes approximately 3 pounds.

title: five cup salad
directions: Mix together (drain fruit).
Can add nuts.

title: easy green enchiladas
directions: Dip each corn tortilla in hot cooking oil to soften tortilla so it will be easier to work with.
Mix both cans of soup and chili peppers in a separate bowl.
Dip each tortilla in soup mixture after dipping in hot cooking oil.
Put 2 tablespoons meat in center of tortilla and roll up.
Put in pan.
Roll each tortilla the same until pan is full.
When pan is full, pour remainder of soup mixture over enchiladas and sprinkle with shredded cheese of choice.
Cook for 15 to 20 minutes at 350° or until cheese is melted.

title: margaret's barbecue
directions: Mix all together in a saucepan and cook on top of stove until done.

title: italian-style sauce
directions: Brown Italian sausage in frypan.
Using a crock-pot, or large pot on low heat, empty contents of tomato paste into pot.
Add water (to equal amounts of tomato paste), stirring constantly. Sauce should be thick, not watery.
Add crushed garlic, oregano and Italian sausage.
Simmer 4 to 6 hours.

title: zucchini-beef skillet
directions: In large skillet, brown beef with onion, stirring frequently. Add tomatoes, dill pickes, garlic, salt and pepper.
Simmer uncovered 5 minutes.
Add zucchini/other squash, cover and cook 15 minutes or until squash is tender.
Serve over egg noodles.

title: sea fare(seafood florentine bake)
directions: Preheat
oven to 350°.
Arrange fish fillets in greased 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle with salt, onion powder and pepper. Spoon
soup
over
fillets.
Top
with spinach.
Beat remaining ingredients with wire whisk until smooth.
Pour over spinach. Bake,
uncovered,
about
40 minutes or until top is golden brown.
Let
stand 10 minutes before serving.
Makes 8 servings.

title: bisquick-velvet crumb cupcakes
directions: Beat all ingredients on low speed for 30 seconds, scraping bowl constantly.
Beat on medium speed 4 minutes, scraping bowl occasionally.
Pour into cupcake pans with paper liners in them. Bake in a 350° oven until golden brown.

title: ten bean soup
directions: Wash bean mix.
Place in pot and cover with water 2 inches above beans.
Soak overnight.

title: gingerbread cookie dough
directions: Cream margarine, sugar, eggs and molasses.
Sift flour, baking soda and spices and add to creamed mixture.
Mix and shape.
Dough is enough for 15 eight-inch gingerbread men.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: banana cake
directions: Mix ingredients and bake at 350° about 50 minutes.
Cook in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: simple punch
directions: Mix and keep in refrigerator; before serving, add 1 quart ginger ale.
Stir well.

title: chinese chicken wings
directions: Mix soy sauce, anise, ginger, allspice and oil in large bowl. Add sugar and stir until dissolved.
Stir in scallions.
Add chicken wings to marinate and coat the wings.
Cover with plastic wrap and refrigerate for 8 hours or overnight.
Preheat oven to 375°.

title: company breakfast bake
directions: Cover the bottom of a 9 inch square pan with frozen hash browns.
Cover hash browns with sausage.
Sprinkle with cheddar cheese. Stir together the remaining ingredients.
Pour this mixture over everything.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350 degrees for 30 minutes.

title: barbecue sauce for pork chops or ribs
directions: Heat oil and add onion and garlic.
Cook until tender, not brown.
Add other ingredients and bring to boil.
Turn down heat and simmer for 5 minutes.
Baste meat last 10 minutes of cooking time with sauce.
Can be stored in refrigerator for several weeks. Yields 1 quart, enough for 3 to 4 chops or ribs.

title: hawaiian chicken
directions: Combine all ingredients, except chicken, to make marinade. Place chicken and marinade in shallow pan.
Refrigerate for 4 hours.
Remove chicken and brown under broiler.
Return chicken to pan with marinade.
Bake uncovered at 325° for 1/2 hour.

title: cherry dump cake
directions: Place pineapple (don't drain) in oblong baking dish.
Place cherry pie filling on top of pineapple.
Pour dry cake mix evenly over mixture.
Slice pieces of butter and cover cake.
Mix well. Bake 35 to 40 minutes.
Check occasionally when baking.
If dry spots in cake mix appear, use extra butter in these spots.

title: onion soup
directions: Heat butter; add onions.
Cook until soft.
Add bouillon and simmer 30 minutes.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Put toast in bowl. Pour soup over toast and top with Parmesan cheese.

title: roasted red potatoes
directions: Cut potatoes into slices.
Toss.
Place in baking dish. Sprinkle with salt, pepper and cheese.
Cover with foil and bake in 350° oven until tender, about 40 minutes.

title: rum cake(newfane inn, europe)
directions: Combine eggs, sugar and vanilla in deep bowl.
Beat with electric or rotary beater until thoroughly mixed.
Set in another bowl containing very hot (not boiling) water and beat about 15 minutes or until mixture is high, light and fluffy.
Remove from hot water and continue beating until mixture is cool.
Sprinkle 1/3 of the flour over egg mixture and fold in gently with slotted spoon.
Repeat until flour is used.
Fold in butter.
Pour into buttered and floured 9-inch spring-form pan (or in 2-inch deep 9-inch layer pan).
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Turn out cake onto cooling rack.
When cold, cut into 2 layers.

title: party salsa
directions: Add red cayenne pepper to taste.
The more added, the hotter it gets.
If mild salsa is wanted, do not add cayenne pepper.
Stir together in pan.
Boil 30 to 40 minutes until thick.
If a thicker salsa is wanted, cook longer.
Serve with corn chips.
Freezes well.

title: pumpkin ribbon bread
directions: For filling, blend cream cheese, 1/3 cup sugar and 1 tablespoon flour together.
Add 1 egg and orange peel.
Stir together.

title: orange glazed cranberry pumpkin bread
directions: Grease two 9 1/4 x 5 1/4 x 2-inch loaf pans.
Preheat oven to 350°.
In large bowl, mix together flour, sugar, baking soda, pumpkin pie spice, salt and baking powder.
In second bowl, stir together remaining ingredients until well mixed.
Add pumpkin mixture to flour mixture and stir until all ingredients are well moistened.
Pour batter into two greased loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 65 minutes or until breads test done with wooden pick.
Cool in pans 10 minutes, then remove to cooling racks.
When completely cooled, drizzle glaze over top and sides.

title: mound's balls
directions: Mix and make into balls.
Chill 1 hour.

title: kentucky pound cake
directions: Separate eggs.
Beat egg whites; set aside.
Mix other ingredients (flour, sugar, oil, drained pineapple, egg yolks and hot water).
Mix well.
Add egg whites, nuts and cinnamon.
Bake 1 hour and 10 minutes in a 325° oven.

title: korean spinach salad
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients in blender.
Arrange spinach, bacon, mushrooms, red onion, mandarin oranges and grapes in bowl.
Pour some of dressing over.
Refrigerate rest of dressing for another salad.
Stores well.

title: mom's pennsylvania dutch chicken pot pie
directions: Cook chicken in enough water to cover until chicken is cooked, about 1 hour.
Remove chicken from bone and cut into small pieces. Return chicken pieces to broth.
Add peeled and quartered potatoes, sliced celery, chopped onions, salt, pepper and egg noodles.
Cook until potatoes and noodles are tender.
Mix flour or cornstarch and milk; add to broth and cook to thicken broth a little.

title: strawberry dessert pizza
directions: Mix graham cracker crumbs and butter.
Press into bottom of pan.
Mix Cool Whip, cream cheese and powdered sugar.
Spread on crust.
Mix water, cornstarch and sugar together.
Bring to boil. Cook until thick and clear.
Add strawberry jello.
Cool and pour on top.
Add strawberries to cover top.
Can use any fruit in season.

title: sunshine pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta.
Drain and rinse with cold water to cool quickly. Drain well.
Drain pineapple, reserving 1/2 cup juice.
Mix reserved juice together with all ingredients except pineapple and broccoli.
Cover and chill.
Toss pasta mixture just before serving.
Arrange pineapple and broccoli florets around pasta perimeter.
Makes 20 (1-cup) servings.
One serving has 209 calories, 18 calories from fat.

title: cucumber relish
directions: Grate cucumbers, pepper and onions.
Put salt over this mixture and let stand 1 hour.
Drain well, pressing out all water. Add vinegar, sugar and seeds.
Boil 5 minutes.

title: roxanne ney's cranberry salad
directions: Mix together first 4 ingredients.
Let set.
Mix together Cool Whip and cream cheese and spread over top of firm salad.
Sprinkle with walnuts and serve.

title: water chestnuts
directions: Drain water chestnuts.
Cut the bigger ones in half.
Put in bowl; add soy sauce.
Cover chestnuts.
Leave in bowl 5 to 6 hours.
Drain and roll in sugar.
Cut uncooked bacon slices in half.
Wrap chestnuts in bacon and hold bacon together with toothpicks.
Put in pan and bake at 300° until bacon is cooked.

title: bacon breadsticks
directions: Spread breadsticks with butter and sprinkle with garlic powder. Wrap a piece of bacon around sticks, securing with toothpicks. Place on a greased cookie sheet and bake at 350° until bacon is done.

title: chicken pasta salad
directions: Cook chicken and onion in water until done, then bone.
Cut into bite size pieces.
Cook macaroni as label directs; drain.
In 8-quart pot, heat salad oil (1 tablespoon); cook carrots and 1/4 teaspoon salt until tender-crisp, about 3 to 5 minutes.
Remove to bowl.

title: zippy pretzels
directions: Mix butter, soup mix, Worcestershire sauce and garlic powder and pour over pretzels on large cookie sheet.
Make sure to coat well.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Turn every 15 minutes.
Leave in oven 15 minutes after oven is off.

title: apple slices
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients like pie dough.
Press half of dough on 15 x 11-inch cookie sheet.
Cover with mixture of next 4 ingredients.
Roll out rest of dough to cover apples.
Beat egg white with 1 tablespoon of sugar; spread over top crust.
Bake 40 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cover greased casserole with slices of bread (crusts removed). Cover with diced chicken, mushrooms (can use canned ones), water chestnuts and slices of cheese. Spread with mayonnaise.
Add ingredients are done by layers.
Cover this with a mixture of chicken broth, milk, cream of celery soup and eggs, all beaten together.
Put in casserole and let stand overnight.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours or less.
Before finished baking, can cover with bread crumbs and pimentos.

title: dirt dessert
directions: Crush entire package of cookies in blender and set aside.
Mix milk and pudding.
Mix for 1 to 2 minutes, until thick.
Put Cool Whip into large bowl and fold in pudding mixture.
Cream together the cream cheese and margarine.
Add confectioners sugar and fold until well blended.
Start with cookie mixture.
Then alternate layers (leave enough cookie mixture to sprinkle on top to make it look like dirt).

title: hot fudge sundae cake
directions: Melt and cook until thick on low.
Bake cake in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cut in squares when cool.
Cut each square in half and put layer of ice cream between each half.
Pour sauce over cake square.

title: sausage skillet casserole
directions: Brown sausage. Add rice, soup and water. Cook, covered, until rice is done. Add peas and mushrooms. Add Swiss cheese and stir until melted.

title: apple dumplings
directions: Bring to a boil, then set aside to cool.

title: chocolate fudge
directions: Cook sugar and milk to soft ball stage.
Pour over other ingredients and beat.
Then pour in pan and spread flat.
Chill. Makes 5 pounds.

title: barbecue venison
directions: Cook bacon until crisp; drain, reserve drippings.
Crumble bacon and set aside.
Cook venison and onion in drippings until browned.
In saucepan, combine ketchup, vinegar, sugar, Worcestershire sauce, garlic, 1/2 cup water, 1 teaspoon salt and 1/8 teaspoon pepper.
Stir in venison and onion.
Cover and simmer until venison is tender, about 45 to 55 minutes.
This also can be made in crock-pot.
Serve over rice or on a sandwich.

title: blt dip
directions: Mix and chill.
Break up loaf of French bread and dip.

title: vi's pea soup (thick)
directions: Chop vegetables into medium chunks.
Place in large pot with ham and washed peas.
Add enough water to cover ham.
Add bay leaf and pepper, no salt. Cover and bring to a boil, stirring.
Reduce heat immediately and simmer about 2 hours or until the split peas have melted away.
Now you can add salt if you wish.
Remove bay leaf.
Make sure you have some good meat left on the bone.

title: holiday pecan pie
directions: Heat oven to 325. In a mixing bowl, combine eggs, margarine, sugar, and vinegar until well mixed. Stir in coconut, raisins, and pecans. Pour into unbaked pie crust and bake at 325 for 30 to 40 minutes or until filling is set in center.

title: raisin apple crisp
directions: Butter a shallow baking dish, 9 x 12-inch.
Spread apples and raisins evenly in pan.

title: neiman-marcus bars
directions: Combine cake mix with egg and oleo.
Spread in a 14 1/2 x 10 1/2 pan, which has been sprayed with Pam.
Mix sugar, eggs, cream cheese, coconut, and pecans.
Pour over first mixture.
Cool before slicing into bars.
Wonderfully rich and chewy.

title: soup
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Add water (about 1 quart).
You may need to add more as soup cooks.
Cook in crock-pot or on stove for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: turkey spaghetti sauce
directions: Saute onion and garlic in oil in Dutch oven until onion is tender; add turkey.
Cook until done, stirring to crumble meat. Stir in next 9 ingredients.
Simmer, uncovered, for 1 hour.
Add mushrooms and cheese; simmer, uncovered, for 20 minutes.
Remove bay leaf.
Serve over hot spaghetti.
Yields 6 1/2 cups sauce.

title: green tomato pie
directions: Peel tomatoes with a vegetable peeler or immerse in boiling water until skins will slip off, about 3 minutes.
Slice very thin and measure.

title: sausage rolls
directions: Mix all ingredients together and roll into 1-inch balls.
Bake at 350° for about 8 to 10 minutes on ungreased cookie sheet.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Put sugar, cocoa, milk, and butter in saucepan.
Bring to a boil stirring constantly.
After reaching a boil, remove from heat.
Stir in oatmeal, coconut, and peanut butter.
Drop by teaspoonful on a cookie sheet and cool.

title: em's brownies
directions: Mix 1 cup sugar, eggs, 1 stick margarine, baking powder, flour, Hershey's syrup and walnuts.
Bake in jelly roll pan at 350° for 20 minutes.
Boil 6 tablespoons butter, milk and 1 cup of sugar.
Add chocolate bits.
Pour on top of hot brownies.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Combine sweet potatoes, butter, egg yolks, brown sugar, salt and spices; mix well.
Add milk, blending until smooth.
Beat egg whites until foamy; gradually add 1/4 cup sugar, beating until stiff.
Fold into sweet potato mixture.
Pour filling into pie shell.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake an additional 30 minutes.
When cool, garnish with whipped cream and grated orange rind.

title: banana pudding
directions: Cream together oleo, cheese and sugar.
Blend together the instant pudding with 3 cups milk.
Whip according to directions on box.
Blend the whipped topping with the pudding.
Now add the cream cheese mixture.
Layer with cookies and bananas.

title: reuben casserole
directions: Spread the drained sauerkraut on the bottom of a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Lay sliced tomatoes on top.
Spread dressing over tomatoes.
Layer corned beef and then cheese over tomatoes.
Bake at 450° for 1/2 hour.
Remove from the oven.
Separate each Hungry Jack biscuit into 3 pieces and cover the top of the casserole with biscuits.
Bake another 15 minutes or until biscuits brown.

title: california brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray, then flour two 9 x 9-inch pans. Melt butter and chocolate over low heat.
Cool.
Beat eggs, sugar and vanilla with electric mixer on medium speed for 3 minutes. Stir in butter-chocolate mixture, then slowly add the flour.
Do not overmix.
Fold in the cookie crumbs and most of the pecans. Spread the batter evenly into the pans and sprinkle with the remaining pecans.
Bake about 40 minutes or until set.
(The brownies will be soft in the center).
Let cool completely, cut into 3 x 3-inch squares.
Makes 18 brownies.
For extra-rich results, use chocolate bars instead of Baker's chocolate.

title: easy chicken cordon bleu
directions: Cook chicken in 1-inch cooking wine. While cooking, cook bacon in microwave. After chicken is done, stack 2 pieces bacon, 1 to 2 slices of ham and a slice of Swiss cheese on each piece of chicken. Cover until cheese melts. Best served hot with green beans and rice.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream together the sugar and oil.
Add eggs, one at a time, creaming after each.
Add remainder of ingredients; blend together.
Chill 1 hour or more.
Shape into ball.
Roll in sugar. Flatten on cookie sheet with glass.
Sprinkle on more sugar. Bake in a 375° oven for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes about 6 dozen large cookies.

title: chicken noodle soup
directions: Rinse chicken pieces well and remove skin.
Place in a large pot (4 to 6-quart) and cover with cold water.

Place whole allspice and peppercorns in a tea strainer (or cheesecloth) and add to chicken; simmer until chicken is thoroughly cooked (1 to 2 hours). Remove spices and chicken from broth and debone and cut up chicken in bite-size pieces.
Add carrots, celery, chicken and onion powder to broth and simmer 30 minutes.
Add water as needed.
Add noodles and simmer 30 minutes or more.
Just before serving, stir in chopped parsley.

title: chicken with lemon gravy
directions: Cook chicken in microwave until almost done (5 to 7 minutes). Remove and keep warm in a covered dish.

title: chopped liver
directions: Saute onions with butter to soften.
Season with salt and pepper.
Fry liver until done.
Chop eggs, meat, bread and onion. Run through food grinder with fine blade twice.
If mixture appears dry add mayonnaise to suit.
Serve with crackers.

title: butternut squash
directions: Cut stem end off of squash and discard.
Slice squash in half long way.
With a spoon, scoop out the seeds and discard.
Fill cavity with Butter Buds, salt and pepper.
Bake in microwave oven covered for 15 to 25 minutes until done.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Set out all ingredients an hour before mixing.
Cream butter or margarine, Crisco and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Add cocoa.
Add flour and milk alternately, ending with flour.
Add salt and vanilla.
Beat well.
Pour batter into a tube pan of which only the bottom has been greased. Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 35 minutes.

title: green bean salad
directions: Boil 1/2 cup vinegar, 1/2 cup sugar and 1/2 cup salad oil. Pour over ingredients and chill overnight.
Next day before serving, drain off some of the liquid.

title: spaghetti and meatballs
directions: Mix thoroughly; shape into balls.
Prick sausage and brown, then set aside.
Fry meatballs in olive oil until golden brown and remove.

title: mexican corn casserole
directions: Melt butter.
Put in onion.
Pour into bowl all other ingredients; stir well.
Put into a 13 x 9-inch Pyrex dish (greased).
Bake at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: zenobia bryant's fresh apple cake
directions: Combine sugar and
oleo
and
add
eggs in a container; beat well.
Mix with flour and buttermilk all the ingredients, then stir in the
apples.
Bake	in greased baking pan at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: scalloped spinach with cheese
directions: Divide spinach, sauce, cheese, eggs and crumbs.
Place in alternate layers in casserole.
Dot with butter.
Begin and end with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° until crumbs are browned. (Liquid from spinach may be used to prepare white sauce.)
Yield: 4 servings.

title: mushroom fondue sauce
directions: Blend butter and flour.
Add beef broth.
Cook until thick. Add Worcestershire, mushrooms and sour cream.
Heat and serve.

title: sausage and stewed potatoes
directions: Cut sausage into thin slices and fry. Remove from grease and drain. Peel potatoes and cut into 1 in. cubes. Cover with water and boil until tender. Mix flour with 3/4 cup water. Mixture should be very thin with no lumps. Pour mixture into boiling potatoes, stir gently and add the sausage. Cook over medium low heat for 5-10 minutes.

title: caramel toffee bars
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add egg yolk.
Beat until light. Stir in flour, salt and vanilla.
Pat firmly into a lightly buttered 13 x 9-inch cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or just until light golden brown.

title: stuffed grape leaves
directions: Boil grape leaves if from grape vines for 15 minutes.
Lay out grape leaves; stuff like a cabbage.
Place roll of mixture at bottom of leaf, fold in sides and roll.
Place rolled leaves, seam side down in large pot.
After all leaves are rolled, pile in pot. Place large dish over the top of the leaves.
Cover with water; bring to a boil.
Cover pot and simmer for 30 to 45 minutes.
Serve with lemon juice, pita bread and Slata.

title: potato casserole
directions: Combine soup, cheese, onion, sour cream and melted butter. Mix well.
Add hash browns to soup mixture and place in lightly greased 9 x 13-inch dish or pan.
Melt 1/4 cup of butter; mix with 1 stack crushed saltine crackers and spread over top of casserole. Bake in preheated 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: quick chicken and rice
directions: Melt butter in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Put in rice.
Combine soups and heat on Stove Top.
Pour half of soup mixture over rice. Place chicken on top.
Pour rest of soup on top of chicken.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: granny's corn pudding
directions: Beat eggs, sugar, salt and pepper; add corn, then milk.
Add melted butter or margarine.
Pour into a greased baking dish.
Set dish in a pan of cold water.
Place in a cold oven.
Set oven at 400°.
When oven reaches 400°, reduce heat to 275° and cook until knife comes out clear, about 1 hour.

title: easy cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt margarine in baking dish.
In mixing bowl combine dry ingredients and add milk; mix.
Pour over margarine.
Spoon pie filling over top of batter.
Bake for 30 or 35 minutes.

title: extra crispy oven-fried chicken
directions: Remove skin from chicken. Dip chicken in milk, then in Grape-Nuts flakes. Bake in Teflon pan at 400° for 1/2 hour. Reduce heat to 350°. Cover loosely with foil. Bake 20 to 30 minutes longer. Do not turn chicken during baking.

title: applesauce drop cookies(diabetic)
directions: Sift flour, salt, cinnamon, nutmeg, cloves and soda together. Cream butter, sweetener and egg together until light and fluffy. Add flour mixture and applesauce alternately, mixing well after each addition.
Fold in raisins and all-bran.
Drop by level tablespoonfuls, about 1 inch apart, onto greased cookie sheet. Bake at 375° for 20 minutes, or until golden brown.
Yields 4 dozen cookies.

title: lemon buttermilk pound cake
directions: Cream butter, sugar and eggs.
Add flavoring, then dry ingredients and buttermilk.
Bake in greased and floured tube pan for 1 1/4 hours at 350°.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa, milk and margarine in a pan.
Bring to a full boil, boil just 1 minute, stirring often.
Remove from heat, stir in oats and vanilla.
Drop spoonfuls onto wax paper and let cool until hardened.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix cream cheese, pineapple, 1 cup pecans, green pepper, onion and salt.
Use a little of the juice to mix.
Refrigerate for 1 hour.
Shape into ball; roll in remaining chopped nuts.
Serve with assorted crackers.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Cream oleo and sugar.
Add flour, vanilla and potato chips. Drop by teaspoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar while hot (optional).

title: chocolate scotcheroos
directions: In large saucepan, combine corn syrup and sugar. Cook over medium heat until sugar dissolves; stir frequently. Bring to boil, then remove from heat. Stir in and mix well the peanut butter. Pour over Rice Krispies in a large bowl. Mix well. Pour into 10 x 16-inch cookie sheet with sides. Set aside.

title: barbecue chicken
directions: Place chicken in crock-pot.
Add water, salt, pepper and garlic powder.
Cook on high until hot.
Cook on low overnight.
Cool, skin, bone and remove fat.
Pull apart and chop.
Add barbecue sauce; mix thoroughly.
Place in baking dish.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Add mashed bananas to butter and sugar. Add eggs and salt. Add soda to sour milk. Vinegar can be added to milk to make it sour, 2 to 3 teaspoons.
Add flour. Nuts may be added, if desired. Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and drain.
Cook rice and drain.
Mix broccoli, rice, soup and 1/2 cup cheese together.
Pour into casserole dish. Sprinkle rest of cheese on top and bake at 350° until the cheese melts.

title: cinnamon apples
directions: Boil together for about 15 or 20 minutes. Then add 8 to 10 cups peeled, quartered apples (Jonathans are good). Simmer until apples are tender.
This is a big recipe.

title: toffee squares
directions: In saucepan, melt margarine over low heat.
Take off heat. Mix sugar, then blend other ingredients in order.
Press in ungreased dish.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients, except tomato sauce.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Spread 1/4 cup of tomato sauce on top of the mixture.
Bake for 45 to 70 minutes, depending on the oven.

title: uncle alvin's baked ahi
directions: Cut ahi into steaks about 3/4-inch thick.
Salt and pepper steaks and lay in baking dish (touching each other).
Mix mayonnaise and onions together and spread over top of steaks. Next, spread bread crumbs on top, then spread crab on top of crumbs.
Add optional mushrooms.
Melt butter, garlic powder and lemon juice.
Dribble over fish.
Bake at 350° for approximately 20 minutes.

title: bologna cups
directions: Place bologna in muffin cups.
Do not cut edges.
Stir together beans, mustard and molasses.
Place 1 tablespoon of mixture in center of bologna.
Top with cheese and onion.
Place under broiler; heat until bologna curls up into cup shape and cheese melts.
Serve hot with chips or French fries.

title: lime jello salad
directions: Dissolve jello as per directions on box.
When jello is almost completely
thickened,
beat
with electric mixer.
On slow speed, beat in cottage cheese and pineapple.
Let set to thicken and ready for use.

title: penuche icing
directions: Melt butter in saucepan.
Stir in brown sugar.
Boil and stir over low heat for 2 mins.
Stir in milk.
Bring to boil, stirring constantly.
Cool to lukewarm.
Gradually stir in confectioners sugar.
Place pan in ice water and stir until thick enough to spread.

title: fake easy strudel burrito tortillas(fast and easy)
directions: Place one burrito tortilla on working surface; butter well. Fill with chopped apples, nuts, sugar and sprinkle a little Minute Tapioca over the filling.
Place filling on one side.
Roll up the tortilla.
Place in a pan and bake at 325° until done.
Slice and serve.
Surprise!
It tastes and is as good as strudel.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix above together and chill.
Any fruit can be added or exchanged.

title: oreo ice cream
directions: Mix all ingredients and put in an ice cream freezer.
Follow direction on freezer for making ice cream.
Ice cream can be any flavor, just add what you like best!

title: chicken subs
directions: Chop chicken into cube.
Pan-grill chicken with seasonings, bell pepper and onion.
After browned, place sub rolls on top to steam for a minute.
Put on roll and add Provolone cheese.
Serve warm.

title: nantucket cranberry pie
directions: Grease a 9-inch pie tin. Put raw cranberries into the greased pie tin. Sprinkle with 1/2 cup sugar and nut meats.
Mix remaining ingredients in a bowl and pour over cranberry mixture. Bake at 325° for 35 to 40 minutes. Serve warm topped with whipped cream or vanilla ice cream.

title: hot chocolate
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Add water gradually so that it doesn't lump.
Heat to serving temperature.
Add marshmallows, if desired.

title: banana fluff
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water; add cold water and salt. Chill until cold and soupy.
Place in bowl of cracked ice or ice water and whip with beater until fluffy and thick like whipped cream.
Fold in bananas, pineapple and marshmallows.
Turn into mold; chill until firm.
Unmold and serve plain or with whipped cream.
Serves 10.

title: deviled homo and lesbo spread
directions: Mix ham, celery and egg.
Combine curry powder and olive oil. Add to ham mixture and moisten with mayonnaise.
Add salt to taste.

title: stuffed shells(big hit at parties and family gatherings)
directions: Boil 4 quarts of water.
Cook shells according to package directions.
Drain and cool.
In a large bowl, combine cheeses, eggs, parsley, oregano, salt and pepper.
Fill each shell with about 2 tablespoons cheese mixture.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Bake at 350° for 30 minutes in sheet pan.
Ice with powdered sugar icing.
May use half the coconut in icing.

title: zucchini bake
directions: Layer ingredients in order.
Cover with foil.
Bake 30 minutes at 325°.
Take foil off and brown under broiler.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat well until each ingredient is added.
Pour in unbaked pie shell; place pecan halves on top of liquid.
Bake 40 to 50 minutes in an oven set at 375°.

title: red cabbage (rotkraut)
directions: Put cabbage, apples, bay leaf, salt and cloves into bowl. Pour vinegar over mixture; mix well.
Cover and let set overnight.

title: easy chicken casserole
directions: Cook and debone chicken.
Combine chicken, soup and sour cream.
Spread in greased casserole dish.
Combine cracker crumbs and melted butter.
Sprinkle over chicken mixture.
Bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: broccoli rice casserole
directions: Saute onion in butter.
Cook broccoli per package instructions.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: *pispalita
directions: Cook spinach in pan with no water over low heat.
Drain.
Add cottage cheese, eggs and 2 tablespoons butter. Add salt to taste and mix thoroughly.

title: hidden valley ranch crackers
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour over crackers.
Mix to coat.
Place on cookie sheet and bake at 275° for 15 to 20 minutes. Stir every 5 minutes.

title: fudgy bonbons
directions: Melt chocolate chips and butter.
Remove from heat and stir in condensed milk.
Stir in flour, nuts and vanilla until combined well.
Cover each candy kiss completely with 1 level tablespoon of dough.
Place cookies on cookie sheet 1 inch apart.
Bake at 350° for 6 to 7 minutes.
Cookies will appear soft and shiny.
Cool. Melt white chocolate and Crisco and drizzle over cookies.
Cool.

title: oatmeal drop cookies
directions: Cover raisins with boiling water; let stand until raisins are soft.
Cream margarine and sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla and beat well.
Add flour, salt, cinnamon, nutmeg and baking soda mixture; mix well.
Stir in oatmeal and raisins and mix well.
Drop with spoon on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: almond gingersnaps(swedish pepparkakor)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Work butter until creamy. Add sugar, syrup, spices, baking soda, almonds and flour.
Turn onto floured baking board and knead until smooth.
Shape into 2 thick, slightly flattened rolls.
Wrap each in wax paper.
Chill.
Cut crosswise into thin slices.
Place on ungreased baking sheet and bake for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: cabbage rolls
directions: Mix together and roll in cabbage leaves.
Bake at 250° for 1 hour.

title: chinese almond cookies
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Cut in butter until mixture is like corn meal.
Add egg and almond extract; mix well and roll into a ball.
Roll slightly less than 1/4-inch; cut with a 2-inch round cutter.
Place on an ungreased cookie sheet, about 2 inches apart. (Or, form into 1-inch balls and flatten on cookie sheet with a spoon to form a circle.)
Place an almond half on top of each cookie.
Bake in a 325° oven for about 15 to 20 minutes.
Yields 50 cookies.

title: waldorf grape salad
directions: Toss first 5 ingredients.
Whip cream; add remaining ingredients except lettuce and blend well.
Fold dressing into salad.
Serve cold on lettuce cups.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: crab quiche
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Beat eggs until blended.
Stir in cream, onion, salt and cayenne pepper.
Pat crabmeat dry with paper towels.
Sprinkle crabmeat and cheese over pie shell.
Pour egg mixture over crabmeat and cheese.
Sprinkle with parsley.
Bake 15 minutes.
Reduce oven temperature to 300°.
Bake 30 minutes longer or until done.
Let stand for 10 minutes before cutting.

title: donna's pork barbecue
directions: Place pork in baking dish and add all ingredients, mixed well. Cover tightly with foil and bake at 250° for 3 1/2 to 4 hours. Shred meat with 2 forks and return to oven (covered) and continue baking 1 to 2 more hours until really tender.
Stir occasionally. If sauce cooks down, make additional and add to meat.
Serve with rolls.

title: wassail(holiday drink)
directions: In a large saucepan over medium heat, bring all ingredients to a boil.
Simmer for 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Put in a slow cooker and set on medium until time to serve. When ready to serve, strain. Pour into a punch bowl.
Serve warm.
Makes 20 servings.

title: sweet-sour meat balls
directions: Mix all ingredients together in small balls (egg size) in baking dish. Mix 1/2 cup catsup and 1/2 cup water and pour over top of meat balls.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Freezes well.

title: shoo-fly pie
directions: Mix flour, sugar, shortening and coconut to form crumbs. Reserve 1/2 cup for topping.
In another bowl, mix egg, honey and 3/4 cup hot water.
Add dry mixture.
Dissolve soda in remaining 1/4 cup hot water and add to mixture.
Pour into pie shell and sprinkle crumbs on top.
Bake at 375° for 35 minutes.
This pie will keep for several days without refrigeration.
This is an old Amish recipe.

title: peaches stuffed with macadamia nuts and apricot sauce
directions: In a large boiler, boil peaches for 2 minutes.
Remove from boiling water and immerse in cold water.
Remove from cold water and cut tops off peaches; core pit.
Cut a small area off the bottom so the peach will stand up straight.
Stand in greased baking dish.

title: jim's white chili
directions: Cook the chicken until done (I bake it first for 1 1/2 hours with a little water until tender). Cool and then cut into small pieces or shred. (You can also cut the raw chicken into pieces and cook it until done with the onion and garlic.) Saute the onion and garlic. Add the cooked chicken and spices and simmer a few minutes. Add to the undrained beans and chicken broth. Simmer for 2 hours. Add the cheese and stir until melted.

title: old fashioned french dressing
directions: Blend all the ingredients except the oils.
Then add olive and salad oils and mix well again.
Chill.
Shake before serving. Makes about 1 1/2-quarts.
This dressing keeps well in the refrigerator.

title: filo chicken
directions: Mix onion and mayonnaise.
Add lemon juice, garlic and tarragon.
Set aside.

title: age-zushi
directions: Cut bean cake squares in half and gently pull open the center of each, making little bags.
Simmer in water to cover, 20 minutes.
Drain.
Place chicken stock, soy sauce, sugar and a dash of monosodium glutamate in a saucepan.
Bring to a boil; add the bags and simmer 15 minutes.
Carefully spoon out bags; drain. Cook chicken breasts in remaining liquid for about 5 minutes. Remove.
Add mushrooms to pan and cook for 15 minutes.
If most of the liquid is gone, add 1/3 cup chicken stock, 1 teaspoon each of soy sauce and sugar, and a dash of monosodium glutamate.
Drain mushrooms when tender.
Snap ends off peas; pull side strings. Cut into small pieces.
Parboil in salted water for 1 minute. Drain and rinse with cold water.
Gently combine chicken, vegetables, omelet and sushi rice.
Fill bags; fold over top to close.
Makes 12 bags.

title: corn-pea salad
directions: Combine corn, peas, onion, celery, pimento and water chestnuts. Bring to boil the vinegar, sugar, oil, salt and pepper. Pour over vegetables. Stir. Cover and marinate a few hours or overnight.

title: pina colada fruit salad
directions: Start with whipped topping, drain fruit, cut pieces in half (if needed).

title: strawberry pretzel salad
directions: Mix pretzels, 3 tablespoons sugar and margarine together; press into a 13 x 9 x 2 inch pan. Bake at 400° for 7 minutes.

title: chicken and cheese enchiladas
directions: Heat soup, chillies and sour cream until mixed well.
Spread thin layer of soup mixture in 9 x 13-inch dish.
Sprinkle cheese and onion on shell, then 1 tablespoon soup mixture.
Roll and place in dish.
Pour remaining soup mixture over top of tortillas. Cover with remaining cheese.

title: cranberry apple or blueberry apple muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Beat egg; stir in milk and oil.
Mix in remaining ingredients until moistened.
Apple should be peeled and diced.
Cranberries should be halved.
(Batter should be lumpy.) Bake 20 minutes or until slightly browned.
Makes 12 to 15 muffins. Enjoy!

title: chili cheese dip
directions: Spread cream cheese in bottom of 2 glass pie plates.
Put chili on next, then Cheddar cheese. Serve with nacho chips. Makes 2 (9-inch) pies.

title: casserole rye bread
directions: In a large bowl, combine the 2 flours.
In a large bowl, mix 1 1/2 cups of mixed flours, sugar, caraway, sunflower seeds, pumpkin seeds and yeast.
In saucepan, combine water, milk and butter and heat slowly over low heat until warm (110°).
Add milk mixture to caraway mixture, enough to make a thick batter and beat for 2 minutes.
Add remaining flour to make stiff dough.
Stir in bowl until well mixed.
Cover with damp cloth; rise until doubled, 45 minutes.
Stir batter down 30 seconds.
Put in a 1 1/2-quart casserole or buttered bread pan.
Rise, covered, 30 minutes.
Bake in preheated 400° oven for 45 to 50 minutes until dark brown. Remove from pan or casserole and cool on rack.

title: nut fingers
directions: Combine all ingredients in a medium sized mixing bowl.
Mix well with hands. Shape into finger size cookies.

title: cheesy hash browns
directions: Mix hash browns, 1/2 cup of melted butter, salt, pepper, onion, soup and sour cream.
Add cheese.
Spread in a 9 x 13-inch buttered dish.

title: huckleberry crunch
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients
and
put in 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Mix remaining
ingredients
and
sprinkle over berries. Bake at 375° for 40 minutes; serve with cream or ice cream.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain peaches, pineapple and oranges.
Save juice.
Put 2 1/2 cups juice in saucepan.
Add pudding and cook until it boils. After cools, put pudding over fruit.
Just before serving, add bananas and grapes.

title: red and green salad
directions: Cut cauliflower, broccoli, mushrooms and onions into bite sized pieces.
Combine with dressing and marinate in refrigerator several hours or overnight.
Add cut up tomato and stir when ready to serve.

title: cherry supreme
directions: In medium size bowl, beat cream cheese until light and fluffy. Gradually add sweetened condensed milk and stir until well mixed. Blend in lemon juice and vanilla flavoring.
Turn into crust. Refrigerate 2 or 3 hours.
Garnish with chilled pie filling.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: In a very large bowl, combine cheese, soup, sour cream, onion, 1/2 cup margarine, salt and pepper; mix well.
Fold in hash browns.
Pour mixture into a greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Toss together corn flake crumbs and 1 tablespoon margarine. Sprinkle over casserole.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until casserole is golden brown and potatoes are tender.
Serves 10.

title: party cheese biscuits
directions: Cut the margarine into flour until the texture resembles coarse meal.
Grate cheese into a fine mixture.
Mix cheese, pepper and salt with flour mixture.
Fold in rice crispies.
Press the mixture into an individual biscuit cutter.
Remove the pressed mixture to a cookie sheet one at a time.
Bake at 350° for 13 to 15 minutes.

title: "can't be" beet jelly
directions: Combine beet juice, lemon juice and pectin in a large pan. Bring to a rolling boil.
Quickly add sugar and boil for 6 minutes.
Add the soft drink powder and mix thoroughly.
Pour into 8 ounce jelly jars.
Fill to within 1/2-inch to top of jars. Screw bands on lids tightly; process in boiling water bath 5 minutes.
Yields 4 (8 ounce) jars.

title: impossible pizza burger pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease 10 x 1 1/2-inch pie dish.
Cook ground meat and onion over medium heat until meat is brown; drain. Spread in pie plate.
Beat milk, baking mix, eggs, salt and pepper until smooth, 15 seconds in blender on high or 1 minute with hand beater.
Pour into pie plate. Bake 25 minutes.
Top with spaghetti sauce and cheese; bake for another 15 minutes.
Cool 5 minutes.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: chicken stir-fry
directions: Pour 1 tablespoon oil into a wok or large skillet coating bottom and sides; heat to medium high (325°) for 2 minutes.
Add broccoli and next 4 ingredients; stir-fry 4 minutes.
Remove vegetables from skillet.
Pour remaining 1 tablespoon oil into wok.
Add chicken; stir-fry 4 minutes or until tender.
Return vegetables to wok; stir in salad dressing, soy sauce and ginger. Serve over rice.
Yields 3 to 4 servings.

title: party spread
directions: Make paste of ingredients.
Spread on party rye.
Bake at 400° until brown.

title: chinese fried rice with bacon and mushrooms
directions: Cook bacon and drain.
Saute celery and onions in drippings until tender.
Add mushrooms, cooked rice, salt and soy sauce, stirring gently to coat all ingredients with soy sauce.
Cook 10 minutes longer on low, stirring occasionally.
Add crumbled bacon and mix well.
Serve.

title: colby cheese salad
directions: Cook pineapple and sugar for 5 minutes, stirring; cool.
Add mayonnaise, grated cheese and cut up pecans.
Fold in the whipped cream.
Put in loaf pan and chill.

title: carrot cake
directions: Sift all dry ingredients together.
Cream sugar and oil.
Add eggs one at a time, add carrots.
Combine carrot mixture with flour mixture.
Pour into 3 well-greased cake pans and bake at 325 degrees for 30 minutes or until done. Frost with cream cheese frosting.

title: baked beans
directions: In a large cast-iron skillet, brown hamburger meat with onion. Add beans, brown sugar and barbecue sauce.
Simmer 20 to 25 minutes.

title: harvest stew
directions: Brown meat in oil.
Add 2 cups water, barbecue sauce, carrots, potatoes, onions and salt.
Cover and simmer 1 hour.
Gradually add remaining water to flour, stirring until well blended.
Add flour mixture to hot meat and vegetables, stirring constantly until it boils and thickens.
Prepare biscuit mix like dumplings. Drop by tablespoons onto hot stew mixture.
Simmer 10 minutes. Cover; simmer another 15 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: mandarin orange salad
directions: Make Jell-O as directed on package; refrigerate until partially set (will stick to sides of bowl).
Remove from refrigerator and whip with electric mixer.
While still beating, gradually add the Cool Whip.
Fold in the mandarin orange sections.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle with chopped nuts.
Refrigerate.
Cut into squares for serving.

title: beer cheese dip
directions: Scoop out the center of the rye bread and break center into pieces.
Bring beer to a boil; add butter.
In a separate bowl, put cheese, onions and Worcestershire sauce.
Add beer and butter mixture and blend until smooth.
Place mixture into the bread bowl.
Refrigerate for 1/2 to 1 hour until cheese is firm.
Place on a serving tray with bread crumbs around the outside.

title: sugar-coated peanuts
directions: Cook
on high until it boils;
turn down and stir until liquid leavens.
Put in shallow pan.
Cook 15 minutes in oven (350°). Take out; stir and cook 15 more minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli per package directions.
Drain.
Combine all other ingredients, except crackers.
Mix with broccoli.
Pour into a greased casserole.
Sprinkle crackers on the top.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: shish kabob
directions: Trim part of fat from meat; cut meat in 2-inch cubes.
In large glass bowl, combine meat, onions, parsley, salt and pepper.
Pour over wine and mix thoroughly.
Refrigerate overnight.
When ready to barbecue, mix meat again.
Spear meat alternately with onions, tomatoes and peppers on long metal rods or small individual wooden skewers.
Cook over coals to desired degree of doneness.

title: aloha cake
directions: Bake cake mix as directed in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Cool.
Mix milk and instant vanilla pudding.
Beat well.
Add cream cheese. Beat well.
Spread over cooled cake.
Spread drained pineapple over top of pudding mixture.
Cover with Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with chopped nuts.
Place cherry halves on top.

title: peanut butter pudding
directions: Prepare pudding as directed on package.
Beat in peanut butter with rotary eggbeater.
Spoon pudding into 4 dessert dishes. Chill in refrigerator at least 1 hour.

title: bacon cheddar fondue
directions: Fry bacon and crumble.
Add onion and garlic (minced) to 1/4 cup bacon drippings.
Add soup, slowly stir in milk.
Blend until smooth.
Add cheese until melted.
Add bacon and rest of ingredients.
Pour into fondue pot and keep warm.
Garnish with bacon and parsley.
If mixture becomes too thick, add a little milk.
Makes 5 cups.

title: mexican layered dip(a big hit for a party)
directions: Brown ground turkey in skillet sprayed with nonstick cooking spray.
Add taco seasoning and water and simmer and stir until all water is cooked away.
Set aside to cool.
Spread refried beans evenly over bottom of 8-inch or 9-inch round or square baking dish. Layer with meat, green chilies, onion and sour cream.
Top with grated cheese and tomatoes.
Chill and serve with no-oil tortilla chips.
Recipe makes 8 servings.
Ultra low-fat.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Crush 1 pack of Ritz crackers and add enough milk to dissolve crackers. Beat eggs. Mix eggs, cracker mixture, eggplant, 1 cup cheese and 1/2 margarine. Pour into casserole dish. Crush remaining crackers and sprinkle over top of casserole. Melt remaining butter and pour over crushed crackers. Sprinkle remaining cheese over top. Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes or until cheese melts.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: In a buttered 8 x 8 or similar size casserole dish layer the asparagus, cream of celery soup, cheese, bread crumbs, butter, salt and pepper.
Place next layer starting with english peas, cream of mushroom soup, cheese, bread crumbs, butter, salt and pepper.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until bubbly.

title: yummy salad
directions: Dissolve cream cheese in heated soup.
Dissolve jello in 1/2 cup boiling water.
Stir the hot soup into the jello.
Blend, cool a bit, then add the other ingredients.

title: terrific apple cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat the oil and sugar.
Add the eggs. Beat until creamy.
Sift together flour and spices.
Stir into batter or use low speed on mixer.
Add all remaining ingredients. Mix.
Batter will be thick and lumpy.
Butter and flour a 13 x 9-inch pan, angel food tube pan or Bundt pan.
Cool in pan before turning out.
Bake a 13 x 9-inch pan for 1 hour at 350° or other pans for 1 hour and 15 minutes at 350°.

title: lime fluff pie
directions: Combine pie filling mix, gelatin, sugar and water in saucepan. Cook and stir over medium heat until mixture comes to a full boil.
Add lime rind and juice.
Pour into bowl.
Cover with plastic wrap and chill until cold and slightly thickened.
Fold in 2 1/2 cups Cool Whip.
Spoon into crust.
Freeze 1 hour or chill in refrigerator 3 hours.
Garnish with remaining Cool Whip.

title: mock ravioli
directions: Heat spaghetti sauce.
Set aside. Cook bow ties according to package directions, drain and set aside.
Mix together spinach, grated cheese, bread crumbs, parsley, garlic, salt and eggs. Grease a baking dish.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Allow hash browns to thaw.
Mix all ingredients together and place in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: oatmeal pie
directions: Mix well the eggs, sugar, brown sugar, oats, coconut, butter and vanilla.
Pour in pie shell and bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: grandma jane's tuna macaroni bake
directions: Cook macaroni in boiling water until tender; drain well.
Saute onion in margarine; remove from heat.
Add undiluted soup. Gradually add milk, tuna, seasonings and 2 slices of cheese. Heat, stirring occasionally, until mixture is hot and cheese is melted.
Mix in the macaroni.
Pour into a greased 2-quart rectangular baking dish.
Arrange remaining cheese on top.
Bake in moderate 350° oven for 5 to 10 minutes, until cheese melts.

title: one step lasagna
directions: Combine beef, water, salt
and spaghetti sauce.
In 9 x 13-inch pan layer 1/3
of
the spaghetti sauce mixture, 1/2 of noodles, 1/2 cottage cheese and 1/2 Mozzarella cheese.
Repeat layers, ending with
sauce.
Sprinkle
with
Parmesan
cheese. Bake, covered, with foil
at
350°	for
2 hours or microwave, covered, with plastic wrap on High for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: pork chop and potato dinner
directions: Mix soup, mushrooms, milk and onion in bowl; set aside.
Place sliced potatoes in nonstick casserole dish (or spray with Pam). Pour soup mixture over potatoes.
Trim fat and season pork chops. Brown only slightly in skillet and then place pork chops on top of potatoes and soup mixture.
Cover and bake at 375° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Mix
the
first
ingredients well.
Place chicken on top. Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 2 1/2 hours.

title: ranch style baked beans
directions: Brown meat in a large iron skillet.
Stir in soup mix, beans, catsup, mustard, vinegar and sugar.
Simmer 30 to 45 minutes. Pour into 2 1/2-quart bean pot to serve.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: best broccoli casserole
directions: Bring water and salt to a boil.
Add rice and cover. Remove from heat and let sit for 5 minutes.
Melt butter in skillet; combine rice, celery and onion with remaining ingredients. Pour into a greased 1 1/2 qt. casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cabbage soup
directions: Simmer in pot for 2 hours.

title: parmesan spinach spread
directions: Press spinach to dry. Combine spinach, 1 cup Parmesan cheese and next 7 ingredients. Spoon into a greased 1-quart baking dish. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes. Sprinkle with the remaining 1/4 cup Parmesan cheese and paprika. Bake an additional 10 minutes. Serve with crackers, party rye or small slices of Panera's Asiago cheese bread.

title: banana punch
directions: Bring 6 cups water and sugar to a boil in sauce pan.
Boil 5 minutes.
Cool completely.	Add frozen orange juice, 4 1/2 cups water and pineapple juice to sugar mixture.
Puree bananas in blender.
Add lemon juice.	Add to juice mixture.
Pour into 3 large zip lock bags (easier if plastic bag is put in loaf pan before pouring).
Freeze at least 12 hours to up to 3 weeks.
Thaw 4-6 hours before serving.
Add 1 liter ginger ale to each bag of punch.
Pour into punch bowl to serve.
Serves 20.

title: clam chowder
directions: Fry salt pork until crispy, remove pork and use the drippings. Add 2 cups of clam juice, diced potatoes and diced onions to the fat.
Cook covered 20 minutes until potatoes are cooked.
Add clams, 1 3/4 cups of milk and the cream.
Blend the remaining milk and flour together, stir this into the chowder.
Heat to boil stirring occasionally.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Serves 10 small bowls - serve with the cooked salt pork on top.

title: funnel cakes
directions: Beat
eggs
with milk.
Gradually beat in flour, sugar, salt and baking powder until very smooth.
Holding the opening of
a funnel
closed
with
your forefinger, fill funnel with batter. Controlling
the
flow
with your forefinger, dribble the batter into hot oil at 375°, starting at center of pan and swirling outward
in
a
circle.
Fry 2 or 3 minutes or until brown.
Drain on
absorbing
paper and sprinkle with powdered sugar.
Makes 2 dozen, depending on size.

title: hawaiian fruit dip
directions: In med. bowl, whisk pudding, and milk until well blended. Blend in sour cream. Stir in pineapple and coconut. Cover. Refrigerate until chilled, 30 min to an hour. Serve with fresh fruit dippers.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Combine butter, sugar and flour.
Stir in chips and vanilla. Drop by teaspoons on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° until lightly browned.
While still warm, sprinkle with sugar.

title: hush puppies
directions: Combine corn meal, flour, baking powder and salt.
Add minced onion and egg.
Stir in milk to make a stiff batter.
Drop by tablespoon into 1 inch hot fat (375°).
Fry until golden brown, about 3 minutes.
Drain on absorbent paper and serve at once. Makes about 20.

title: margie's supreme goulash
directions: Put water onto boil for macaroni.
Brown hamburger in a deep skillet.
Add tomato sauce and the cheese sauce to browned hamburger; stir well.
Shake on seasoned salt until a thin layer is over most of surface, stir in with hamburger mixture.
Strain macaroni and add to mixture.
Add chili powder to taste.

title: chicken party casserole
directions: Blend flour with 1/2 cup chicken broth.
Gradually add the remaining 2 cups of broth.
Bring to boil, stirring.
Add grated cheese and cook; stir until cheese is melted.
Remove from heat; stir in chicken.
In a 3-quart casserole, alternate layers of chicken mixture with the artichoke hearts and asparagus, beginning and ending with the chicken.
Sprinkle with more grated cheese, if desired.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Can be made ahead and refrigerated until needed.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix butter, sugar, Karo, salt, eggs, and vanilla together until well blended.
Stir in pecans.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350° until tests done.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Saute onion and celery in butter.
Cook rice according to package directions.
Add chicken, soup, water chestnuts and mayonnaise to onion and celery mixture.
Pour rice into buttered casserole dish.
Pour in chicken mixture and top with crushed crackers.
Dot with butter and bake at 400° until bubbly for about 30 minutes.

title: sugared pecans
directions: Beat together egg white and water until foaming.
Add pecan meat.
Mix well.
Add sugar and cinnamon and mix together well. Spread mixture on flat cookie sheet with sides.
Bake 45 minutes at 275°, stirring every 15 minutes.
After baking, spread on wax paper and dry before putting in container.

title: easy peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add peanut butter; cream well.
Add eggs; beat well.
Add flavoring.
Drop cookies on cookie sheet. Preheat oven to 350° and cook for 10 minutes.

title: farmers salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Add tomato juice, lemon juice and salt.
Chill to egg white consistency.
Fold in tuna, celery, macaroni and peas.
Turn into lightly greased baking dish and chill firm.
Cut into squares and serve on lettuce leaf with Mustard Salad Dressing.

title: holiday peppermint crunch bark
directions: Melt chocolate in double boiler.
Add the candy; mix gently. Pour onto ungreased, non-Teflon cookie sheet.
Put into freezer about 10 minutes.
Break into pieces and store in cool, dry place.

title: lunch meat loaf
directions: Grind all meats together and mix; add garlic.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Put in loaf pan.
Bake at 350° to 375° for 30 to 60 minutes.
When done, sprinkle with paprika.
Serve.

title: casserole
directions: Spray baking dish with nonstick spray. Mix milk and soup in separate bowl. Cover bottom of baking dish with chicken. Sprinkle with Mozzarella cheese. Pour soup mixture over the top and sprinkle with onion powder. Repeat another layer. Cover final layer with bread crumbs and drizzle with melted butter. Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: apple salad
directions: Cook the first 5 ingredients until thick on medium-low heat. Set aside to cool.
Peel and cut into bite size pieces the apples; add to cooled mixture.
Top with the softened cream cheese and Cool Whip; mix with mixer and put on top.
Garnish with chopped pecans.

title: palm beach cake
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients; pat in a baking dish.
Mix the remaining ingredients; then pour over cake mixture.
Bake for 45 to 50 minutes at 350°.

title: no bake pineapple pie
directions: Mix cream cheese and pineapple juice. Add pudding. When starts to thicken, pour into crust and chill.

title: peach dessert
directions: Use a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Put peaches in pan.
Spread.
Sprinkle with tapioca and coconut.
Add cake mix.
Sprinkle melted butter over cake.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.
Serve with ice cream or Cool Whip.

title: filled lemon cookies
directions: In small mixer bowl, beat butter and cheese until light and fluffy.
Beat in egg, vanilla and half the cake mix (dry) until smooth.
Stir in remaining cake mix.
(Dough will be stiff.) Cover; chill 1/2 hour.
Prepare Raisin Filling; cool.
Heat oven to 375°.
Roll about 1/4 of dough at a time 1/8-inch thick on lightly floured cloth-covered board.
Cut with 1 1/2-inch square cutter.
Place half of the squares on ungreased baking sheet; spoon 1/2 teaspoon filling on each.
Cut 1/2-inch "X" in center of remaining squares.
Place on filling and press together.
Bake 10 minutes or until very light brown around edges.
Makes about 4 dozen cookies.

title: sparkling fruit mold
directions: Stir boiling water into gelatin in large bowl at least 2 minutes until completely dissolved.
Refrigerate 15 minutes. Gently stir in cold ginger ale.
Refrigerate about 30 minutes, or until slightly thickened.
Gently stir for 15 seconds.
Stir in grapes and oranges.
Pour into 6-cup mold.
Refrigerate 4 hours. Unmold.
Garnish as desired.
Makes 12 servings.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix well ground round and sausage.
Add onion and green pepper, if desired.
Place in 1 (10 x 5 x 3-inch) baking dish or 2 (8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch) baking dishes (loaf style).
Bake at 350° until top is well browned.
Drain drippings.
Flip loaf over in pan (bottom up).
Continue to bake until top is well browned.
Drain drippings.
Cut or slice into servings.
Top with either a can of Meat Loaf Fixins, beefy mushroom soup or tomato paste and sauce mixed.
Bake until topping is bubbly.

title: chocolate oatmeal no bake cookies
directions: In heavy saucepan stir butter, sugar, cocoa and milk.
Bring to a boil and boil for 1 minute stirring occasionally.
Remove from heat and add peanut butter and vanilla.
Stir in oats.
Drop by teaspoonful onto wax paper.

title: no peek stew
directions: Mix all together and place in oven for 2 1/2 hours at 325°. Cover tightly and "no peeking".
Serve over noodles.

title: cheese fondue
directions: Put tomato juice and onion soup mix in large saucepot. Cook until boiling; lower to medium heat. Slice cheese
and add to above mixture. Cook until melted. Dip toasted bread cubes into hot cheese fondue.

title: hamburger dip
directions: Spread beans in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cook hamburger and onion. Drain and put over beans.
Add chilies, cheese and taco sauce. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Add sour cream on top, if desired.

title: banana oat bran muffins
directions: Mix all ingredients in order given.
Fill 12 muffin tins to top.
Bake approximately 20 minutes.
Do not overbake.
Makes a dozen.

title: almond chicken bake
directions: Heat oven to 460°.
Toss 3/4 cup cheese with flour.
Mix cheese, chicken, celery, 1/3 cup almonds, mayonnaise, juice and seasonings.

title: instant pumpkin pie
directions: *Or use 1 teaspoon pumpkin pie spice.

title: watergate salad
