directions: Add the dry pudding mix to the can of crushed pineapple in a large bowl.
Blend thoroughly.
Add marshmallows and fold in the Cool Whip.

title: stuffed zucchini
directions: Mix hamburg, rice, onion and eggs.
Slice zucchini lengthwise.
Hollow out seeds.
Place stuffing in zucchini and put in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cover with soup or paste.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: farm cookies
directions: In small bowl, combine flour, baking powder, soda and salt. Stir to mix well.
Set aside.
In large bowl, beat butter.
Add brown sugar and sugar; beat until fluffy.
Beat in eggs and vanilla.
Add flour mixture.
Beat until well mixed.
Stir in oatmeal, cornflakes, coconut and nuts.

title: jello mold
directions: Drain pears.
Heat juice to bubbling and dissolve jello.
Put cream cheese into jello.
Whip into jello.
Get almost set.
Cut pears up and put in mix and fold in.
Fold in Cool Whip and put into mold.
Serves 8 people.

title: italian buffet meatballs
directions: Put meat in bowl.
Add cheese, bread crumbs, garlic, parsley, salt and pepper.
Mix.
Make into balls and fry.
Place in sauce.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix cream of chicken soup and mushroom soup with chicken broth.
Mix stuffing mix with margarine.

title: chocolate truffle cake
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Grease bottom of 8-inch spring-form pan.
Melt chocolate and butter in the top of a double boiler. Remove from heat.
Add flour, sugar and water and blend well.
Add egg yolks, one at a time, beating well after each addition.

title: russian salad
directions: Melt marshmallows and cream cheese in milk.
Dissolve gelatin in hot water.
Add remaining ingredients.
Combine mixture; congeal.

title: mushroom lima beans
directions: Mix all together. Sprinkle crushed cheese crackers on the top. Bake until it bubbles.

title: white bean dip with toasted pita chips
directions: Combine bread crumbs and water and set aside to soak.
Cut fresh pepper into triangles or strips (1 inch wide); set aside.

title: chocolate thumbprint cookies
directions: Cream butter, sugar, egg yolk, milk and vanilla in small mixer bowl.
Combine flour, cocoa and salt.
Blend into creamed mixture. Chill dough about 1 hour or until firm enough to handle.
Prepare Vanilla Filling.
Roll dough into 1-inch balls.
Roll in sugar. Place on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Press thumb gently into center of each cookie.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes or until set.

title: rolled hermits cookies
directions: Mix ingredients and roll out.
Place on greased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes or until done.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Cream butter, gradually add sugar, creaming until light and fluffy.
Beat 1 minute on electric mixer or longer by hand.
Sift baking powder, flour and salt.
Add eggs, one at a time to creamed mixture beating well after each addition.
Add flour mixture alternating with milk and flavoring, beating after each addition until smooth.
Bake at 350° about 35 to 40 minutes.
Frost with favorite can frosting.

title: apricot glazed chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place chicken in a baking pan that has been sprayed with a nonstick cooking spray.
In a small bowl combine remaining ingredients.
Mix well and spread over chicken. Bake, uncovered, for 1 hour.
Makes 4 servings with 283 calories, 31 g protein, 14 g fat, 7 g carbohydrate and 99 mg cholesterol each.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix all ingredients. Roll into ball. Bake at 400° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: salt clay for ornaments
directions: Boil water.
Add salt to boiling water.
Stir.
Add 1 cup cornstarch.
Stir.
Remove from heat, add cold water and stir.
If not thick, put back on stove.

title: chocolate popcorn squares
directions: Combine Marshmallow Creme, chocolate pieces and corn syrup into a saucepan.
Cook over low heat until mixture is blended. Pour over popcorn and mix well.
Press into a buttered 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Cut into 1-inch squares.

title: microwave caramel corn
directions: Cook first 4 ingredients in microwave until boiling, plus 2 minutes.
Add soda and vanilla.
Pour over popped corn in a large paper sack and shake.
Microwave 1 1/2 minutes.
Shake.
Microwave 1 1/4 minutes. Shake and pour immediately onto waxed paper.

title: all-bran bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Mix All-Bran cereal, sugar, shortening and salt.
Pour boiling water over bran mixture.
Let cool, then add yeast.
Add egg and half of flour.
Beat well.
Add remaining flour.
Cover and let rise until double in bulk.
Punch down.
Form into 2 small loaves, place in buttered pans and let rise again until double.
Just before baking, brush tops of loaves with melted butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Yield:
12 servings.
Carbohydrate 32 g, protein 5 g, fat 9.3 g, calories 229.

title: hot rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1 cup of the water.
Add 1 teaspoon of sugar to activate it.
Heat milk and remaining 1/2 cup of water.
Beat eggs, sugar and salt together.
Add yeast and milk.
Add enough flour for desired consistency.
Knead.
Let rise until doubled. Punch down and let rise again.
This is not critical if you are rushed for time.
Work each roll into a small ball.
Let rise 20 to 30 minutes.
Bake at 375° until golden brown.

title: cranberry orange bread
directions: Sift dry ingredients together into large bowl.
Put juice and rind in measuring cup and add enough boiling water to make 3/4 cup.
Add to dry
mixture.
Add egg and melted shortening and mix just enough to moisten flour mixture.
Fold in cranberries and nuts.
Bake in greased loaf pan at 325° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: pork chops on rice(makes 6 servings.)
directions: Brown and season pork chops.
Put the uncooked rice in a baking dish; lay the pork chops on top.
Place a slice of tomato or a spoonful of stewed tomatoes and a slice of onion on each chop.
Pour over this a can of consomme soup.
Bake in a covered dish 45 minutes at 300°.
Uncover and bake 15 minutes longer.
Be sure to have baking dish large enough to take care of the rice as it cooks.

title: baked tomatoes
directions: Remove the stems of tomatoes and cut in half crosswise without peeling.
Mix first 3 ingredients and spread on cut halves of tomatoes. Mix crumbs and butter and sprinkle on top.
Bake at 350 degrees until crumbs are slightly brown, about 30 min.

title: crawfish dip
directions: Saute 1/3 of green onions and onions in butter until onions are transparent.
Add crawfish and 1/3 green onion and Worcestershire sauce.
Simmer 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add garlic powder.
Bring liquid to an easy boil; reduce heat.
Add soup and 1/3 green onions.
Simmer 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add seasonings and salt to taste.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Stir occasionally.
Can be served over spiral pasta or used as a dip with crackers.

title: sand tarts
directions: Cream
butter, shortening and sugar.
Add
flour,
nuts and vanilla.
Mix well.
Pinch off pieces the size of a marble and roll about finger size.
Shape into
crescents.
Bake
on ungreased cookie sheet at 325° for 25 to 30
minutes.
Do
not brown.
Roll in powdered sugar while warm.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Cook onion, celery and mushroom slices in butter and chicken broth in saucepan until golden.
Add soup; mix flour and juice from mushrooms and add to mixture.
Heat for 5 minutes.
Add pimentos and chicken.
Pour over cooked spaghetti.
Top with grated cheese and sliced olives.
Bake 30 to 45 minutes at 325° until bubbly.

title: savory pot roast
directions: Peel potatoes and carrots. Place in large Dutch oven or slow cooker with roast and halved onion. Combine other ingredients and pour over roast. Cover and simmer over medium heat approximately 3 hours.

title: dream bars
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients (will be crumbly) and pat into a 9 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.
Cool.
Cover crust with dates.
Combine remaining ingredients except dates.
Spread mixture over crust and dates.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Bake cake as directed on box in 9 x 13 pan.
When cake comes out of oven, punch holes in hot cake with handle of wooden spoon. Spread milk over cake and then spread with strawberry topping. Cool completely and then spread Cool Whip on top.
Refrigerate overnight before serving.

title: herbed burgers
directions: Mix together and form patties.
If desired, freeze in individual sandwich bags to be used as needed.

title: microwave caramel corn
directions: Combine margarine, brown sugar, corn syrup and salt in 2-quart casserole.
Heat on High power 6 to 7 minutes or until boiling. Stir 3 or 4 times during cooking time.
Working quickly, add baking soda and vanilla.
Stir until thoroughly mixed.
Place popped corn in an unrecycled brown paper grocery bag.
Pour hot syrup over corn and shake or stir.
Heat on High power 1 minute and 45 seconds, stirring 2 times.
Cool and break into pieces. Store in Tupperware container.

title: seafood casserole
directions: Cook onion, pepper and celery until soft in 1 tablespoon oil. Add seafood.
Simmer gently until seafood is cooked, about 5 minutes.
Add drained mushrooms.
Add lobster bisque or shrimp soup or Newberg sauce and 1/2 cup milk.
Newberg sauce is made with milk; do not add extra.
Pour all into casserole dish.
Sprinkle top with grated cheese and bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.
Serve with rice.
If serving more than 6, use 1 pound each of the seafood. One can of crabmeat may also be added.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Cook carrots. Drain and cool.
Cut onion and pepper in rounds and mix with carrots.
Mix together other ingredients and pour over vegetables.
Cover and marinate for 12 hours or more. Will keep 2 to 3 weeks.

title: baked bootleg beans
directions: Dice bacon and fry. When 1/2 done, add onion. When onion is slightly brown, pour off grease and add pork and beans. Add brown sugar, vinegar and catsup. Stir well, then cover pan with lid. Bake slowly in a 300° oven for a couple hours or, if you prefer, can simmer slowly on top of stove for about 30 minutes.

title: microwave banana pudding
directions: Mix flour, sugar, milk and vanilla in microwave dish.
Cook on High for 5 minutes.
Add some hot liquid to egg yolks.
Beat.
Add to hot liquid.
Return to microwave and cook 2 to 3 minutes. Stir, cook another 2 to 3 minutes.
Stir.
Do this until thickness desired.
Pour over wafers and bananas.

title: souper corn bread
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Combine soup, eggs and milk.
Stir in muffin mix until well blended.
Fold in sausage.
Pour into 9-inch square greased pan.
Bake 20 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: aunt nelda's crunchies
directions: Melt chocolate chips in a heavy boiler.
Add marshmallows, chow mein noodles and peanuts.
Mix well.
Drop by teaspoons on wax paper.
Let harden.

title: quick cake
directions: Mix cake mix, butter or margarine, 1 egg and nuts together with spoon.
Put into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix 2 eggs, cream cheese and sugar together and pour over mix in pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: simply snappy supper
directions: Proceed to cupboard or freezer.
Locate anything edible and pull tab to open.

title: coca-cola salad
directions: Drain juice off cherries and pineapple.
Heat to boiling. Measure to make 2 cups of liquid.
If not 2 cups, add enough water to juice to make up the difference.
Pour over jello and dissolve. Add cherries, pineapple, cheese and nuts.
Place in refrigerator. Let stand overnight.

title: orange-pineapple congealed salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in 2 cups of hot water.
Add orange juice, pineapple, drained oranges and nuts, if desired.
Chill until firm. Serve on lettuce.

title: orange julius
directions: Mix together in blender and serve.
Serves 4.

title: special "k" bars
directions: Bring sugar and syrup to boil; add peanut butter.
Pour over Rice Krispies.
Press into buttered cookie sheet.
Melt chips together and spread over bars.
Let cool, then chill 1 hour before serving.

title: pastel sherbet cream punch
directions: Combine pineapple juice, sherbet and half of ice cream.
Beat until smooth.
Add sparkling water.
Spoon remaining ice cream into punch.
Serve immediately.
Yields 14 (1/2-cup) servings.

title: cheesy fondue
directions: Combine cheeses and flour; toss to coat.
Bring wine to simmer over medium heat in fondue pot.
Gradually add cheeses, stirring until melted.
Stir in nutmeg and pepper.

title: caramel corn
directions: Melt margarine in large pan.
Stir in sugar, corn syrup and salt; boil five minutes without stirring.
Remove from heat; stir in soda.
Gradually pour over popped corn that has been put in 2 (9x13-inch) pans.
If you spray the pans first with pam, it helps in the cleaning up.
Mix well.
Bake at 250° for 45 minutes to an hour, stirring occasionally.
Cool, then break apart.
Store in airtight container.

title: peanut butter bonbons
directions: Mix peanut butter, powdered sugar and margarine until smooth. Add Rice Krispies and nuts.
Mix and form into balls.
Melt chocolate chips and paraffin in a double boiler or microwave. Pick up balls with a fork and dip in chocolate.
Set on wax paper. Refrigerate until set.

title: rigatoni with broccoli(yield:  4 servings)
directions: 1. Cut broccoli into bite-sized pieces.
Bring 4 quarts of water to boil, add broccoli and salt to taste.
Cook 5 minutes. Scoop broccoli out and set aside.

title: potatoes basquaise
directions: Peel and rinse potatoes.
Place them in a 3-quart pot.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer for 20 minutes.
Drain.
When cooled, cut into 1/8-inch slices.

title: ralph's dirty baked potato soup
directions: Bake the potatoes and cut into strips (1/2 to 1/4 inches). Leave the skins on and use a clean pair of scissors to cut into small pieces. Put pieces into a gallon zip lock bag and smash them-leaving some pieces whatever size you like in you soup.

title: peanut butter bread
directions: Dissolve soda in the sour milk.
Mix all ingredients together. Grease 1 loaf pan.
Bake at 300° about 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: pheasant casserole
directions: Saute sausage and drain off grease.
Saute mushrooms and onion in sausage grease.
When nearly done, add water chestnuts. Squeeze lemon juice over mixture.
Cook rice according to package. Make a white sauce of flour, butter, milk, chicken broth, salt and pepper.
Lightly toss together the meat, sausage, rice and mushroom mixture.
Pour sauce over and toss again.
Bake at 350° for at least 1 hour.
Turn off and leave in oven until ready to serve.
This improves the flavor.
Sprinkle with almonds before serving.

title: seafood salad
directions: Cook spaghetti and cool.
Then add to other ingredients. Chill 3 hours.

title: dirt cake
directions: Cream together the cream cheese, powdered sugar and butter; set aside.
Mix together the vanilla pudding and milk.
Fold Cool Whip into pudding mixture.
Mix pudding mixture with cheese mixture.

title: baked bananas
directions: Remove skins from the bananas. Cut in halves lengthwise. Put in shallow pan. Mix all ingredients. Bake in slow oven 20 minutes. Baste bananas with half of the mixture.

title: sherried turkey
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Brown turkey in margarine in frying pan. Remove to casserole dish.
Cook onion in remaining margarine; stir in soup and sherry.
Pour over turkey.
Bake casserole, covered, for 1 hour.
Serve over rice.

title: butter goody cake
directions: Combine butter, 1 egg, pecans and cake mix.
Mix well and press in the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
(Mixture will be stiff.)

title: carrot cake
directions: Sift flour, sugar and cinnamon into large mixing bowl.
Add vanilla and oil, then one egg at a time.
With electric mixer, beat until smooth.
Fold in nuts and bake in ungreased tube cake pan at 350° for about 1 1/2 hours.
Leave in pan until cool.
This cake can be used with or without being iced.

title: never fail pie crust
directions: Cut the flour, shortening and salt together in a bowl.
Mix the egg, vinegar and water together in a cup.
Add to the flour mixture.
Makes two 9-inch crusts.

title: cheesy hash browns
directions: Combine thawed potatoes and the next 7 ingredients.
Top with corn flakes and butter.
Bake, uncovered, for 50 to 60 minutes at 250°.

title: makes its own crust coconut pie
directions: Combine all ingredients in order and mix well.
Pour into greased deep 10-inch pie plate.
Bake 45 minutes or until golden brown at 350°.

title: steamed cabbage
directions: Chop
fresh
cabbage.
Put
in skillet with butter, hot water and
a pinch of red pepper.
Cook over high heat 8 to 10 minutes. Do not overcook.
Sprinkle with salt and serve.

title: corn bread dressing
directions: Cook onion and celery in broth only for 5 minutes.
Crumble corn bread and biscuits with pepper and sage.
Add to mixture, stirring until all bread is moist and soft.
Add chopped boiled eggs; turn by hand for 1 to 2 minutes.
Dressing should be rather soft.
Pour in a 2-quart baking dish and cook at 400° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: helen's cherry cream pie
directions: Beat cream and 1/2 cup sugar until creamy.
Add large tub of Cool Whip.
Pour into graham cracker crust.
Chill.
Top with cherry pie filling and 1/2 cup sugar.

title: zebra parfaits
directions: Prepare the chocolate pudding with 2 cups milk, following package directions.
When the pudding is prepared, layer it with the whipped topping in parfait glasses.
Start with chocolate pudding and finish with whipped topping.
There should be about 3 layers of each.
Top each serving with a cherry.
Makes 4 servings.

title: beef and barley soup
directions: In large Dutch oven or kettle, heat oil over medium heat. Brown beef; add onions, carrots, celery, tomatoes, water and bouillon. Bring to boil. Cover and simmer for about 2 hours or until beef is tender. Add barley; simmer another 50 to 60 minutes or until barley is done. Yields 10 to 12 servings (3 1/2 quarts).

title: blueberry pie
directions: To make crust, follow directions on graham cracker crust box (make 2 pies).
Sprinkle cinnamon on crust.
Combine Cool Whip, cream cheese and confectioners sugar.
Mix with mixer and spread over pie crusts.
Just add blueberries on top.
Chill and serve.

title: red devil pound cake
directions: Cream sugar and oil.
Add eggs one at a time.
Add flour and milk alternately.
Add cocoa, salt and vanilla.
Add food coloring last.
Mix all ingredients well.
Pour into greased tube pan. Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: red, white and blue salad
directions: Note:
This salad takes time to prepare since each layer must set until firm before the next layer is added.

title: fruit pie
directions: Mix milk, Cool Whip, fruit and nuts until well blended.
Mix the lemon juice in last; do not omit, this is what makes the pie set.
Spoon mixture into pie shells and chill until ready to serve.
The pies can be frozen.

title: grandma's apple cake
directions: Mix all ingredients in one bowl.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch (greased and floured) baking pan.
Cook at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Top with cream cheese icing or powdered sugar.

title: date confections
directions: Boil sugar, margarine, egg, dates and nuts 5 minutes until blended.
Add Rice Krispies.
Cool.
Drop by tablespoon in powdered sugar.

title: jack pot
directions: Brown the ground beef with the onions in a skillet.
Add soup, water and noodles.
Cover.
Cook until noodles are tender.
Add beans, 1/2 of cheese and seasonings.
Pour into a casserole dish. Sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Makes 8 servings.

title: irish soda bread
directions: Sift all dry ingredients together twice.
Mix in raisins and caraway seed.
Add buttermilk and mix all together.
If batter is dry, add 1 or 2 tablespoons more buttermilk.

title: lemon chicken hawaiian style
directions: Cut chicken into 1-inch pieces.
Heat 2 to 2 1/2 inches oil to 360°.
Mix remaining ingredients until smooth.
Dip chicken in this and fry until golden brown, turning once.
Drain.
Serve with Lemon Sauce.

title: oven steamed chicken
directions: Prepare chicken and put in a large
casserole.	Add the onion, bell pepper, salt, pepper and cream
of
mushroom soup. Cover and cook in oven at 375° for 1	1/2 hours or until done. Serve rice and a green salad.

title: maple-glazed nuts
directions: In heavy skillet, stir together syrup, cinnamon, butter and salt.
Cook and stir over medium heat until mixture becomes brown and starts to thicken.
Add vanilla and the nuts and toss until the nuts are covered.

title: venison roll-ups
directions: Cut steaks into a total of approximately six pieces and pound until thin; set aside.

title: cabbage rolls
directions: Saute sausage, rice and onion together in skillet, stirring often, about 5 minutes.
Pour off fat.
Cool, and add seasoning and cottage cheese.
Drop cabbage leaves into boiling water for about 1 minute; drain.
Divide rice mixture into four parts.
Wrap each part in 2 cabbage leaves and fasten with a toothpick.
Arrange in a 1-quart casserole.
Mix soup, milk and sour cream together. Pour over cabbage rolls and bake, covered, at 350° for 1 1/4 hours.
Yield:
4 servings.

title: hungarian beef
directions: Cook and stir beef, onion and garlic in oil in 8-inch skillet over medium heat until beef is brown.
Stir in mushrooms, 1/2 cup water, the catsup, instant bouillon, paprika and salt.
Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer until beef is done, about 15 minutes.
Mix 1/4 cup water and the flour.
Stir into beef mixture.
Heat to boiling, stirring constantly.
Boil and stir 1 minute.
Stir in sour cream.
Heat, stirring occasionally, until hot.
Serve over buttered macaroni.

title: pizza bread
directions: Press bread like pizza dough.
Mix all ingredients together. Put mixture on dough, saving a little for top.
Put pepperoni on dough and Mozzarella cheese.
Roll up like jellyroll, pinching ends together.
Brush remaining mixture on top.
Spray cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Cool and slice.

title: mushroom spoon bread
directions: For Microwave: Combine dry ingredients.
Stir in soup, milk and Egg Beaters.
Pour into microwave-safe 4-quart bowl. Microwave on High for approximately 6 minutes or until surface appears dry.
Remove and allow to sit approximately 5 minutes before serving.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix all ingredients well; form small balls. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until golden brown.

title: refreshing vegetable dip
directions: Combine all ingredients, except vegetables, until smooth. Add vegetables (well drained) and stir.
Serve with platter of celery and carrot sticks, raw cauliflower bits and cherry tomatoes to dip.

title: no cream ice cream
directions: Peel bananas, wrap in foil and freeze for several hours.
Chop bananas into about 1-inch long slices.
Place bananas in blender with 1/8 to 1/4 cup skim milk and blend at medium speed, turning blender on and off to combine bananas and milk (consistency should be lumpy).
Add strawberries (or other frozen fruit), a few at a time.
Add Equal, vanilla and enough milk to make a creamy consistency.
It is done when mixture has look of soft serve ice cream.
This mixture does not freeze well, but may be frozen up to about 30 minutes.

title: caramel fudge cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Prepare cake mix as directed on package. Pour 2 cups of batter into greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake 15 minutes.
In heavy saucepan over low heat, melt caramels and margarine.
Remove from
heat.
Add sweetened condensed milk.
Mix well.
Spread caramels over cake.
Spread remaining batter over caramels.
Top with pecans.
Bake 30 minutes or until cake springs back when lightly touched.
Cool.

title: angel cake supreme
directions: Make cake according to directions and bake in a greased and floured jelly roll pan. While cake is slightly warm, spread pineapple gently over top. Cool. Combine cream cheese, pudding mix and milk and beat until thick. Spread on top of cake. Spread whipped topping on top. Sprinkle with finely chopped nuts or coconut, if desired. Chill before serving.

title: no bake chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Bring sugar, milk, oleo and cocoa to a boil while stirring constantly.
Boil for 2 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add salt, vanilla and oatmeal.
Stir together.
Drop by tablespoon on waxed paper.
Cool completely.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Combine peanut butter, Crisco, brown sugar, milk and vanilla.
Beat at medium speed until well blended.
Add egg.
Beat just until well blended.
Combine flour, salt and baking soda.
Add to creamed mixture at low speed.
Drop heaping teaspoonfuls 2 inches apart onto ungreased baking sheet.
Bake 7 to 8 minutes or until set and just beginning to brown.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: lasagne
directions: Brown beef and drain off fat. I cook mine in a 350° oven with water about 30 minutes. Put beef, after salting with garlic salt, in a large saucepan. Add jars of sauce, tomato sauce and paste. Let simmer on stove. Boil water with salt added; put oil in at same time as noodles. Boil 10 to 13 minutes; drain water off of noodles. In 13 x 9-inch (at least) pan, layer sauce, cheese (mix eggs with cottage cheese), shredded cheese and Parmesan cheese. It makes about 2 layers. Don't put final layer of cheese until a few minutes before removing from oven or it will burn. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: super crab dip
directions: Mash drained crabmeat.
Add other ingredients and mix.
Chill in refrigerator at least 1 hour before serving.
Serve on crackers.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Top with crushed Ritz crackers.
Bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: granny's meat loaf
directions: Combine ingredients; cook at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: caramel pecan baked apples
directions: Core apples and peel strips from top of each.
Place 1 in custard cup.
Fill core with 1 teaspoon butter.
Microwave 2 minutes.
Top each with 1 tablespoon caramel topping and 1 tablespoon nuts.
Cook 30 seconds; let stand.

title: 7-layer brownies
directions: Melt butter on cookie sheet; add cracker crumbs and press out onto sheet.
Layer other ingredients in order given and drizzle milk over all.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cut into bars.

title: texas chili
directions: Brown hamburger and drain. Add diced onion and saute until tender. Add other ingredients and cook until heated through.

title: all at once spaghetti dinner
directions: Cook and stir beef and onion in a heavy 3-quart saucepan until meat loses its red color.
Stir in seasonings and olives.
Pour in 3 cans tomato sauce and the water.
Bring to a boil.
Break uncooked spaghetti in half.
Sprinkle in a little at a time, stirring it into the sauce.
Cover tightly and simmer 25 to 30 minutes over low heat.
Stir in cheese until it is melted.
Serves 6.

title: french garlic chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Heat oil in heavy flameproof casserole dish wide enough to accommodate single layer of chicken.
Add chicken, salt and pepper.
Saute for 5 minutes on both sides; remove from pot.
Add garlic, all but 1 clove; saute until brown. Don't worry about scorching.
Spread cloves; return chicken to pot.
Add wine, thyme and rosemary; cover.
Bake for 55 minutes; remove from oven.
Heat cognac in small pan and light.
Pour over chicken; shake until flames die.
Sprinkle with parsley.
Toast bread lightly; rub extra garlic (cut) on both sides of bread.
To serve, place 2 pieces of bread on each plate, chicken, garlic cloves and sauce.
Spread extra garlic cloves on bread.
Enjoy.

title: garlic salad dressing
directions: Grind pickles and garlic together.
Mix oil, ketchup and mayonnaise.
Blend with the ground up ingredients.
Makes about 3 pints.
Refrigerate.
(This makes enough to share with a friend.)

title: spicy oven-fried chicken
directions: Melt margarine in 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
Set dish aside.
Combine bread crumbs, paprika and onion powder in a shallow dish.
In separate bowl, combine egg substitute and mustard.
Brush mixture on skinned chicken.
Coat chicken pieces with bread crumb mixture and place pieces in prepared baking dish.

title: chocolate-tipped butter cookies
directions: In a mixing bowl, cream 1 cup butter and sugar. Add flour and vanilla; mix well. Cover and refrigerate for 1 hour. Shape 1/2 cupfuls of dough into 1/2-inch thick logs. Cut logs into 2 1/2-inch pieces; place on ungreased baking sheets. Bake at 350° for 12 to 14 minutes or until lightly browned. Cool on wire racks. In a microwave or double boiler, melt chocolate and remaining butter. Dip one end of each cookie into chocolate and then into nuts; place on waxed paper until chocolate is set. Yield: About 5 dozen.

title: super chicken casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients, except almonds and potato chips. Bake in greased casserole at 350° for 45 minutes.
Top with nuts and chips.
Bake for 15 minutes more.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: watercress fish sauce
directions: Melt butter in saucepan.
Blend in flour.
Gradually add milk and cook until thickened.
Add additional milk if sauce is too thick.
Stir in steak sauce and season with salt and pepper. Blend in watercress.
Serve immediately with hot poached, steamed or broiled fish.
Makes 1 cup.

title: chinese style fried rice(low-fat)
directions: Bring 1 cup of water to a boil in a saucepan.
Stir in the rice.
Remove from heat.
Cover and let stand for 5 minutes.
Cook egg in margarine in a skillet until set.
Add onion and rice. Cook and stir over medium heat until rice and onion are lightly browned, about 5 minutes.
Combine remaining 1/3 cup water and soy sauce.
Stir into rice.
Serve hot.
Yield:
about 4 servings.

title: burox
directions: Fry hamburger meat, onion and bell pepper in a pan and drain. Boil cabbage until tender and drain.
Mix cabbage with meat and add cheese and soup.
Cook all ingredients until cheese is melted. Put spoonful of ingredients into a section of bread dough.
Pinch ends together to seal and bake at 400° until brown.

title: karidopeta(walnut cake)
directions: Use 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.

title: ham ball
directions: Blend deviled ham, olives, mustard and hot sauce.
Form into a ball on a serving dish.
Chill about 1 hour and then reform. Combine cream cheese and milk; frost ball with mix.
Chill; remove from refrigerator 15 minutes before serving.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add eggs, flour and soda and sour cream.
Beat well.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: strawberry pretzel salad
directions: Crust:
Mix margarine, pretzels and 3 tablespoons sugar together; press into bottom of 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: out of this world fruit dip
directions: In small bowl, combine all ingredients; mix well.
Serve with fresh fruit, vanilla wafers and graham crackers.
This is wonderful for strawberries!

title: tofu cheesecake
directions: Combine all ingredients in a bowl.
Place in blender; whiz until very smooth.
Empty into pie crust.
Smooth top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Top with fruit topping.

title: peanut brittle
directions: In heavy iron skillet, mix sugar and syrup; cook, while stirring, until sugar is dissolved.
Stir in raw peanuts and cook (on medium-high heat) until mixture turns brown and peanuts start popping.
Remove from heat; add salt and soda.
Stir as little as possible to get mixed.
Pour on buttered cookie sheet.
Let cool; break into pieces.

title: pigs in a blanket
directions: Pull apart layers of dinner roll.
Wrap little wieners inside pastry.
Secure with toothpick.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.

title: layered chocolate butterscotch bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 13 x 9-inch baking pan. In 1 1/2-quart mixing bowl, combine vanilla wafers, melted butter and vanilla; stir to blend.
Press into prepared pan.
Sprinkle with coconut, chocolate and butterscotch pieces.
Pour condensed milk all over the top; sprinkle with peanuts.
Bake near center of 350° oven for 20 to 27 minutes or until edges are lightly browned. Cool completely.
Cut into bars.
Cover; store in refrigerator. Yield:
3 dozen.

title: rock candy
directions: Stir sugar, corn syrup and water over low heat until dissolved.
Cook without stirring over high heat to the hard crack stage, 310°.
Remove from heat.

Add coloring and flavoring if desired (1 teaspoon vanilla, 1 1/2 teaspoons peppermint extract, 1/2 teaspoon almond extract or a few drops of oil of cinnamon). Pour the mixture onto a greased cookie sheet or shallow pan.
When cold, break into pieces.
Makes about 1 sheet pan.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli.
Mix together soup and cheese, gradually adding milk, mayonnaise and egg.
Place broccoli in casserole dish.
Pour mixture over the top.
Then put a teaspoon of butter and bread crumbs over the casserole.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: custard pie
directions: Mix together eggs, sugar, salt, milk and vanilla.
Strain custard mixture into unbaked pie shell.
Sprinkle with nutmeg. Bake in hot oven at 425° for 25 to 35 minutes or until knife comes out clean.

title: people puppy chow
directions: Melt and blend together the first 3 ingredients.
Add cereal. You may also use corn puffs and roasted peanuts, if desired.
Stir to coat cereal.
Spread on cookie sheet to dry a bit, then put into 2 large plastic bags with powdered sugar.
Shake lightly to coat cereal pieces.
Store in airtight container.

title: nutty caramel clusters
directions: Grease baking sheet or line with wax paper; set aside.
In a 1-quart microwave-safe casserole, combine caramels, butter and milk.
Cook, uncovered, on High for 1 to 2 minutes or until soft enough to stir smooth, stirring once during cooking.
Stir in nuts.
Drop from a teaspoon onto the prepared baking sheet.
In a 1-cup glass measure, combine chocolate chips and shortening. Cook, uncovered, on High, for 1 to 2 minutes, or until soft enough to stir smooth, stirring once during cooking.
Just like caramels, chocolate pieces retain their shape even when melted.
Drizzle chocolate over each cluster.
Cool to room temperature.
Cover and chill until firm.
Store tightly covered in the refrigerator. Yields about 25 pieces.

title: cream cheese dip
directions: Dice up scallions.
Mix with cream cheese and French onion soup mix.
Serve with crackers or tortilla chips.

title: low carb fish or chicken
directions: Spray baking dish with Pam.
Combine all ingredients except cheese and spread over fish or chicken.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and bake until fish is flaky or chicken is moist but not pink.

title: quail(for 8 to 12 quail)
directions: Bring to a boil; drop fresh or frozen quail in and cook on low heat until tender.
Let stand in water 1 to 3 hours.

title: pork chops with rice
directions: Brown pork chops and remove from pan. Add tomatoes, onion, green pepper, salt and pepper.
Mix together and add rice.
Add water and mix.
Lay pork chops on top.
Cover and cook 35 minutes or until rice is tender.

title: simple crab quiche
directions: Line a 9-inch quiche dish or deep-dish pie plate with pastry. Trim excess around edges.
Prick bottom and sides of pastry with a fork.
Bake at 425° for 5 minutes.
Cool.
Sprinkle crabmeat, cheese, green onions and 1 tablespoon parsley evenly into pastry shell.
Combine next 4 ingredients, stirring well; pour over crabmeat mixture.
Bake at 325° for 35 to 40 minutes or until set. Let stand 10 minutes before serving.
Garnish with parsley sprigs, if desired.

title: heavenly hash
directions: Mix gelatin in hot water and stir until completely dissolved. Add cream cheese (broken into small pieces), fruit cocktail, marshmallows, and pecan pieces.
Mix together.
Refrigerate to allow gelatin to set.
Remove from refrigerator and fold in Cool Whip.
Return to refrigerator for several hours to set.

title: soft molasses cookies
directions: Mix ingredients in the order given.
Drop by spoonful onto baking sheet.
Bake in a 350° oven for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: filled angel food cake
directions: Invert cake onto a serving plate.
With a serrated knife, carefully cut a one inch layer from the top of the cake.
Remove the layer and set aside.
Cut around cake 1 inch from the outer and inner edges to within 1 inch of bottom.
Carefully tear out the center portion of the cake to leave a shell.
Remove crumbled portion.

title: diet barbecue sauce
directions: Mix well in blender until smooth.

title: zucchini relish
directions: Chop fine the zucchini, bell peppers and onion.
Mix with salt.
Let stand, covered, in refrigerator overnight.
Drain and rinse in cold water.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cook 20 minutes and seal in hot jars.
Makes 6 pints.

title: easy chicken and rice casserole
directions: Mix soups and rice together in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch baking dish that has the melted margarine in the bottom.
Layer chicken on top and sprinkle salt, pepper, onion and garlic powder to your taste.
Cover with aluminum foil and bake in a 350° oven for at least one hour.

title: italian beans parmesan
directions: In skillet, saute onion and pepper in butter until soft.
Add potatoes and saute 2 minutes. Add tomatoes.
Cook over high heat until slightly thickened.
Add beans.
Heat thoroughly.
Sprinkle with cheese.

title: broccoli-cauliflower salad
directions: Chop vegetables into bite-size pieces and chop green onions. Combine remaining ingredients into a sauce and pour over the vegetables.
Let marinate 2 hours or overnight.
Sprinkle top with bacon chips just before serving.
Optional topping:
sliced black olives or raisins.

title: cream cheese pumpkin bars
directions: Beat eggs, sugar, oil and pumpkin until light and fluffy. Stir together dry ingredients, add to pumpkin mixture and mix well.
Spread batter into an ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
When cool, put Cream Cheese Icing on top.

title: cocktail sauce
directions: In small bowl, combine all the ingredients and season to taste.
Refrigerate, covered, and serve chilled.
Will keep in refrigerator several weeks.
Sauce is good with hot or cold seafood.
Yield: 1 1/2 cups.

title: candied yams
directions: Peel and slice the raw sweet potatoes.
Melt butter in the bottom of a skillet; add raw sliced sweet potatoes.
Cover with the sugars.
Pour over the water and cover.
Cook over medium heat until mixture thickens and the potatoes are tender.
Add vanilla just before serving.

title: date nut fingers
directions: Beat eggs until foamy.
Beat in sugar and vanilla.
Sift dry ingredients and stir into other ingredients.
Mix in nuts and chopped dates.
(Best if mixed with hands to blend dates completely into mixture.)
Spread into greased 8-inch square pan. Bake in moderate slow oven (325°) for 25 to 35 minutes or until top has a dull crust.
Cut in finger sized pieces while warm. Cool, then remove from pan and roll in powdered sugar.
Makes 21 fingers (1 x 2 1/2-inches).

title: cherry cobbler
directions: Mix first four ingredients together.
Add flour and baking powder.
Mix well.
Bake in a cake mold 1 hour in a 325° oven.

title: quick mince crescents
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In medium saucepan combine mincemeat and water.
Cook as package directs.
Cool completely.

title: sweet potato carter
directions: Mix all ingredients together with electric mixer.
Add pear juice, if needed, to make the mixture smooth.
Put in a greased pan (about 2-quart dish).
Cover with topping.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: cocktail meatballs
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Combine all ingredients and shape into 1 1/2-inch balls.
Place in oven and bake for 10 minutes.
Remove from oven and drain.

title: puff pastries
directions: Sift flour; measure.
Add salt and sift again.
Combine margarine and boiling water in saucepan.
Keep over low heat until butter is melted.
Add flour all at once and stir vigorously over low heat until mixture forms a ball and leaves side of pan. Remove from heat.
Add unbeaten eggs one at a time, beating thoroughly after each egg; continue beating until a thick dough is formed.
Drop by small teaspoon on greased sheet.
Bake at 400° until beads of moisture no longer appear on surface 20 to 22 minutes.
When cool, cut tops off.
Put a small amount of chicken or crab salad in puff.
Replace top.
Refrigerate.
May be frozen and filled later.

title: tater tot pie
directions: Brown ground beef and onions in a skillet.
Drain off excess grease.
Add celery soup, chicken soup, and tater tots.
Mix well. Pour into a greased 12 x 8 baking dish.
Bake at 325 degrees for 1 hour.
